  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1:   1Although we cannot be sure, it is possible that Ezra compiled
        the Psalms and wrotePs. 1as an \u201Cintroduction\u201D to the Psalter. Others
        believePs. 1was written by David or Jeremiah.The Tree of Life"
      title: "  1Although we cannot be sure, it is possible that Ezra compiled the
        Psalms and wrotePs. 1as an \u201Cintroduction\u201D to the Psalter. Others
        believePs. 1was written by David or Jeremiah.The Tree of Life"
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]What delight comes to the one who follows God\u2019s
        ways! [[COMMENT(1)]]He won\u2019t walk in step with the wicked,nor share
        the sinner\u2019s way,nor be found sitting in the scorner\u2019s seat."
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">1</span>
        content: "  <span class=\"ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs\">Although we cannot
          be sure, it is possible that Ezra compiled the Psalms and wrote</span>   
          <span class=\"ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs\">as an \u201Cintroduction\u201D
          to the Psalter. Others believe</span>    <span class=\"ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs\">was
          written by David or Jeremiah.</span>    "
      - number: 1:1
        content: "    is the contrast of those who follow God\u2019s ways with those
          who choose their own path. Read through this psalm with the purpose of
          learning how to live with God in the first place.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "His passion is to remain true to the Word of \u201CI AM,\u201Dmeditating
        day and night [[COMMENT(0)]] on the true revelation of light. "
      comments:
      - number: 1:2
        content: "  To meditate on the revelation of light day and night means to
          meditate 24/7 on what is good and delightful. However,    signifies a period
          of enlightenment () and    signifies a period of obscurity. Both when we
          have the light of insight and when we seem to be in the dark, meditation
          is the key to unlock the revelation of God.      Or \u201CTorah.\u201D
          From    we learn that the righteous and the wicked are distinguished by
          what they delight in.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He will be standing firm like a flourishing treeplanted [[COMMENT(0)]]
        by God\u2019s design,deeply rooted by the brooks of bliss,bearing fruit in
        every season of life.He is never dry, never fainting,ever blessed, ever prosperous. "
      comments:
      - number: 1:3
        content: "  Or \u201Ctransplanted.\u201D That is, God planted our lives from
          where we were into a place of blessing. See  .      The metaphors found
          in this verse can be paraphrased as \u201CNo matter what he sets out to
          do, he brings it to a successful conclusion.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But how different are the wicked.They are like chaff [[COMMENT(0)]]
        blown away by the wind.
      comments:
      - number: 1:4
        content: '  Chaff is lifeless, only a shell without the kernel. Chaff depicts
          a life without the truth of Christ. See  .  '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The wicked will not endure the day of judgment,for God will not defend
        them.Nothing they do will succeed or endure for long,for they have no part
        with those who walk in truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: But how different it is for the righteous!The Lord embraces their
        paths as they move forwardwhile the way of the wicked leads only to doom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Coronation of the KingAct I \u2013 The Nations Speak"
      title: "The Coronation of the KingAct I \u2013 The Nations Speak"
      number: 1
      content: How dare the nations plan a rebellion.Their foolish plots are futile!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 2:1
        content: "  Or \u201CWhy are they devising emptiness?\u201D Some Jewish scholars
          believe that    and    form one psalm, for the theme of both is the way
          of the godly versus the way of the ungodly.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Look at how the power brokers of the worldrise up to hold their summitas
        the rulers scheme and confer togetheragainst <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        and his Anointed King, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: "3: Act II \u2013 God Speaks"
      title: "Act II \u2013 God Speaks"
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLet\u2019s come together and break away from the Creator.Once
        and for all let\u2019s cast off these controlling chainsof God and his Christ!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 2:3
        content: "  The word found here for \u201CChrist\u201D is the Hebrew word
          for \u201CMessiah\u201D or \u201CAnointed One.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: God-Enthroned [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>.</smallcaps>
        merely laughs at them;the Sovereign One mocks their madness!
      comments:
      - number: 2:4
        content: '  The Aramaic is  , the Aramaic form of  or Lord      '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then with the fierceness of his fiery anger,he settles the issue
        [[COMMENT(0)]] and terrifies them to death  with these words:'
      comments:
      - number: 2:5
        content: "  Or \u201CIn good time he drives them away.\u201D      Or \u201Csnorts
          with anger.\u201D The Hebrew word    (\u201Cfiery anger\u201D) has a homonym
          that means \u201Cnose.\u201D    "
    - name: "6: Act III \u2013 The Son Speaks"
      title: "Act III \u2013 The Son Speaks"
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI myself have poured out [[COMMENT(0)]] my King on Zion,  my
        holy mountain.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 2:6
        content: "  The Hebrew word () is frequently used for pouring out a drink
          offering to God. See  . Jesus was \u201Cpoured out\u201D as a consecrated
          offering.      The word    is found 157 times in the Bible and 38 times
          in the Psalms.      For the believer today, Zion is not only a place but
          also a realm where Christ is enthroned.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI will reveal the eternal purpose of God.For he has decreed
        over me, \u2018You are my favored Son.And as your Father I have crowned you
        as my King Eternal.Today I became your Father."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Ask me to give you the nations [[COMMENT(0)]] and I will do it,and
        they shall become your legacy.Your domain will stretch to the ends of the
        earth.
      comments:
      - number: 2:8
        content: "  Or in the Masoretic Text \u201CAsk wealth of me.\u201D    "
    - name: "9: Act IV \u2013 The Holy Spirit Speaks"
      title: "Act IV \u2013 The Holy Spirit Speaks"
      number: 9
      content: "And you will shepherd them [[COMMENT(0)]] with unlimited authority,crushing
        their rebellion as an iron rod  smashes jars of clay!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 2:9
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint.      God\u2019s \u201Ciron
          rod\u201D can be a metaphor for the power of spiritual truth. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CListen to me, all you rebel kingsand all you upstart judges
        of the earth.Learn your lesson [[COMMENT(0)]]  while there\u2019s still time."
      comments:
      - number: 2:10
        content: "  Or \u201CDo what is wise.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Serve and worship the awe-inspiring God.Recognize his greatness and
        bow before him,trembling with reverence in his presence. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 2:11
        content: "  Or \u201Crejoice with trembling.\u201D The Hebrew word for \u201Crejoice\u201D
          means \u201Cto spin around with excited emotions\u201D or \u201Cto twirl.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Fall facedown before him and kiss the Son [[COMMENT(0)]]before his
        anger is roused against you.Remember that his wrath can be quickly kindled!But
        many blessings are waiting for allwho turn aside to hide themselves in him!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 2:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cbe ruled by the Son.\u201D The Hebrew word for \u201Ckiss\u201D
          is    and can also mean \u201Cto be ruled by\u201D or \u201Cbe in subjection
          to\u201D the Son. Yet another possible translation of this difficult verse
          is \u201Cbe armed with purity.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Covered by the GloryThe Humbling of a King'
      title: Covered by the GloryThe Humbling of a King
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s song when he was forced to flee from Absalom, his
        own sonLord, I have so many enemies, so many who are against me."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: The Help of God'
      title: The Help of God
      number: 2
      content: "Listen to how they whisper their slander against me, saying:\u201CLook!
        He\u2019s hopeless! Even God can\u2019t save him from this!\u201DPause in
        his presence  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 3:2
        content: "  This is the Hebrew word  , a puzzling word to translate. Most
          scholars believe it is a musical term for pause or rest. It is used seventy-one
          times in the Psalms as an instruction to the music leader to pause and
          ponder in God\u2019s presence. An almost identical word,  , means \u201Ca
          massive rock cliff.\u201D It is said that when    is spoken, the words
          are carved in stone in the throne room of the heavens.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But in the depths of my heart I truly knowthat you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        have become my Shield;You take me and surround me with yourself. [[COMMENT(0)]]Your
        glory  covers me continually.You lift high my head. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:3
        content: "  Many translations render this \u201CYou are a shield around me.\u201D
          The ancient Hebrew can be translated \u201CYou, O&nbsp;Lord, are my taker\u201D
          (Augustine). The implication is that God shields us by taking us into himself.
          Jesus Christ is the taker of humanity, the one who was made flesh. He not
          only took our nature, he also took our sins that he might take us into
          glory.      Or \u201Cmy glory.\u201D      In the time of David, to lift
          up the head signified acquittal when judged, being freed from the prison
          of shame. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '4: The Song of Safety'
      title: The Song of Safety
      number: 4
      content: "I have cried out to you, [[COMMENT(0)]]  <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        from your holy presence. You send me a Father\u2019s help.Pause in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 3:4
        content: "  The Hebrew reads \u201CI have cried out to you with my voice.\u201D
          How else do we cry out to God\u2014isn\u2019t it always with our voice?
          But the word for \u201Cvoice\u201D has many different Hebrew meanings.
          It can also mean \u201Cthe bleating of a lamb.\u201D David was God\u2019s
          lamb bleating out to his Shepherd for help.      Or \u201Cfrom your holy
          hill.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So now I\u2019ll lie down and sleep like a baby\u2014then I\u2019ll
        awake in safety, for you surround me with your glory."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Secret of Strength'
      title: The Secret of Strength
      number: 6
      content: "Even though ten thousand dark powers [[COMMENT(0)]] prowl around
        me,I won\u2019t be afraid."
      comments:
      - number: 3:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cmilitary troops.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Rise up and help me, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>! Come and save
        me, God!For you will slap them in the face,breaking the power of their words
        to harm me. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 3:7
        content: "  Or \u201CYou broke the teeth [lies] of the wicked.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For the Lord alone is my Savior. [[COMMENT(0)]]What a feast of favor
        and bliss he gives his people!Pause in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 3:8
        content: '  The Hebrew word used sixty times in the Psalms for deliverance
          is  , a variant form of the name for Jesus. This is pointing us to where
          our salvation is found.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Evening Prayer for Help'
      title: An Evening Prayer for Help
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One [[COMMENT(0)]]For the end,  a melody
        by King DavidGod, you are my righteousness, my Champion Defender.Answer me
        when I cry for help!Whenever I was in distress, you enlarged me. [[COMMENT(1)]]I\u2019m
        being squeezed again\u2014I need your kindness right away!Grant me your grace,
        hear my prayer, and set me free!"
      comments:
      - number: 4
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here, found in the inscription of fifty-four
          Psalms, is usually rendered as \u201Cchoirmaster\u201D or \u201Cchief director
          of music.\u201D It is taken from the root word for \u201Cshining\u201D
          or \u201Cbrilliant\u201D (i.e., purity, holiness). Another way to translate
          \u201Cchoirmaster\u201D is \u201Cthe shining one\u201D or \u201Cthe one
          who glitters from afar.\u201D Jesus Christ is the chief musician of all
          eternity who sings in the midst of his people ().      As translated from
          the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201Cstringed instruments\u201D or \u201Csmiting.\u201D    "
      - number: 4:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cyou created room for me.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Listen to me, you elite among men:How long will you defame my honor
        [[COMMENT(0)]]and drag it down into shame?Will you ever stop insulting me?How
        long will you set your heart on shadows,chasing your lies and delusions?Pause
        in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 4:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cmy glorious one.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: May we never forget that <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> works wonders
        [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>  </smallcaps>for every
        one of his devoted lovers.And this is how I know that he will answer my every
        prayer.
      comments:
      - number: 4:3
        content: "  There is considerable variation in possible translations from
          different manuscripts. Some manuscripts read \u201Csets apart a faithful
          one for himself.\u201D Another possible translation is \u201Chas revealed
          to me his marvelous love.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Tremble in awe before the Lord, and do not sin against him.Be still
        upon your bed and search your heart before him. [[COMMENT(0)]]Pause in his
        presence
      comments:
      - number: 4:4
        content: "  Or \u201CMeditate on your bed and repent [lament].\u201D It is
          always wise at the end of every day to cleanse our hearts in God\u2019s
          grace and mercy.  "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Bring to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> the sacrifice of righteousness
        and put your trust in him.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Lord, prove them wrong when they say, \u201CGod can\u2019t help you!\u201DLet
        the light of your radiant facebreak through and shine upon us!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The intense pleasure you give mesurpasses the gladness of harvest
        time,even more than when the harvestersgaze upon their ripened grainand when
        their new wine overflows.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Now, because of you, Lord, I will lie down in peace and sleep comes
        at once,for no matter what happens, I will live unafraid!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Song of the Clouded DawnMorning Watch'
      title: Song of the Clouded DawnMorning Watch
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneFor her who receives the inheritance,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] by King DavidListen, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, to my
        passionate prayer! [[COMMENT(1)]]Can\u2019t you hear my groaning?"
      comments:
      - number: 5
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here is    or \u201Cflutes.\u201D It can
          also be translated \u201Cinheritances.\u201D The early church father Augustine
          translated this as \u201CFor her who receives the inheritance,\u201D meaning
          the church of Jesus Christ. The Father told the Son in    to ask for his
          inheritance; here we see it is the church that receives what Jesus asks
          for. We receive our inheritance of eternal life through the death and resurrection
          of the Son of God. The Septuagint reads \u201CFor the end,\u201D also found
          in numerous inscriptions of the Psalms.    "
      - number: 5:1
        content: "  Or \u201CMy words\u2014give them a hearing, Lord!\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Don\u2019t you hear how I\u2019m crying out to you?My King and my
        God, consider my every word,for I am calling out to you."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Making It Right'
      title: Making It Right
      number: 3
      content: 'At each and every sunrise you will hear my voiceas I prepare [[COMMENT(0)]]
        my sacrifice of prayer to you.Every morning I lay out the pieces of my life
        on the altarand wait for your fire to fall upon my heart. '
      comments:
      - number: 5:3
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cprepare\u201D is  , a priestly term
          for lighting the altar fire, preparing a sacrifice, and laying it out in
          order upon the altar to be consumed.      Implied in the concept of preparing
          the morning sacrifice. The Aramaic text states, \u201CAt dawn I shall be
          ready and shall appear before you.\u201D The Hebrew can also be translated
          \u201CI\u2019ll be on the watchtower [for the answer to come].\u201D See 
          ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I know that you, God, are never pleased with lawlessness,and evil
        ones will never be invited into your house.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Boasters collapse, unable to survive your scrutiny,for your hatred
        of evildoers is clear.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Multitude of Mercy'
      title: Multitude of Mercy
      number: 6
      content: You will make an end of all those who lie.How you hate their hypocrisy
        and despise all who love violence!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But I know that you will welcome me into your house,for I am covered
        by your covenant of mercy and love.So I come to your sanctuary [[COMMENT(0)]]
        with deepest aweto bow in worship and adore you.
      comments:
      - number: 5:7
        content: "  Or \u201CI come to the temple of your holiness.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: Multitude of Sins'
      title: Multitude of Sins
      number: 8
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, lead me in the pathways of your pleasurejust
        like you promised me you would,or else my enemies will conquer me.Smooth
        out your road in front of me,straight and level, so that I will know where
        to walk.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Their words are unreliable.Destruction is in their hearts,drawing
        people into their darkness with their speeches. [[COMMENT(0)]]They are smooth-tongued
        deceivers, flattering with their words.
      comments:
      - number: 5:9
        content: "  Or \u201Ctheir throat is an open grave.\u201D  "
    - name: '10: Multitude of Blessings'
      title: Multitude of Blessings
      number: 10
      content: Declare them guilty, O&nbsp;God!Let their own schemes be their downfall!Let
        the guilt of their sins collapse on top of them,for they rebel against you.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: But let them all be glad,those who turn aside to hide themselves in
        you.May they keep shouting for joy forever!Overshadow them in your presence
        as they sing and rejoice.Then every lover of your name will burst forth with
        endless joy.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Lord, how wonderfully you bless the righteous.Your favor wraps around
        each one and covers themunder your canopy of kindness and joy.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1:   6Psalm 6is a part of the daily prayer ritual of religious Jews.A
        Cry for HealingHow Long?'
      title: '  6Psalm 6is a part of the daily prayer ritual of religious Jews.A
        Cry for HealingHow Long?'
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]For the Pure and Shining OneA song for stringed instruments,
        for the new day [[COMMENT(1)]] by King David<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        don\u2019t condemn me.Don\u2019t punish me in your fiery anger. [[COMMENT(2)]]"
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">6</span>
        content: '    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">is a part of the
          daily prayer ritual of religious Jews.</span>    '
      - number: 6
        content: "  This is the Hebrew word  . Although we cannot be certain, many
          scholars believe it to mean \u201Ceighth.\u201D It could represent a harp
          with eight strings, an octave, the eighth division of singers, the eighth
          day, or the eighth month. Eight is the biblical number of a new beginning,
          a new day. Jewish rabbis have taught that the number eight is the number
          of the future messianic age when Messiah comes and makes all things new.    "
      - number: 6:1
        content: '  David implied that he had sinned and needed forgiveness. This
          is the first of seven penitential psalms (;  ;  ;  ;  ;  ).    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Please deal gently with me, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>;show me
        mercy, for I\u2019m sick and frail and weak.Heal me, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        for I\u2019m falling apart. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cmy bones are shaking.\u201D Bones are often used metaphorically
          for our inner being.    "
    - name: '3: Return to Me'
      title: Return to Me
      number: 3
      content: "My soul is so troubled; but you,<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2014how
        long? [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:3
        content: '  The Hebrew ends abruptly, with sudden silence and broken syntax.
          Words failed David, too broken to finish his sentence. This sudden silence
          is a figure of speech called aposiopesis.    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, turn to me and rescue my lifebecause
        I know your faithful love will never fail me.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Extreme Anguish'
      title: Extreme Anguish
      number: 5
      content: "In the darkness of death who remembers your name in worship?How could
        I bring you praise if I\u2019m buried in a tomb? [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:5
        content: "  Or \u201CSheol,\u201D the realm of the dead. This is the first
          psalm to mention the grave (or Sheol). It is depicted in the poetic literature
          of the Hebrews as a vast wasteland, a stronghold of darkness, and a beast
          of prey.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I\u2019m worn out with my weeping and groaning.Night after night
        I soak my pillow with tears, [[COMMENT(0)]]and flood my bed with weeping."
      comments:
      - number: 6:6
        content: "  Or \u201CI cause my bed to swim  .\u201D Our beds are frequently
          the washing place where the sheep are sheared (). The bed was the place
          of David\u2019s sin; it became the place of his weeping. Even as Adam sinned
          in a garden, Jesus wept in a garden over Adam\u2019s sin.    "
    - name: '7: He Heard My Cry'
      title: He Heard My Cry
      number: 7
      content: "My eyes of faith  [[COMMENT(0)]] won\u2019t focus anymore, for sorrow
        fills my heart.There are so many enemies who come against me!"
      comments:
      - number: 6:7
        content: "  The Hebrew is singular, \u201CMy eye;\u201D a likely metaphor
          for the eye of his heart. David\u2019s faith was growing weak.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Turn from me, all you troublemakers! [[COMMENT(0)]]For <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        has turned to hear the sound of my weeping.
      comments:
      - number: 6:8
        content: '  See  ;  .    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Yes!  <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>  my healer has heard all my pleadingand
        has taken hold of my prayers [[COMMENT(0)]] and answered them all.
      comments:
      - number: 6:9
        content: "  Or \u201Caccepted my prayers.\u201D The Hebrew word can mean
          \u201Cto grasp,\u201D \u201Cto lay hold of,\u201D \u201Cto marry,\u201D
          or, figuratively, \u201Cto accept.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now it\u2019s my enemies who have been shamed.Terror-stricken, they
        will turn back again, [[COMMENT(0)]]knowing the bitterness of sudden disgrace!"
      comments:
      - number: 6:10
        content: '  See  ;  .  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Song for the Slandered SoulRescue Me'
      title: Song for the Slandered SoulRescue Me
      number: 1
      content: "David\u2019s passionate song [[COMMENT(0)]] to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>To
        the tune of \u201CBreaking the Curse of Cush, the Benjamite\u201D <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        my God, I turn to hide my soul in you.Save me from all those who pursue and
        persecute me."
      comments:
      - number: 7
        content: "  The inscription reads \u201Cshiggaion,\u201D which means \u201Ca
          loud cry\u201D and is taken from a Hebrew word that means \u201Croar.\u201D
          It is a wild and passionate song. Have you ever been under such pressure
          that you felt like roaring? That is a \u201Cshiggaion.\u201D Some scholars
          believe the central thought of the word is that of wandering. It may also
          indicate the style of music to which the song was written.      The name
          Cush means \u201Cfirelike,\u201D \u201Cburned,\u201D or \u201Cblackened.\u201D
          This person\u2019s identity is not definite, but some believe this is an
          oblique reference to Saul, whose heart was burned and blackened by his
          sin and whose character was \u201Cfirelike.\u201D Saul was a Benjamite.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "There is none to deliver me but you!Don\u2019t let my foes fall upon
        me like fierce lions with teeth bared.Can\u2019t you see how they want to
        rip my soul to shreds?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, my God, if I have done evil like they
        say I have,and my hands are guilty,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: if I have wronged someone at peace with me,if I have betrayed a friend,
        repaying evil for good,or if I have unjustly harmed my enemy,
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Vindicate Me'
      title: Vindicate Me
      number: 5
      content: Then let my enemy pursue and overtake me.Let them grind me into the
        ground.Let them take my life from me and drag my dignity through the dust!Pause
        in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, arise in your anger against the anger
        [[COMMENT(0)]] of my enemies.Awaken your fury and stand up for me!Execute
        the judgment  you have decreed against them.
      comments:
      - number: 7:6
        content: "  Or \u201Coutrages (plural).\u201D      Or \u201CCommand justice!\u201D
          It is in God\u2019s hands alone to bring true justice to the earth, for
          he is the Righteous Judge.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: All the people gather around you.Return to your place on high to preside
        over them. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 7:7
        content: '  There is at least a hint here of the resurrection and ascension
          of Jesus, who had all authority to judge given to him and now rules from
          on high.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You are <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> who judges the people.Vindicate
        me publicly, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, and restore my honor and integrity.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]Declare me innocent.
      comments:
      - number: 7:8
        content: "  Augustine, an early church father, translates this word as \u201Charmlessness.\u201D
          David saw himself as harmless to his enemies. This is what integrity is
          all about. We maintain our character even when misunderstood or persecuted.
          Are you like this?    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Once and for all, bring to an end the evil tactics of the wicked!Establish
        the cause of the righteous,for you are the righteous God, the soul searcher,who
        tests every heartto examine the thoughts and motives. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 7:9
        content: "  Or \u201Chearts and kidneys,\u201D which is a Hebraic way of
          saying all of human nature, including our thoughts, motives, and feelings.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: God, your wraparound presence is my shield.You bring victory to all
        who are pure in heart.
      comments: []
    - name: "11: God\u2019s Lethal Weapons"
      title: "God\u2019s Lethal Weapons"
      number: 11
      content: God, your righteousness is revealed when you judge.Because of the
        strength of your forgiveness,your anger does not break out every day. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 7:11
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. Although the Hebrew is \u201CGod
          is angry during all the day,\u201D this verse has other possible translations.
          The Latin Vulgate: \u201CGod is a judge, righteous, strong, and patient.
          Will he be angry every day?\u201D The Septuagint: \u201Cnot bringing forth
          his anger every day.\u201D The Syriac: \u201Che is not angry every day.\u201D
          In other words, even though God judges righteously, his anger does not
          break out every day. There are over ten words in Hebrew that can be translated
          \u201Canger.\u201D The word used in this verse is    and comes from a word
          that means the \u201Croar\u201D or \u201Cgroan\u201D of a camel.    "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "Yet if one does not repent,you will not relent to sharpen [[COMMENT(0)]]
        your shining sword.You have an arsenal of lethal weaponsthat you\u2019ve
        prepared for them.You have bent and strung your bow,making your judgment-arrows
        shafts of burning fire."
      comments:
      - number: "7:12\u201313"
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Csharpen\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Cbrighten.\u201D God will make bright his sword of truth for the righteous
          and to the ungodly. God\u2019s Word is a sword to bring light and judgment
          to the heart.  "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "Yet if one does not repent,you will not relent to sharpen [[COMMENT(0)]]
        your shining sword.You have an arsenal of lethal weaponsthat you\u2019ve
        prepared for them.You have bent and strung your bow,making your judgment-arrows
        shafts of burning fire."
      comments:
      - number: "7:12\u201313"
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Csharpen\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Cbrighten.\u201D God will make bright his sword of truth for the righteous
          and to the ungodly. God\u2019s Word is a sword to bring light and judgment
          to the heart.  "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Look how the wicked conceive their evil schemes.They go into labor
        with their lies and give birth to trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They dig a pit for others to fall into,not knowing that they will
        be the very oneswho will fall into it.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Thankful Praise'
      title: Thankful Praise
      number: 16
      content: Every pit-digger who works to trap and harm otherswill be trapped
        by his own treachery.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But I will give my thanks to you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,for
        you make everything right in the end.I will sing my highest praise to the
        God of the Highest Place!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s SplendorGod\u2019s Majesty"
      title: "God\u2019s SplendorGod\u2019s Majesty"
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneSet to the melody of \u201CFor the Feast
        of Harvest\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]] by King DavidYahweh, our Sovereign God,your
        glory streams from the heavens above,filling the earth with the majesty of
        your name!People everywhere see your splendor."
      comments:
      - number: 8
        content: "  Or \u201CFor the director of music, according to gittith.\u201D   
          could mean \u201Cwinepress,\u201D or refer to a musical instrument common
          to the Gittites, making it a Philistine lute (;  ). The Moffat translation
          reads \u201CSet to a vintage melody.\u201D This inscription in the Septuagint
          is \u201CTo the director over the wine vats.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: Human Dignity'
      title: Human Dignity
      number: 2
      content: "You have built a stronghold by the songs of children.Strength rises
        up with the chorus of infants.This kind of praise has power to shut Satan\u2019s
        mouth.Childlike worship will silence [[COMMENT(0)]]the madness of those who
        oppose you."
      comments:
      - number: 8:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cmuzzle.\u201D There may be a vast difference between
          the glory of the heavens and the little mouths of children and babies,
          yet by both the majestic name of the Lord is revealed. It is amazing that
          perfected praises do not rise to God from the cherubim or seraphim, but
          from children and babies, the weakest of humanity.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Look at the splendor of your skies,your creative genius glowing in
        the heavens.When I gaze at your moon and your stars,mounted like jewels in
        their settings,I know you are the fascinating artist who fashioned it all!But
        I have to ask this question:'
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Why would you bother with puny, mortal manor care about human beings?
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:4
        content: '  See  ;  ;  .    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Yet what honor you have given to men,created only a little lower than
        Elohim, [[COMMENT(0)]]crowned  with glory and magnificence.
      comments:
      - number: 8:5
        content: "  This is the same Hebrew word used for the Creator-God in  .     
          Or \u201Csurrounded.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: You have delegated to themrulership over all you have made,with everything
        under their authority,placing earth itself under the feet of your image-bearers.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:6
        content: "  The Septuagint translation of    is quoted in  . Today, all things
          are not yet under our feet. Even mosquitoes still come to defeat us. But
          there will be a time of restoration because of Christ\u2019s redemption,
          when everything will rest beneath our authority. See  ;  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "All the created order and every living thingof the earth, sky, and
        sea\u2014the wildest beasts and all that move in the paths of the sea [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014everything 
        is in submission to Adam\u2019s sons."
      comments:
      - number: "8:7\u20138"
        content: "  The \u201Cpaths of the sea\u201D speaks of God\u2019s way of
          deliverance (), for Jesus was the One who walked on the water (;  ).     
          Or \u201Csheep and oxen, beasts of the field, birds of the air, fish of
          the sea, and everything that moves in the paths of the sea.\u201D  "
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "All the created order and every living thingof the earth, sky, and
        sea\u2014the wildest beasts and all that move in the paths of the sea [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014everything 
        is in submission to Adam\u2019s sons."
      comments:
      - number: "8:7\u20138"
        content: "  The \u201Cpaths of the sea\u201D speaks of God\u2019s way of
          deliverance (), for Jesus was the One who walked on the water (;  ).     
          Or \u201Csheep and oxen, beasts of the field, birds of the air, fish of
          the sea, and everything that moves in the paths of the sea.\u201D  "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Yahweh, our Sovereign God,your glory streams from the heavens above,filling
        the earth with the majesty of your name!People everywhere see your splendor!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Triumphant ThanksDelighting in God'
      title: Triumphant ThanksDelighting in God
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneTo the tune of \u201CThe Secrets of the
        Son\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]A Psalm of DavidI will worship you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        with extended handsas my whole heart erupts with praise! [[COMMENT(1)]]I
        will tell everyone everywhere about your wonderful works!"
      comments:
      - number: 9
        content: "  As translated by Augustine, an early church father. The Hebrew
          is \u201Cto the death of the son.\u201D Because of David\u2019s sin with
          Bathsheba, the son born to them had to die, not as a judgment upon the
          child, but as a sacrifice to cleanse David of his sin. This was God\u2019s
          way of restoring David. A sinless son bore the guilt. This is a picture
          of Jesus!    "
      - number: 9:1
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cpraise\u201D is  , which can mean \u201Cto
          shoot [an arrow]\u201D or \u201Cto worship with extended hands.\u201D It
          implies an ecstatic burst of praise that is thrown into the heavens like
          a shout. It is the praise that breaks strongholds. A fresh determination
          arose in David\u2019s spirit to praise his way into victory.    "
    - name: '2: Deliverance'
      title: Deliverance
      number: 2
      content: I will be glad and shout in triumph.I will sing praise to your exalted
        name, O&nbsp;Most High.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For when you appear, I worshipyou while my enemies run in retreat.They
        stumble and perish before your presence.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Divine Judgment'
      title: Divine Judgment
      number: 4
      content: For you have stood up for my causeand vindicated me when I needed
        you the most.From your righteous throne you have given me justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: With a blast of your rebuke, nations are destroyed.You obliterated
        their names forever and ever.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The Lord thundered and our enemies have been cut off,vanished in
        everlasting ruins.All their cities have been destroyed\u2014even the memory
        of them has been erased."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, our mighty God, reigns forever!He
        sits enthroned as King ready to render his verdictsand judge all with righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He will issue his decrees of judgment,deciding what is right for the
        entire world,dispensing justice to all.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: All who are oppressed may come to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> as
        a highshelter in the time of trouble, a perfect hiding place.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For everyone who knows your wonderful namekeeps putting their trust
        in you.They can count on you for help no matter what.O&nbsp;Lord, you will
        never, no never, neglect thosewho come to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Listen, everyone! Sing out your praises to the Godwho rules in Zion!Tell
        the world about all the miracles he has done!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Daughter of Zion'
      title: Daughter of Zion
      number: 12
      content: He tracks down killers and avenges bloodshed,but he will never forget
        the ones forgotten by others,hearing every one of their cries for justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So now, O&nbsp;Lord, don\u2019t forget me.Have mercy on me.Take note
        of how I\u2019ve been humiliatedat the hands of those who hate me.You are
        the one who can snatch me away from the gates of death."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then I will sing your praises as I pass through the gatesof the Daughter
        of Zion, rejoicing in your deliverance!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: For the nations get trappedin the very snares they set for others.The
        hidden trap they set for the weakhas snapped shut upon themselves!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Destruction of the Wicked'
      title: Destruction of the Wicked
      number: 16
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is famous for his justice.While the
        wicked are digging a pit for others,they are actually setting the terms for
        their own judgment.They will fall into their own pit.Consider the truth of
        this  [[COMMENT(0)]]and pause in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 9:16
        content: "  The Hebrew word    means \u201Cto consider the truth of the matter.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Don\u2019t forget this: all the wicked will one dayfall into the
        darkness of death\u2019s domain, [[COMMENT(0)]]including the nations that
        forget God and reject his ways."
      comments:
      - number: 9:17
        content: "  This is the word  , the underworld, which is frequently translated
          \u201Chell.\u201D  "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He will not forget the needs of the poor.One day the needy will be
        remembered,and their hopes will not be forever dashed in disappointment.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, it\u2019s time to arise and judgethe
        nations who defy you.Don\u2019t let rebellious men triumph."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Make them tremble in fear before your presence.Place a lawgiver over
        them.Make them know that they are only puny, frail humanswho must give account
        to you!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1:   10It is likely thatPss. 9and10were originally one acrostic psalm.
        Eight Hebrew manuscripts unite them as well as the Aramaic, Septuagint, and
        the Latin Vulgate.The Cry of the OppressedThe Lord is Concealed'
      title: '  10It is likely thatPss. 9and10were originally one acrostic psalm.
        Eight Hebrew manuscripts unite them as well as the Aramaic, Septuagint, and
        the Latin Vulgate.The Cry of the OppressedThe Lord is Concealed'
      number: 1
      content: '[[COMMENT(0)]]Lord, why do you seem so far away when evil is near?Why
        have you hidden yourself when I need you the most? [[COMMENT(1)]]'
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">10</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">It is likely that</span>   
          <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">and</span>    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">were
          originally one acrostic psalm. Eight Hebrew manuscripts unite them as well
          as the Aramaic, Septuagint, and the Latin Vulgate.</span>    '
      - number: 10:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cwhen trouble is near.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The arrogant in their elitist pride persecute the poor and helpless.May
        you pour out upon themthe very evil they\u2019ve dreamed up against others!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "How they brag and boast of their cravings, exalting the greedy.They
        congratulate themselves as they despise you\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "these arrogant ones, so smug and secure!In their delusion the wicked
        boast, saying,\u201CGod doesn\u2019t care about what we do.There\u2019s nothing
        to worry about!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: So successful are they in their schemesand prosperous in all their
        plans!Your laws are far from them;they scoff at their enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They boast that neither God nor men will bring them down.They sneer
        at all their enemies, saying in their hearts,\u201CWe\u2019ll have success
        in all we doand never have to face trouble.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Their mouths spew out cursing, lies, and threats.Only trouble and
        turmoil come from all their plans.
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: Like beasts lurking in the shadows of the city,they crouch silently
        in ambush, waiting for the innocent to pass by.Pouncing on the poor, they
        catch them in their snareto murder their prey in secretas they plunder their
        helpless victims.
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: Like beasts lurking in the shadows of the city,they crouch silently
        in ambush, waiting for the innocent to pass by.Pouncing on the poor, they
        catch them in their snareto murder their prey in secretas they plunder their
        helpless victims.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: They crush the lowly as they fall beneath their brutal blows,watching
        their victims collapse in defeat!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Lord is Concerned'
      title: The Lord is Concerned
      number: 11
      content: "Then they say to themselves,\u201CThe Lofty One [[COMMENT(0)]] is
        not watching while we do this.He doesn\u2019t even care! We can get away
        with it!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 10:11
        content: "  This is the Hebrew name for God  , the \u201CLofty [Exalted]
          God.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now arise, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>-God! Crush them once and
        for all!Don\u2019t forget the helpless and oppressed."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "How dare the wicked think they\u2019ll reject God and escape judgment.They
        say to themselves,\u201CGod won\u2019t hold me accountable.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Lord, I know you see all that they\u2019re doing,noting their each
        and every deed.You know the trouble and turmoil they\u2019ve caused.Now punish
        them thoroughly for all that they\u2019ve done!The poor and helpless ones
        trust in you, Lord,for you are famous for being the helper of the fatherless.I
        know you won\u2019t let them down."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Break the power of the wicked and all their strong-arm tactics.Search
        them out and destroy themfor the evil things they\u2019ve done."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: You, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, are King forever and ever!All
        the nations will perish from your land.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, you have heard the desires of the humbleand
        seen their hopes. [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>!</smallcaps>You will hear their
        cries and encourage their hearts.
      comments:
      - number: 10:17
        content: '  The tenderhearted, compassionate God is able to hear our unspoken
          desires. What moves our hearts moves his heart. How kind is    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The orphans and the oppressed will be terrified no longer,for you
        will bring them justice, and no earth-dweller will trouble them again.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Song of the SteadfastThe Advice to Flee'
      title: Song of the SteadfastThe Advice to Flee
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One by King DavidMy faith shelters my soul
        continually in <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>.Why would you say to me:\u201CRun
        away while you can!Fly away like a bird to hide in the mountains for safety."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For your enemies have prepared a trap for you!Can\u2019t you see
        them hidingin their place of darkness and shadows?They\u2019re set against
        all those who live upright lives."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Answer of Faith'
      title: The Answer of Faith
      number: 3
      content: "What can the righteous accomplishwhen truth\u2019s pillars are destroyed
        and law and order collapse?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet  <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>  is never shaken  [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014he
        is still found in his temple of holiness,reigning as King <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        over all.He closely watches and examines everything man does.With a glance,
        his eyes  examine every heart,for his heavenly rule will prevail over all."
      comments:
      - number: 11:4
        content: "  This is an implied contrast made explicit from the text. This
          psalm shows the contrast between what can be shaken and what is unshakable.     
          The actual Hebrew is \u201Chis eyelids.\u201D Some see the \u201Ceyelid\u201D
          as the lid of the ark of the covenant, which was the mercy seat.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> tests both the righteous and the wicked.God\u2019s
        very soul detests lovers of violence."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He will [[COMMENT(0)]] rain down upon them judgment for their sins.A
        scorching wind will be their lot in life.
      comments:
      - number: 11:6
        content: "  Or \u201CMay he.\u201D  "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But remember this: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is the Righteous
        One who lovesjustice, and every godly onewill gaze upon his face!'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Song for the New DayIntercession'
      title: Song for the New DayIntercession
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA song of smiting, sung for the new day
        by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]Help, Lord! Save us! For godly ones are disappearing.Where
        are the dependable, principled ones?They\u2019re a vanishing breed!"
      comments:
      - number: 12
        content: "  The events surrounding this psalm could be the killing of the
          priests by Saul in  . Saul ordered the death of \u201Ceighty-five men who
          wore the linen ephod.\u201D The killing rampage continued until an entire
          community of priests had been slaughtered with their women and children.
          This great evil marked David from that day forward. The inscription found
          in the Septuagint is \u201CThe Eighth Psalm of David.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Everyone lies, everyone flatters, and everyone deceives.Nothing but
        empty talk, smooth talk, and double-talk.
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: Intervention'
      title: Intervention
      number: 3-4
      content: "You will destroy every proud liar who says, \u201CWe lie all we want.Our
        words are our weapons, and we won\u2019t be held accountable.Who can stop
        us?\u201DMay <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> cut off their twisted tonguesand
        seal their lying lips.May they all be silenced\u2014those who boast and brag
        with theirhigh-minded talk."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: Intervention'
      title: Intervention
      number: 3-4
      content: "You will destroy every proud liar who says, \u201CWe lie all we want.Our
        words are our weapons, and we won\u2019t be held accountable.Who can stop
        us?\u201DMay <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> cut off their twisted tonguesand
        seal their lying lips.May they all be silenced\u2014those who boast and brag
        with theirhigh-minded talk."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But the Lord says, \u201CNow I will arise!I will defend the poor,those
        who were plundered, the oppressed,and the needy who groan for help.I will
        spring into action to rescue and protect them!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Inspiration'
      title: Inspiration
      number: 6
      content: "For every word <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> speaks is sure and reliable.His
        truth is tested, found to be flawless, and ever faithful.It\u2019s as pure
        as silver refined seven times in a crucible of clay. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 12:6
        content: "  The clay furnace (\u201Ccrucible\u201D) is the heart of man.
          We are the earthen vessels inside which God has placed his flawless words.
          His words test us, they try us, and they refine us, seven times over, until
          they are purified and assimilated into our spirits. The fire of testing
          purifies us as vessels to carry the Word within our hearts.  "
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: Lord, you will keep us safe,out of the reach of the wicked.Even though
        they strut and prowl,tolerating and celebrating what is worthless and vile,you
        will still lift up those who are yours!
      comments: []
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: Lord, you will keep us safe,out of the reach of the wicked.Even though
        they strut and prowl,tolerating and celebrating what is worthless and vile,you
        will still lift up those who are yours!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prayer Turns Depression into Delight 13Some believe David composed
        this psalm shortly after being anointed to be the king of Israel. David knew
        greatness was his destiny, but he struggled with the persecution and challenges
        that came before his exaltation. In the wilderness David trusted and prayed
        his way out.Depression'
      title: Prayer Turns Depression into Delight 13Some believe David composed this
        psalm shortly after being anointed to be the king of Israel. David knew greatness
        was his destiny, but he struggled with the persecution and challenges that
        came before his exaltation. In the wilderness David trusted and prayed his
        way out.Depression
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]For the Pure and Shining OneA Psalm of DavidI\u2019m
        hurting, Lord\u2014will you forget me forever? [[COMMENT(1)]]How much longer,
        Lord?Will you look the other way when I\u2019m in need? "
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">13</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">Some believe David
          composed this psalm shortly after being anointed to be the king of Israel.
          David knew greatness was his destiny, but he struggled with the persecution
          and challenges that came before his exaltation. In the wilderness David
          trusted and prayed his way out.</span>    '
      - number: 13:1
        content: '  This is the psalm that describes the journey from self to God,
          from despair to delight, from feeling abandoned to feeling affirmed. It
          begins with pain and ends with praise. Moaning gives way to music. We each
          can take comfort in what David experienced.      David felt as though God
          was hiding his face from his cries. David was left alone to wrestle with
          his doubts, feeling as though his patience could hold on no longer. Have
          you ever been there?    '
    - name: '2: Intercession'
      title: Intercession
      number: 2
      content: "How much longer must I cling to this constant grief?I\u2019ve endured
        this shaking of my soul.So how much longer will my enemy have the upper hand?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Take a good look at me, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, my God, and
        answer me!Breathe your life into my spirit.Bring light to my eyes in this
        pitch-black darknessor I will sleep the sleep of death.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Don\u2019t let my enemy proclaim, \u201CI\u2019ve prevailed over
        him.\u201DFor all my adversaries will celebrate when I fall."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I have always trusted in your kindness, so answer me.I will spin in
        a circle of joywhen your salvation [[COMMENT(0)]] lifts me up.
      comments:
      - number: 13:5
        content: "  The term for \u201Csalvation\u201D is  , which is nearly identical
          to \u201CJesus, our Salvation.\u201D Our Savior plans blessings and hope
          for each of us as we trust in him.  "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I will sing my song of joy to you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,for
        in all of this you have strengthened my soul.My enemies say that I have no
        Savior,but I know that I have one in you!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Looks Down from Heaven 14With a few differences,Ps. 14andPs.
        53are nearly identical.Ps. 14is practical;Ps. 53is prophetic.Ps. 14deals
        with the past,Ps. 53with the future.No God'
      title: God Looks Down from Heaven 14With a few differences,Ps. 14andPs. 53are
        nearly identical.Ps. 14is practical;Ps. 53is prophetic.Ps. 14deals with the
        past,Ps. 53with the future.No God
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]For the Pure and Shining OneA Psalm of DavidOnly the
        withering soul [[COMMENT(1)]] would say to himself,\u201CThere is no God.\u201DAnyone
        who thinks like this is corrupt and callous,devoid of what is good."
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">14</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">With a few differences,</span>   
          <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">and</span>    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">are
          nearly identical.</span>    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">is
          practical;</span>    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">is prophetic.</span>   
          <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">deals with the past,</span>   
          <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">with the future.</span>    '
      - number: 14:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cfool.\u201D The word for \u201Cfool\u201D comes from
          a Hebrew word meaning \u201Cwithering.\u201D If we make no room for God,
          we have withered hearts, our moral sense of righteousness is put to sleep,
          and the noble aspirations of the heart shrivel up and die.  "
    - name: '2: None Who Are Good'
      title: None Who Are Good
      number: 2
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> looks down in love,looking over all
        of Adam\u2019s sons and daughters.He\u2019s looking to see if there is anyone
        who acts wisely,any who are searching for God and wanting to please him."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But everyone has wandered astray,walking stubbornly toward evil.Not
        one is good; he can\u2019t even find one."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Overwhelmed with Dread'
      title: Overwhelmed with Dread
      number: 4
      content: "They live in luxury while exploiting my people!Won\u2019t these workers
        of wickedness ever learn?They don\u2019t ever think of praying to God."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But look at them now, in panic, trembling with terror.For God is on
        the side of his godly lovers.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Overcome with Joy'
      title: Overcome with Joy
      number: 6
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is always the safest place for the poorwhen
        the workers of wickedness oppress them.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How I wish that Israel\u2019s rescuewould arise from the midst of
        Zion!When <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> restores his people,Jacob\u2019s
        joy will break forthand Israel will be glad!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Living in the Shining Place 15The first line in Hebrew reads \u201C,
        who may abide [as a guest] in your tent [tabernacle]?\u201D Perhaps David\u2019s
        prophetic musicians sang this song of instruction as they laid the ark to
        rest in David\u2019s tent. It is a song that reveals who will dwell in God\u2019s
        holy presence and who will live with him in heaven\u2019s glory. It actually
        is a description of Zion\u2019s perfect Man, Christ Jesus, and all those
        who are transformed into his image (Rom. 8:29).A Question PosedThe Answer
        Provided"
      title: "Living in the Shining Place 15The first line in Hebrew reads \u201C,
        who may abide [as a guest] in your tent [tabernacle]?\u201D Perhaps David\u2019s
        prophetic musicians sang this song of instruction as they laid the ark to
        rest in David\u2019s tent. It is a song that reveals who will dwell in God\u2019s
        holy presence and who will live with him in heaven\u2019s glory. It actually
        is a description of Zion\u2019s perfect Man, Christ Jesus, and all those
        who are transformed into his image (Rom. 8:29).A Question PosedThe Answer
        Provided"
      number: 1
      content: '[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>A poetic song by David<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        who dares to dwell with you?Who presumes the privilege of being close to
        you,living next to you in your shining place [[COMMENT(1)]] of glory?'
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">15</span>
        content: "  <span class=\"ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs\">The first line
          in Hebrew reads \u201C</span><span class=\"ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs\">,
          who may abide [as a guest] in your tent [tabernacle]?\u201D Perhaps David\u2019s
          prophetic musicians sang this song of instruction as they laid the ark
          to rest in David\u2019s tent. It is a song that reveals who will dwell
          in God\u2019s holy presence and who will live with him in heaven\u2019s
          glory. It actually is a description of Zion\u2019s perfect Man, Christ
          Jesus, and all those who are transformed into his image (</span><span class=\"ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs\">).</span>    "
      - number: 15:1
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Csanctuary\u201D is taken from a root
          word for \u201Cshining place.\u201D This psalm gives us David\u2019s equivalent
          to Jesus\u2019 Sermon on the Hillside. If we will dwell in the Holy Place,
          there must first be a holy place in our spirits where God dwells. God\u2019s
          guests must submit to the holiness that lives there. There is etiquette
          for God\u2019s house revealed in this psalm.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They are passionate and wholehearted,always sincere and always speaking
        the truth\u2014for their hearts are trustworthy."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They refuse to slander [[COMMENT(0)]] or insult others;they\u2019ll
        never listen to gossip or rumors,nor would they ever harm a friend with their
        words."
      comments:
      - number: 15:3
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cslander,\u201D  , means to spy on someone
          and look for evil to use against that person.  "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They will despise evil and evil workerswhile commending the faithful
        ones who follow after the truth.They make firm commitments and follow through,even
        at great cost.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: They never crush others with exploitationand they would never be bought
        with a bribeagainst the innocent.Those who do these things will never be
        shaken;they will stand firm forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Golden SecretMy Protection'
      title: The Golden SecretMy Protection
      number: 1
      content: A precious song, engraved in gold, [[COMMENT(0)]] by DavidKeep me
        safe, O&nbsp;mighty God.I run to you, my safe place.
      comments:
      - number: 16
        content: "  The Hebrew word used in the inscription is  . There are many
          variations of translation for this word. Here are the major ones: \u201Cgolden,\u201D
          \u201Cgraven,\u201D \u201Ca permanent writing,\u201D \u201Cprecious,\u201D
          \u201Chidden,\u201D \u201Ca spiritual secret,\u201D or \u201Cjewel.\u201D
          The Septuagint renders this \u201Ca sculptured writing of gold\u201D; other
          translations call it a \u201Cgolden poem.\u201D Perhaps the most accepted
          translation of    is \u201Cengraved in gold.\u201D This speaks of the divine
          nature engraved into our hearts by the Word. A new humanity is now stamped
          with God-life, engraved in his golden glory.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I said to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,\u201CYou are my Maker and
        my Master.Any good thing you find in me has come from you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CMy holy loversin the land are my glorious
        ones,who fulfill all my desires.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: My Portion'
      title: My Portion
      number: 4
      content: Yet there are those who yield to their weakness, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        they will have troubles unending.I never gather with such ones, nor give
        them honor in any way.
      comments:
      - number: 16:4
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.      As translated from the
          Septuagint.    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, you alone are my inheritance.You are
        my prize, my pleasure, and my portion.You hold my destiny and its timing
        in your hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: My Praise'
      title: My Praise
      number: 6
      content: "Your pleasant path [[COMMENT(0)]] leads me to pleasant places.I\u2019m
        overwhelmed by the privilegesthat come with following you!"
      comments:
      - number: 16:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cboundary lines.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The way you counsel me makes me praise you more,for your whispers
        in the night give me wisdom,showing me what to do next.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Because I set [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>, but that he thought the
        way God thought. David had made his heart and mind to be identical with the
        heart and mind of God. Always before himself, before anything, were the desires
        of God. It was the heart and mind of God that had first place in David\u2019s
        heart and thoughts.</smallcaps> you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, always
        close to me,my confidence will never be weakened, for I experience your wraparound
        presence every moment. "
      comments:
      - number: 16:8
        content: "  The Hebrew word    carries the sense of being equal or similar.
          David was not saying he was equal to        It is possible to translate
          this section as \u201CI have determined in my heart to be identical with
          the mind and heart of God, and I will not let my resolve be weakened.\u201D     
          Or \u201Cbecause he is at my right hand.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "My heart and soul explode with joy\u2014full of glory!Even my body
        will rest confident and secure."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For you will not abandon me to the realm of death,nor will you allow
        your Faithful One to experience corruption. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 16:10
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe pit.\u201D This is likely a metaphor for Sheol.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Because of you, I know the path of life,as I taste the fullness of
        joy in your presence.At your right side [[COMMENT(0)]] I experience divine
        pleasures forevermore!
      comments:
      - number: 16:11
        content: "  Jesus was pierced in his side with the spear of man\u2019s hatred.
          Eternal pleasures are found hidden in the wounds of Christ, where Jesus
          responded to the world\u2019s hatred with sacred blood and water flowing
          from his side. Forgiveness and grace splashed on the dirt. We are now seated
          with Christ at his right side.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Cry for JusticeHear Me!'
      title: A Cry for JusticeHear Me!
      number: 1
      content: "A priestly prayer [[COMMENT(0)]] of DavidListen to me, Lord.Hear
        the passionate prayer of this honest man.My cause is just and my need is
        real.I\u2019ve done what\u2019s right and my lips speak truth."
      comments:
      - number: 17
        content: '  This is the Hebrew word  , and it is found in the titles of five
          Psalms (;  ;  ;  ;  ).    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Examine and exonerate me.Vindicate me and show the world I\u2019m
        innocent."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For in a visitation of the nightyou inspected my heart and refined
        my soul in fireuntil nothing vile was found in me.I will not sin with my
        words.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Following your word has kept me from wrong.Your ways have molded my
        footsteps, keeping mefrom going down the paths of the violent.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: My steps follow in the tracks of your chariot wheels,always staying
        in their path,never straying from your way.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Hide Me!'
      title: Hide Me!
      number: 6
      content: You will answer me, God; I know you always will.Hear my words like
        you always do as you listen to my every prayer.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Magnify the marvels of your mercy to all who seek you. [[COMMENT(0)]]You
        are the loving Savior of all who turn asideto hide themselves in you.
      comments:
      - number: 17:7
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Protect me from harm;keep an eye on me as you would a child [[COMMENT(0)]]who
        is reflected in the twinkling of your eye.Yes, hide me within the shelter
        of your embrace,under your outstretched wings. '
      comments:
      - number: 17:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cdaughter.\u201D      This could also be a reference
          to the mercy seat, where sacred blood was sprinkled in the Holy of Holies.
          There the golden cherubim overshadowed all who entered the divine chamber
          ().    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Protect me there from all my foes.For there are many who surround
        my soulto completely destroy me.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They are pitiless, heartless\u2014hard as nails,swollen with pride
        and filled with arrogance!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: See how they close in on me,waiting for the chance to throw me to
        the ground. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 17:11
        content: '  This is also what the soldiers did to Jesus. They threw him to
          the ground and nailed him to the cross.    '
    - name: '12: Help Me!'
      title: Help Me!
      number: 12
      content: "They\u2019re like lions eager to tear me apart,like young and fearless
        lions lurking in secret,so ferocious and cruel\u2014ready to rip me to shreds."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Arise, God, and confront them!Challenge them with your might! [[COMMENT(0)]]Free
        me from their clutches and rescue me from their rage.
      comments:
      - number: 17:13
        content: "  The word used here is \u201Csword.\u201D An alternative translation
          would be \u201CRescue my soul from the wicked one, who is your sword.\u201D
          The wicked are sometimes God\u2019s tools to execute his judgments (; 
          ).    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Throw them down to the ground,those who live for only this life on
        earth.Thrust them out of their prosperityand into their portion in eternity,leaving
        their wealth and wickedness behind!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: As for me, because I am innocent, I will see [[COMMENT(0)]] your faceuntil
        I see you for who you really are.I will be satisfied in an awakening of your
        likeness in me!
      comments:
      - number: 17:15
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Csee,\u201D  , means \u201Cto see a
          vision.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1:   18This magnificent poem is so important to the Holy Spirit that
        it appears twice in the Bible. You will also find it in2&nbsp;Sam. 22.I Love
        You, Lord'
      title: '  18This magnificent poem is so important to the Holy Spirit that it
        appears twice in the Bible. You will also find it in2&nbsp;Sam. 22.I Love
        You, Lord'
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]A song [[COMMENT(1)]] to the Pure and Shining One by
        King David, his servant, composed when the Lord rescued David from all his
        many enemies, including from the brutality of Saul.  He said:I love you,
        <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, and I\u2019m bonded to you, [[COMMENT(2)]]my
        strength!"
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">18</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">This magnificent
          poem is so important to the Holy Spirit that it appears twice in the Bible.
          You will also find it in</span>  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">.</span>    '
      - number: 18
        content: "  There are fifty psalms that are described as \u201Ca song\u201D
          in the inscription, and each one is a power song of victory and breakthrough.     
          Or \u201Cthe paw of Saul.\u201D Saul was like a beast that chased David
          until his death.    "
      - number: 18:1
        content: "  David didn\u2019t employ the common Hebrew word for \u201Clove,\u201D 
          , but instead used the Hebrew word for \u201Cpity\u201D or \u201Cmercy.\u201D
          How could David have mercy for God? The word he used,  , is the word for
          a mother who loves and pities her child so much it manifests with a deep
          love and emotional bond. This concept, although difficult to convey in
          English, carries the thought of embrace and touch. It could actually be
          translated \u201CLord, I want to hug you.\u201D Haven\u2019t you ever felt
          like that?    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, you\u2019re the bedrock beneath my
        feet,my faith-fortress, my wonderful deliverer,my God, my rock of rescue
        where none can reach me.You\u2019re the shield around me,the mighty power
        [[COMMENT(0)]] that saves me,and my high place."
      comments:
      - number: 18:2
        content: "  Or \u201Chorn\u201D (i.e., horn of my salvation), which comes
          from a root word meaning \u201Cray of brightness.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "All I need to do is to call on you,<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        the praiseworthy God.When I do, I\u2019m safe and sound in you\u2014delivered
        from my foes!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "For when the cords of death wrapped around meand torrents of destruction
        overwhelmed me, [[COMMENT(0)]]taking me to death\u2019s door,"
      comments:
      - number: "18:4\u20135"
        content: "  Or \u201Cwaves of Sheol [death] engulfed me.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "For when the cords of death wrapped around meand torrents of destruction
        overwhelmed me, [[COMMENT(0)]]taking me to death\u2019s door,"
      comments:
      - number: "18:4\u20135"
        content: "  Or \u201Cwaves of Sheol [death] engulfed me.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: in my distress I cried out to you, the delivering God,and from your
        temple-throne you heard my troubled cry,and my sobs went right into your
        heart. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:6
        content: "  This scene is not only a poetic portrayal of how God answered
          David\u2019s prayer, but also a picture of the sufferings of a greater
          Son of David, Jesus, who hung on the cross with cries of agony. God heard
          him and shook the planet as thick clouds covered the sun.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The earth itself shivered and shook.It reeled and rocked before him.As
        the mountains trembled, they melted away,for his anger was kindled on my
        behalf!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Fierce flames leapt from his mouth, [[COMMENT(0)]]erupting with blazing,
        burning coals as smokeand fire encircled him.
      comments:
      - number: 18:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cnostrils.\u201D    "
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "He stretched heaven\u2019s curtain open and came to my defense.Swiftly
        he rode to earth as the stormy sky was lowered.He rode a chariot of thunderclouds
        amidst thick darkness;his steed was a cherub,soaring on outstretched wings
        of Spirit-Wind."
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "He stretched heaven\u2019s curtain open and came to my defense.Swiftly
        he rode to earth as the stormy sky was lowered.He rode a chariot of thunderclouds
        amidst thick darkness;his steed was a cherub,soaring on outstretched wings
        of Spirit-Wind."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Wrapped in the thick-cloud darkness,his thunder-tabernacle surrounded
        him.He hid himself in mystery-darkness;the dense rain clouds were his garments.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Suddenly the brilliance of his presence broke throughwith lightning
        bolts and hail\u2014a tempest dropping coals of fire."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The Lord thundered; the great God above every godspoke with his thunder-voice
        from the sky.The Most High uttered his voice!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He released his lightning-arrows, and routed my foes.See how they
        ran and scattered in fear!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then with his mighty roar he laid bare the foundations of the earth,uncovering
        the secret source of the sea.The hidden depths of land and sea were exposedby
        the blast of his hot breath.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He rescued me from the mighty watersand drew me to himself!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Even though I was helpless in the handsof my hateful, strong enemy,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]you were good to deliver me.
      comments:
      - number: 18:17
        content: '  Death is our strong enemy. Only through Christ are we delivered
          from its grip.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When I was at my weakest, [[COMMENT(0)]] my enemies attacked\u2014but
        the Lord held on to me."
      comments:
      - number: 18:18
        content: "  Or \u201CIn the day of my calamity.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "His love broke open the way,and he brought me into a beautiful, broad
        place. [[COMMENT(0)]]He rescued me\u2014because his delight is in me! "
      comments:
      - number: 18:19
        content: '  This could be the throne room of heaven.      Here in verses   
          you can see the glorious resurrection of Christ as the Father reached down
          and kissed the Son with life and love. Read it again and think of Christ
          in the tomb being raised by the Father.    '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He rewarded me for doing what\u2019s right and staying pure."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I will follow his commands andI\u2019ll not sin by ceasing to follow
        him, no matter what."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For I\u2019ve kept my eyes focused on his righteous words,and I\u2019ve
        obeyed everything that he\u2019s told me to do."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I\u2019ve been blameless before him and followed all his ways,keeping
        my heart pure."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And so <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> has rewarded me according to
        my righteousness,because I kept my heart clean before his eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Good people will taste your goodness.And to those who are loyal to
        you,you love to prove that you are loyal and true.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And for those who are purified, they find you always pure.But you\u2019ll
        outwit the crooked and cunning with your craftiness."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "To the humble you bring heaven\u2019s deliverance,but the proud and
        haughty you disregard."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: God, all at once you turned on a floodlight for me!You are the revelation-light
        in my darkness,and in your brightness I can see the path ahead.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: With you as my strength I can crush an enemy horde,advancing through
        every stronghold that stands in front of me. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:29
        content: "  Or \u201Cby my God I can jump over a wall.\u201D    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, what a perfect God you are!All <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s
        promises have proven true.What a secure shelter for all thosewho turn to
        hide themselves in you,the wraparound God. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:30
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here (often translated \u201Cshield\u201D)
          means \u201Cto wrap around in protection.\u201D God himself is our shield
          of grace.    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Could there be any other god like <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>?For
        there is not a more secure foundation [[COMMENT(0)]] than you.
      comments:
      - number: 18:31
        content: "  Or \u201Crocky cliff.\u201D    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: God, you have wrapped me in powerand made my way perfect.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Through you I ascend to the highest peaksto stand strong and secure
        in you. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:33
        content: "  Or \u201CYou make my legs like a deer to stand firm on the heights.\u201D    "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "You\u2019ve trained me with the weapons of warfare-worship;my arms
        can bend a bow of bronze."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: You empower me for victory with your wraparound presence.Your power
        within makes me strong to subdue.By stooping down in gentleness,you made
        me great!
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "You\u2019ve set me free, and now I\u2019m standing complete,ready
        to fight some more!"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "I caught up with my enemies and conquered themand didn\u2019t turn
        back until the war was won!"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "I smashed them to pieces andI finished them once and for all; they\u2019re
        as good as dead."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "You\u2019ve placed your armor upon meand made my enemies bow low
        at my feet."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "You\u2019ve made them all turn tail and run,for through you I\u2019ve
        destroyed them all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: They shouted for help, but no one dared to rescue them.They cried
        out to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, but he refused to answer them.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: So I pulverized them to powder and cast them to the wind.I swept them
        away like dirt on the floor.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "You gave me victory on every side,for you make me a leader of nations.Even
        those I\u2019ve never heard of come and bow at my feet."
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: As soon as they heard of me they submitted to me.Even the rebel foreigners
        obey my every word.
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: Their rebellion fades away as they come near;trembling in their strongholds,they
        come crawling out of their hideouts,cringing in fear before me.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> lives!Praise is lifted high to the unshakable
        God!Towering over all, my Savior-God is worthy to be praised!
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Look how he pays back harm to all who harm me,subduing all who come
        against me.
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: He rescues me from my enemies;he lifts me up high and keeps me out
        of reach,far from the grasp of my violent foe.
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: So I thank you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, with my praises!I will
        sing my song to the highest God,so all among the nations will hear me. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:49
        content: '  Paul quoted this verse as one of four prophecies to show that
          Christ came for all people, not just the Jews. See  .  '
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "You have given me, your king, great victories.You\u2019ve always
        been tender and kind to me, your anointed one,your loving servant, David,
        and to all my descendants!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s WitnessesGod\u2019s Story in the Skies"
      title: "God\u2019s WitnessesGod\u2019s Story in the Skies"
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA poem of praise by King David, his loving
        servantGod\u2019s splendor is a tale that is told,written in the stars. [[COMMENT(0)]]Space
        itself speaks his storythrough the marvels of the heavens.His truth is on
        tour in the starry vault of the sky,showing his skill in creation\u2019s
        craftsmanship."
      comments:
      - number: 19:1
        content: "  Or \u201CThe heavens are continually rehearsing the glory of
          God.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Each day gushes out its message [[COMMENT(0)]] to the next,night
        by night whispering its knowledge to all\u2014"
      comments:
      - number: 19:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cspeaks its prophecy.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: without a sound, without a word, without a voice being heard,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: yet all the world can hear its echo.Everywhere its message goes out.What
        a heavenly home God has set for the sun,shining in the superdome of the sky!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: See how he leaves his celestial chamber each morning,radiant as a
        bridegroom ready for his wedding,like a day-breaking champion eager to run
        his course.
      comments: []
    - name: "6: God\u2019s Story in the Scriptures"
      title: "God\u2019s Story in the Scriptures"
      number: 6
      content: He rises on one horizon, completing his circuit on the other,warming
        lives and lands with his heat.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s Word [[COMMENT(0)]] is perfect
        in every way;how it revives our souls!<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s
        laws lead us to truth,and his ways change the simple into wise."
      comments:
      - number: 19:7
        content: "  Or \u201CThe Torah.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s teachings are right and make
        us joyful;his precepts are so pure!<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s commands
        challenge us to keep close to his heart!The revelation-light of his Word
        makes my spirit shine radiant."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s decrees are trustworthy.The
        fear of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is pure, enduring forever."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The rarest treasures of life are found in his truth.That\u2019s why
        God\u2019s Word is prized like others prize the finest gold.Sweeter also
        than honey are his living words\u2014sweet words dripping from the honeycomb!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For they warn us, your servants,and keep us from following the wicked
        way,giving a lifetime guarantee:great success to every obedient soul!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: How would I discern the waywardness [[COMMENT(0)]] of my heart?Lord,
        forgive my hidden flaws whenever you find them.
      comments:
      - number: 19:12
        content: "  The word    is taken from the Hebrew word for \u201Cerrors.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Keep cleansing me, God,and keep me from my secret, selfish sins;may
        they never rule over me!For only then will I be free from faultand remain
        innocent of rebellion.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So may the words of my mouth, my meditation-thoughts,and every movement
        of my heart be always pure and pleasing,acceptable before your eyes, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,my
        only Redeemer, my Protector. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 19:14
        content: "  Or \u201Cmy rock [of protection].\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Victory DecreeMay God Hear You'
      title: A Victory DecreeMay God Hear You
      number: 1
      content: For the Pure and Shining OneFor the end times, by David [[COMMENT(0)]]In
        your day of danger may <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> answer and deliver you.May
        the name of the God of Jacob [[COMMENT(1)]] set you safely on high!
      comments:
      - number: 20
        content: "  The inscription for    is \u201CFor the end times,\u201D as translated
          from the Septuagint.    "
      - number: 20:1
        content: "  Jacob was one transformed by God\u2019s grace, changed from a
          schemer who took from others into Israel, God\u2019s prince.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "May supernatural help be sent from his sanctuary.May he support you
        from Zion\u2019s fortress!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: May he remember every gift you have given himand celebrate every sacrifice
        of love you have shown him. [[COMMENT(0)]]Pause in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 20:3
        content: "  Or \u201CMay he consider your burnt offerings generous.\u201D  "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: May <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> give you every desire of your heartand
        carry out your every plan as you go to battle.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: When you succeed, we will celebrate and shout for joy.Flags will fly
        when victory is yours!Yes, God will answer your prayers, and we will praise
        him!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I know <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> gives me all that I ask forand
        brings victory to his anointed king.My deliverance cry will be heard in his
        holy heaven.By his mighty hand miracles will manifestthrough his saving strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Some find their strength in their weapons and wisdom,but my miracle-deliverance
        can never be won by men.Our boast is in <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> our
        God,who makes us strong and gives us victory!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Our enemies will not prevail; they will only collapse andperish in
        defeat while we will rise up, full of courage.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Give victory to our king, O&nbsp; <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!The
        day we call on you, give us your answer!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Through Your StrengthLooking Back'
      title: Through Your StrengthLooking Back
      number: 1
      content: "For the end times, to the Pure and Shining OneDavid\u2019s poem of
        praise [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, because of your strength
        the king is strong.Look how he rejoices in you!He bursts out with a joyful
        song because of your victory!"
      comments:
      - number: 21
        content: '  Think of this song as a praise song to Jesus, our true King.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For you have given him his heart\u2019s desire,anything and everything
        he asks for.You haven\u2019t withheld a thing from the king.Pause in his
        presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Rich blessings overflow with every encounter with you,and you placed
        a royal crown of gold upon his head.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He wanted life [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014you have given it to him and more!The
        days of his blessing stretch on one after another, forever!"
      comments:
      - number: 21:4
        content: '  This can be viewed as a prophecy of our Lord Jesus asking for
          resurrection-life. Every verse of this psalm is prophetic, pointing us
          to Jesus.    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You have honored him and made him famous.Glory-garments are upon him,and
        you surround him with splendor and majesty.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Your victory heaps blessing after blessing upon him.What joy and bliss
        he tastes, rejoicing before your face! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 21:6
        content: "  Or \u201CYou make him joyful in joy with your face!\u201D  "
    - name: '7: Looking Forward'
      title: Looking Forward
      number: 7
      content: For the king trusts in <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,and he will never
        stumble, never fall.The forever-love of the Most High holds him firm.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Your almighty hands have captured your foes.You uncovered all who
        hate you and you seized them.
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "When you appear before them,unveiling the radiance of your face,they
        will be consumed by the fierce fire of your presence.<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s
        flames will swallow them up.They and their descendantswill be destroyed by
        an unrelenting fire."
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "When you appear before them,unveiling the radiance of your face,they
        will be consumed by the fierce fire of your presence.<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s
        flames will swallow them up.They and their descendantswill be destroyed by
        an unrelenting fire."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: We will watch them fail,for these are the ones who plan their evil
        schemes against the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Looking Up'
      title: Looking Up
      number: 12
      content: They will turn and run at the sight of your judgment-arrowsaimed straight
        at their hearts.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Rise up and put your might on display!By your strength we will sing
        and praise your glorious power!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Prophetic Portrait of the Cross 22Thirty-three prophecies from
        this psalm were fulfilled when Jesus was on the cross.The Cross'
      title: A Prophetic Portrait of the Cross 22Thirty-three prophecies from this
        psalm were fulfilled when Jesus was on the cross.The Cross
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]For the Pure and Shining OneDavid\u2019s song of anguishTo
        the tune of \u201CThe Deer at the Dawning of the Day\u201D [[COMMENT(1)]]God,
        my God!Why would you abandon me now? [[COMMENT(2)]]"
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">22</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">Thirty-three prophecies
          from this psalm were fulfilled when Jesus was on the cross.</span>    '
      - number: 22
        content: '  This could be an amazing picture of Christ giving birth at the
          cross to a generation of his seed. They are like children of God born in
          the dawning of that resurrection morning.    '
      - number: 22:1
        content: "  When Jesus quoted these words while dying on the cross, he was
          identifying himself as the one David wrote about in this psalm. It is a
          breathtaking portrayal of what Jesus endured through his suffering for
          us. The psalm ends with another quotation of Jesus on the cross: \u201CIt
          is finished!\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Why do you remain distant,refusing to answer [[COMMENT(0)]] my tearful
        cries in the dayand my desperate cries for your help in the night?I can\u2019t
        stop sobbing.Where are you, my God?"
      comments:
      - number: 22:2
        content: "  David used poetic nuance here, for the word \u201Canswer\u201D
          () is also a Hebrew homonym for \u201Caffliction.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Yet I know that you are most holy.You are God-Enthroned, the praise
        of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Our fathers\u2019 faith was in you\u2014through the generations they
        trusted in youand you came through."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Every time they cried out to you in their despair,you were faithful
        to deliver them;you didn\u2019t disappoint them."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But I am like a worm,crushed and bleeding crimson, [[COMMENT(0)]]treated
        as less than human.I\u2019ve been despised and scorned by everyone!"
      comments:
      - number: 22:6
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cworm\u201D is  , which is also the
          word for \u201Ccrimson\u201D or \u201Cscarlet.\u201D    was a certain worm
          in the ancient Near East that, when crushed, bled a crimson color so strong
          it was used as a dye for garments. Jesus was not saying he was a despised
          worm, but that he will bleed as he is crushed for our sins.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Mocked by their jeers, despised with their sneers,as all the people
        poke fun at me, spitting their insults,
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "saying, \u201CIs this the one who trusted in God?Now let\u2019s see
        if <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> will come to your rescue!Let\u2019s see
        how much he delights in him!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Lord, you delivered me safely from my mother\u2019s womb.You are
        the one who cared for me ever since I was a baby."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Since the day I was born, I\u2019ve been placed in your custody.You\u2019ve
        cradled me throughout my days,and you\u2019ve always been my God."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So don\u2019t leave me now, for trouble is all around me,and there\u2019s
        no one to help me."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I\u2019m surrounded by many violent foes like bulls;forces of evil
        encircle me like the strong bulls of Bashan. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:12
        content: "  The root word for \u201Cbull\u201D means \u201Cto break or destroy.\u201D
          The word  , although known as a fertile land northeast of Lake Galilee,
          is also a word for \u201Cserpent.\u201D These represent the many demonic
          spirits who came against the Son of God as he was being crucified.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Like ravenous, roaring lions tearing their prey,they pour curses from
        their mouths.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now I\u2019m completely exhausted. [[COMMENT(0)]]Every joint of my
        body has been pulled apart.My courage has melted away."
      comments:
      - number: 22:14
        content: "  Or \u201CI\u2019m poured out like water.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I\u2019m so thirsty and parched.My tongue sticks to the roof of my
        mouth.And now you lay me in the dust of death."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They have pierced my hands and my feet. [[COMMENT(0)]]Like a pack
        of wild dogs they tear at me,swirling around me with their hatred.A band
        of evil men surrounds me.
      comments:
      - number: 22:16
        content: "  As translated from some Hebrew manuscripts, Septuagint and Syriac;
          other Hebrew manuscripts read \u201CLike the lion my hands and my feet.\u201D
          This is a powerful prophecy of crucifixion, given by David many centuries
          before crucifixion was invented by the Romans.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I can count all my bones.Look at how they gloat over me and stare!
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: With a toss of the dice they divide my clothes among themselves,gambling
        for my garments!
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, please don\u2019t stay far away.My
        strength, come quickly to my rescue."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Give me back my life.Save me from this violent death.Save my precious
        one and only [[COMMENT(0)]]from the power of these dogs! '
      comments:
      - number: 22:20
        content: "  Or \u201Cunique\u201D or \u201Cdarling.\u201D Each of us is that
          \u201Cone and only\u201D child or \u201Cunique darling\u201D mentioned
          here in this psalm. See  . On the cross, Jesus\u2014like a deer giving
          birth at the dawning light (see inscription of  )\u2014cared less that
          his body was being torn apart and more about our protection and salvation.
          He prayed for us as he faced death on the cross.      The \u201Cdogs\u201D
          are metaphors for evil spirits who were bent on destroying Jesus on the
          cross. The Hebrew word for \u201Cdog\u201D is taken from a root word meaning
          \u201Cto attack.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: The Resurrection'
      title: The Resurrection
      number: 21
      content: Save me from all the power of the enemy,from this roaring lion raging
        against meand the power of his dark horde.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: I will declare your name before all my brothersand praise you in the
        midst of the congregation. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 22:22
        content: "  Between v.    and v.    the glorious resurrection of Jesus takes
          place. The music is elevated to a higher key as victory is sounded forth.
          \u201CMy people gather\u201D is a reference to the church that was birthed
          through his resurrection glory. (See also v.  .)    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Those who fear <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, praise him!Let all the
        seed of Jacob glorify him with your praises.Stand in awe of him, all you
        offspring of Israel!
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "For he has not despised my cries of deep despair.He\u2019s my first
        responder to my sufferings,and when I was in pain,he was there all the time
        and heard the cries of the afflicted."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "You\u2019re the reason for my praise; it comes from you and goes
        to you.I will keep my promise to praise you before all who fear youamong
        the congregation of your people."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Let all the poor and broken eat until satisfied.Bring <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        praise and you will find him.May your hearts overflow with life forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: From the four corners of the earth,the peoples of the world will remember
        and return to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>.Every nation will come and worship
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: For <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is King of all, who takes charge
        of all the nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The wealthy of this world will feast in fellowship with himright alongside
        the humble of heart,bowing down to the dust, forsaking their own souls.They
        will all come and worship this worthy King!
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: His spiritual seed [[COMMENT(0)]] shall serve him.Future generations
        will hear from usabout the wonders of the Victorious Lord.
      comments:
      - number: 22:30
        content: '  Jesus, our crucified Savior, had no natural offspring. These
          are the sons and daughters who were birthed by the work of the cross.    '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "His generation yet to be born will glorify him.And they will all
        declare, \u201CIt is finished!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:31
        content: "  Or \u201CHe has done it!\u201D See  .  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Good Shepherd'
      title: The Good Shepherd
      number: 1
      content: "David\u2019s poetic praise to God<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is
        my best friend and my shepherd. [[COMMENT(0)]]I always have more than enough. "
      comments:
      - number: 23:1
        content: "  The word most commonly used for \u201Cshepherd\u201D is taken
          from the root word  , which is also the Hebrew word for \u201Cbest friend.\u201D
          This translation includes both meanings. The unique term for shepherd is 
          \u2014\u201Clover of the flock.\u201D This teaches us that a shepherd was
          not just a responsible overseer, but a caring father figure, tending to
          his flock out of a deep sense of love. Shepherds were also fierce protectors
          of their flocks. Jesus is the Fierce Protector of his people.      Or \u201CI
          lack nothing.\u201D What a wonderful declaration over your life! To never
          be in lack, always possessing more than enough. Our God meets our emotional,
          physical, and spiritual needs.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He offers a resting place for me in his luxurious love. [[COMMENT(0)]]His
        tracks take me to an oasis of peace near the quiet brook of bliss. '
      comments:
      - number: 23:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cin spring [green] meadows.\u201D A good shepherd knows
          where to pasture his flock. These green meadows would be a resting place,
          free from all fear. The Greek verb \u201Cto love\u201D is  , which is a
          merging of two words and two concepts.    means \u201Cto lead like a shepherd,\u201D
          and    is a verb that means \u201Cto rest.\u201D Love is our Shepherd leading
          us to the place of true rest in his heart.      The Hebrew word    means
          \u201Cthe waters of a resting place.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "That\u2019s where he restores and revives my life. [[COMMENT(0)]]He
        opens before me the right pathand leads me along in his footsteps of righteousness
        so that I can bring honor to his name."
      comments:
      - number: 23:3
        content: "  Or \u201Che causes my life [or \u201Csoul,\u201D Hb.  ] to return.\u201D
          So often life drains out of us through our many activities, but, as David
          found, God restores our well-being when we pursue what pleases God and
          when we rest in him.      Or \u201Ccircular paths of righteousness.\u201D
          It is a common trait for sheep on the hillsides of Israel to circle their
          way up higher. They eventually form a path that keeps leading them higher.
          This is what the psalm is referring to here. Each step we take following
          our Shepherd will lead us higher, even though it may seem we are going
          in circles.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Even when your path takes me throughthe valley of deepest darkness,fear
        will never conquer me, for you already have!Your authority is my strength
        and my peace. [[COMMENT(0)]]The comfort of your love takes away my fear.I\u2019ll
        never be lonely, for you are near."
      comments:
      - number: 23:4
        content: "  Or \u201CYour rod and your staff, they comfort me.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You become my delicious feasteven when my enemies dare to fight.You
        anoint me with the fragrance of your Holy Spirit; [[COMMENT(0)]]you give
        me all I can drink of you until my cup overflows. '
      comments:
      - number: 23:5
        content: "  Or \u201CYou anoint my head with oil.\u201D \u201COil\u201D or
          \u201Cfragrance\u201D becomes a symbol of the Holy Spirit.      Or \u201Cyour
          cup cheers me like the best wine (LXX),\u201D or \u201Cmy chalice that
          inebriates me, how goodly it is (Vulgate).\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So why would I fear the future?Only goodness and tender love pursue
        me all the days of my life.Then afterward, when my life is through,I\u2019ll
        return to your glorious presence [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>\u2019s palace.\u201D</smallcaps>
        to be forever with you!"
      comments:
      - number: 23:6
        content: "  Or \u201Creturn to    "
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The King of GloryCreation\u2019s King"
      title: "The King of GloryCreation\u2019s King"
      number: 1
      content: "David\u2019s poetic praise to God [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        claims the world as his.Everything and everyone belong to him!"
      comments:
      - number: 24
        content: "  The Septuagint adds \u201Cfor the Sabbath.\u201D    celebrates
          God as the Warrior-King, ruling over a kingdom of purity and holiness.   
          form a trilogy.    speaks of the Savior\u2019s cross,    speaks of the
          Shepherd\u2019s staff, and    speaks of the Sovereign King. We see three
          viewpoints of Jesus\u2019 love for us:  \u2014the Good Shepherd (),  \u2014the
          Great Shepherd (), and  \u2014the Chief Shepherd ().    "
    - name: '2: Who Comes before the King?'
      title: Who Comes before the King?
      number: 2
      content: "He\u2019s the one who pushed back oceans [[COMMENT(0)]]to let the
        dry ground appear,planting firm foundations for the earth."
      comments:
      - number: 24:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cwho established it upon the ocean currents.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Who, then, is allowed to ascend the mountain of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>?And
        who has the privilege of entering into God\u2019s Holy Place?"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Those who are clean\u2014whose works and ways are pure,whose hearts
        are true and sealed by the truth,those who never deceive, whose words are
        sure."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They will receive <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s blessingand
        righteousness given by the Savior-God."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The King is Coming!'
      title: The King is Coming!
      number: 6
      content: "They will stand before God,for they seek the pleasure of God\u2019s
        face, [[COMMENT(0)]] the God of Jacob.Pause in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 24:6
        content: "  The Hebrew is plural (\u201Cfaces\u201D).    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: So wake up, you living gateways!Lift up your heads, you doorways of
        eternity! [[COMMENT(0)]]Welcome the King of Glory,for he is about to come
        through you.
      comments:
      - number: 24:7
        content: "  God\u2019s people are identified as living gates and doorways.
          When God opens the doors of eternity within us, no one is able to shut
          them. To \u201Clift up\u201D our heads is a figure of speech for a bold
          confidence that brings rejoicing and hope.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You ask, \u201CWho is this King of Glory?\u201D<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        armed and ready for battle,<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, invincible in every
        way!"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So wake up, you living gateways, and rejoice!Fling wide, you eternal
        doors!Here he comes; the King of Glory is ready to come in.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You ask, \u201CWho is this King of Glory?\u201DHe is <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        armed and ready for battle,the Mighty One, the invincible commander of heaven\u2019s
        hosts! [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>  </smallcaps>Yes,
        he is the King of Glory!Pause in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 24:10
        content: "  Or \u201CTseva\u2019ot.\u201D The word    is the plural of the
          word  , a feminine noun meaning \u201Cforce.\u201D When these two Hebrew
          nouns are placed together, they would be translated as \u201Cof the forces.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: "1:   25Psalms 25\u201339are fifteen poetic songs about bringing pure
        worship before God.Pss. 25\u201329speak of our confidence to worship God.Pss.
        30\u201334point us to receiving life eternal from our Hero-God. The last
        five,Pss. 35\u201339, bring us to the importance of personal purity and holiness
        before God as we worship him in truth.Don\u2019t Fail Me, God!"
      title: "  25Psalms 25\u201339are fifteen poetic songs about bringing pure worship
        before God.Pss. 25\u201329speak of our confidence to worship God.Pss. 30\u201334point
        us to receiving life eternal from our Hero-God. The last five,Pss. 35\u201339,
        bring us to the importance of personal purity and holiness before God as
        we worship him in truth.Don\u2019t Fail Me, God!"
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]King David\u2019s poetic praise to GodAlways I will
        lift up my soul into your presence, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>."
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">25</span>
        content: '    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">are fifteen poetic
          songs about bringing pure worship before God.</span>    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">speak
          of our confidence to worship God.</span>    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">point
          us to receiving life eternal from our Hero-God. The last five,</span> 
          <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">, bring us to the importance
          of personal purity and holiness before God as we worship him in truth.</span>    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Be there for me, my God, for I keep trusting in you.Don\u2019t allow
        my foes to gloat over me orthe shame of defeat to overtake me."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Could anyone be disgracedwhen he has entwined his heart with yours?But
        my foes will all be defeated and ashamedwhen they harm the innocent.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Direct me, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, throughout my journeyso
        I can experience your plans for my life.Reveal the life-paths that are pleasing
        to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Escort me into your truth; take me by the hand and teach me. [[COMMENT(0)]]For
        you are the God of my salvation;I have wrapped my heart into yours all day
        long! '
      comments:
      - number: 25:5
        content: "  Or \u201CReveal your truth to me as I move forward.\u201D     
          The Hebrew word most commonly translated as \u201Cwait\u201D (wait upon
          the Lord) is  , which also means \u201Cto tie together by twisting\u201D
          or \u201Cto entwine\u201D or \u201Cto wrap tightly.\u201D This is a beautiful
          concept of waiting upon God, not passively, but entwining our hearts with
          him and his purposes.    "
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "Forgive my failures as a young man,and overlook the sins of my immaturity.Give
        me grace, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>! Always look at methrough your eyes
        of love\u2014your forgiving eyes of mercy and compassion.When you think of
        me, see me as one you love and care for."
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "Forgive my failures as a young man,and overlook the sins of my immaturity.Give
        me grace, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>! Always look at methrough your eyes
        of love\u2014your forgiving eyes of mercy and compassion.When you think of
        me, see me as one you love and care for."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "How good you are to me!When people turn to you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,they
        discover how easy you are to please\u2014so faithful and true!Joyfully you
        teach them the proper path,even when they go astray."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Keep showing the humble your path,and lead them into the best decision.Bring
        revelation-light that trains them in the truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Loving are all the ways of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, loving and
        faithful for those who keep his covenant.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the honor of your name, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,never count
        my many sins, and forgive them all\u2014lift their burden off of my life!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 25:11
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here for \u201Cforgive\u201D or \u201Cpardon\u201D
          is a rare word used only twice in the Old Testament and comes from a root
          word meaning \u201Cto lift off a burden.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Who are they that live in the holy fear of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>?You
        will show them the right path to take.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Then prosperity and favor will be their portion,and their descendants
        will inherit the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "There\u2019s a private place reserved for the devoted lovers of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,where
        they sit near him and receivethe revelation-secrets of his promises. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 25:14
        content: "  Or \u201Ccovenant.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Rescue me, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, for you free my feet from
        every trap.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Sorrows fill my heart as I feel helpless, mistreated\u2014I\u2019m
        all alone and in misery!Come closer to me now, for I need your mercy."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Turn to me, for my problems seem to be going from bad to worse.Only
        you can free me from all these troubles!
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Until you lift this burden, the burden of all my sins,my troubles
        and trials will be more than I can handle.Can\u2019t you feel my pain?"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Vicious, violent [[COMMENT(0)]] enemies hate me.There are so many,
        Lord. Can\u2019t you see?"
      comments:
      - number: 25:19
        content: '  This is the Hebrew word  .    '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Will you protect me from their power against me? I have taken shelter
        in you.Let it never be said that when I trusted you,you didn\u2019t come
        to my rescue."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Your perfection and faithfulness are my bodyguards,for you are my
        hope and I trust in you as my only protection.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Zealously, God, we ask youto come save Israel from all her troubles,for
        you provide the ransom price for your people! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 25:22
        content: '    is an acrostic psalm; that is, in the Hebrew text every verse
          begins with a progressive letter of the alphabet. It is considered a poetic
          device of Hebrew literature. Go back through the psalm and notice how many
          verses begin with the next letter of our English alphabet. See if you can
          find them.  '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Declare Me InnocentDavid\u2019s Trust and Transparency"
      title: "Declare Me InnocentDavid\u2019s Trust and Transparency"
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic praise to God<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        be my judge and declare me innocent!Clear my name, for I walk in integrityand
        trust you without wavering."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, you can scrutinize me.Refine my heart
        and probe my every thought.Put me to the test and you\u2019ll find me true."
      comments: []
    - name: "3: David\u2019s Truthfulness"
      title: "David\u2019s Truthfulness"
      number: 3
      content: I will never lose sight of your steadfast love for me.Your faithfulness
        has steadied my steps.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I won\u2019t keep company with tricky, two-faced men,nor will I go
        the way of those with hidden motives."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I despise the sinner\u2019s hangouts.You won\u2019t find me walking
        with the wicked."
      comments: []
    - name: "6-7: David\u2019s Testimony"
      title: "David\u2019s Testimony"
      number: 6-7
      content: "When I come to your altar, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,I\u2019ll
        be clean before you, [[COMMENT(0)]]approaching with songs of thanksgiving,singing
        songs of your mighty miracles."
      comments:
      - number: "26:6\u20137"
        content: "  Or \u201CI wash my hands in innocence.\u201D  "
    - name: "6-7: David\u2019s Testimony"
      title: "David\u2019s Testimony"
      number: 6-7
      content: "When I come to your altar, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,I\u2019ll
