        songs of your mighty miracles."
      comments:
      - number: "26:6\u20137"
        content: "  Or \u201CI wash my hands in innocence.\u201D  "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, I love to live in your house, this
        dwelling place of dazzling glory!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Don\u2019t treat me as one of these scheming sinnerswho plot violence
        against the innocent."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Look how they devise their wicked plans;their hands are always ready
        to receive a bribe.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I\u2019m not like them, Lord\u2014not at all.Save me, redeem me with
        your mercy,for I have chosen to walk only in what is right."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Among the worshipers I will praise <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,for
        I am safe and secure because of you!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Fearless Faith'
      title: Fearless Faith
      number: 1
      content: "David\u2019s poetic praise to God before he was anointed king [[COMMENT(0)]]Yahweh
        is my revelation-light [[COMMENT(1)]]and the source of my salvation.I fear
        no one!I\u2019ll never turn back and run, for you, Yahweh,surround and protect
        me."
      comments:
      - number: 27
        content: '  Inscription from the Septuagint. Most Bible scholars agree this
          psalm was written during the time of a devastating war where David witnessed
          the cruelty, savagery, and horrors of war.    '
      - number: 27:1
        content: '  See  ,  ;  .    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: When evil ones come to destroy me,they will be the ones who turn back.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: My heart will not fear even if an army rises to attack.I will not
        be shaken, even if war is imminent.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Here\u2019s the one thing I crave from Yahweh,the one thing I seek
        above all else:I want to live with him every moment in his house, [[COMMENT(0)]]beholding
        the marvelous beauty  of Yahweh,filled with awe, delighting in his glory
        and grace.I want to contemplate  in his temple."
      comments:
      - number: 27:4
        content: "  A temple had not yet been built when David wrote this psalm.
          He was saying that he longs to be surrounded with God\u2019s presence,
          enclosed and encircled with holiness.      The meaning of the Hebrew word
          for \u201Cbeauty\u201D () is not easily conveyed by one English word. It
          can also be translated \u201Csweetness,\u201D \u201Cpleasantness,\u201D
          \u201Cfriendliness,\u201D \u201Cgraciousness,\u201D \u201Cgoodness,\u201D
          \u201Cloveliness,\u201D \u201Csplendor,\u201D or \u201Cdelightfulness.\u201D
          Take each of these terms and read the verse again, inserting the possible
          alternatives. We must be captured by the awesomeness of God each time we
          come before him and rejoice in his friendship.      The Hebrew verb   
          can also mean \u201Cinquire,\u201D \u201Cmeditate,\u201D \u201Ctake pleasure
          in,\u201D and, in a general sense, \u201Cworship,\u201D \u201Cpray,\u201D
          or \u201Cseek [guidance].\u201D However,    comes from a root word that
          means \u201Cto arise at dawn.\u201D Perhaps David was saying that he would
          arise every dawn to take pleasure in God.    "
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: "In the day of trouble, he will treasure [[COMMENT(0)]] me in his
        shelter,under the cover of his tent.He will lift me high upon a rock,out
        of reach from all my enemies who surround me.Triumphant now, I\u2019ll bring
        him my offerings of praise,singing and shouting with ecstatic joy!Yes, I
        will sing praises to Yahweh!"
      comments:
      - number: "27:5\u20136"
        content: "  Or \u201Chide,\u201D \u201Csave,\u201D \u201Cstore,\u201D \u201Cesteem.\u201D    "
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: "In the day of trouble, he will treasure [[COMMENT(0)]] me in his
        shelter,under the cover of his tent.He will lift me high upon a rock,out
        of reach from all my enemies who surround me.Triumphant now, I\u2019ll bring
        him my offerings of praise,singing and shouting with ecstatic joy!Yes, I
        will sing praises to Yahweh!"
      comments:
      - number: "27:5\u20136"
        content: "  Or \u201Chide,\u201D \u201Csave,\u201D \u201Cstore,\u201D \u201Cesteem.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Hear my cry. Show me mercy, and send the help I need!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I heard your voice in my heart say, \u201CCome, seek my face;\u201Dmy
        inner being responded,\u201CYahweh, I\u2019m seeking your face with all my
        heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So don\u2019t turn your face away from me. [[COMMENT(0)]]You\u2019re
        the God of my salvation;how can you reject your servant in anger?You\u2019ve
        been my only hope,so don\u2019t forsake me now when I need you!"
      comments:
      - number: 27:9
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201CDon\u2019t overlook me.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: My father and mother abandoned me.But you, Yahweh, took me in and
        made me yours. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 27:10
        content: '  Every child needs four things: acceptance, focused attention,
          guidance, and protection. All four of these emotional needs are met by
          God (vv.  ). See  ;  .    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Now teach me, Yahweh, all about your ways and tell me what to do.Make
        it clear for me to understand,for I am surrounded by waiting enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Don\u2019t let them defeat me, Lord.You can\u2019t let me fall into
        their clutches!They keep accusing me of things I\u2019ve never done,breathing
        out violence against me."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Yet I believe with all my heartthat I will see again your goodness,
        Yahweh, in the land of life eternal!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Here\u2019s what I\u2019ve learned through it all:Don\u2019t give
        up; don\u2019t be impatient;be entwined as one with the Lord. [[COMMENT(0)]]Be
        brave and courageous, and never lose hope.Yes, keep on waiting\u2014for he
        will never disappoint you!"
      comments:
      - number: 27:14
        content: "  Or \u201Cwait upon the Lord.\u201D See footnote on  .  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: My Strength and ShieldMy Defender'
      title: My Strength and ShieldMy Defender
      number: 1
      content: "David\u2019s poetic praise to GodI\u2019m pleading with you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        help me! [[COMMENT(0)]]Don\u2019t close your ears to my cry, for you\u2019re
        my defender. If you continue to remain aloof and refuse to answer me,I might
        as well give up and die."
      comments:
      - number: 28:1
        content: "  This psalm was likely written when David was exiled because of
          the rebellion of his son Absalom. He was not longing and looking for his
          throne but for God\u2019s throne (see v.  ).      Or \u201Cmy rocky summit.\u201D  "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Hear my cry for help as I turn toward your mercy seat,as I lift my
        hands toward your sacred sanctuary.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: My Vindication'
      title: My Vindication
      number: 3
      content: "Don\u2019t allow me to be punished along with the wicked\u2014these
        hypocrites who speak sweetly to their neighbors\u2019 faceswhile holding
        evil against them in their hearts."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Go ahead and punish them as they deserve.Let them be paid back for
        all their evil plansin proportion to their wickedness.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Since they don\u2019t care anything about you,or understand the great
        things you\u2019ve done,take them down like an old building being demolished,never
        again to be rebuilt."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: My Strength'
      title: My Strength
      number: 6
      content: But <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, may your name be blessed and built
        up!For you have answered my passionate cry for mercy.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is my strength and my wraparound shield.When
        I fully trust in you, help is on the way.I jump for joy and burst forth with
        ecstatic, passionate praise!I will sing songs of what you mean to me!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You will be the inner strength of all your people,<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        the mighty protector of all,and the saving strength for all your anointed
        ones.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Save your people whom you love, and bless your chosen ones.Be our
        shepherd leading us forward,forever carrying us in your arms!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Glory-God Thunders'
      title: The Glory-God Thunders
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic praise to God for the last daysThe Feast
        of Tabernacles [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps>Proclaim his majesty,
        all you mighty sons of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, [[COMMENT(1)]]<smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps>giving all the glory and strength back to him!"
      comments:
      - number: 29
        content: "  The additional words of the inscription are found in the Septuagint.   
          is one of the loveliest poems ever written. It is pure and unrestrained
          praise. The name  is found eighteen times in eleven verses. David was a
          prophetic seer, and this psalm can properly be interpreted to speak of
          God\u2019s majesty revealed in the last days.    "
      - number: 29:1
        content: "    in Hebrew is  .    is from the root word  , which is the word
          for \u201CGod,\u201D \u201Cgods,\u201D \u201Cmighty warriors,\u201D \u201Cmighty
          men,\u201D \u201Cheroes,\u201D \u201Cangels,\u201D and \u201Cheavenly beings,\u201D
          and could be used to describe anyone who shows any strength or power.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Be in awe before his majesty.Be in awe before such power and might!Come
        worship wonderful <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, arrayed in all his splendor,bowing
        in worship as he appears in the beauty of holiness.Give him the honor due
        his name.Worship him wearing the glory-garmentsof your holy, priestly calling!
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "The voice of the Lord echoes through the skies and seas.The Glory-God
        reigns as he thunders in the clouds.So powerful is his voice, so brilliant
        and bright\u2014how majestic as he thunders over the great waters! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "29:3\u20134"
        content: "  The sea (\u201Cgreat waters\u201D) is a term often used in the
          Bible to symbolize the sea of humanity. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "The voice of the Lord echoes through the skies and seas.The Glory-God
        reigns as he thunders in the clouds.So powerful is his voice, so brilliant
        and bright\u2014how majestic as he thunders over the great waters! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "29:3\u20134"
        content: "  The sea (\u201Cgreat waters\u201D) is a term often used in the
          Bible to symbolize the sea of humanity. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: His tympanic thunder topples the strongest of trees. [[COMMENT(0)]]His
        symphonic sound splinters the mighty forests.
      comments:
      - number: 29:5
        content: '  Trees in the Bible are symbols used for men. The strongest of
          men are toppled and bowed down when the Glory-God speaks.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now he moves Zion\u2019s [[COMMENT(0)]] mountains by the might of
        his voice,shaking the snowy peaks with his earsplitting sound!"
      comments:
      - number: 29:6
        content: "  Or \u201CSirion\u201D (Mount Hermon), an ancient term for Mount
          Zion. See  .    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The lightning-fire flashes, striking as he speaks.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: God reveals himself when he makes the fault lines quake,shaking deserts,
        speaking his voice.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "God\u2019s mighty voice makes the deer to give birth. [[COMMENT(0)]]His
        thunderbolt-voice lays the forest bare.In his temple all fall before him
        with each one shouting,\u201CGlory, glory, the God of glory!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 29:9
        content: "  Or \u201CGod\u2019s mighty voice makes the oaks to whirl.\u201D     
          The Septuagint reads \u201CThose who give him glory he carries to his house.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Above the furious flood, [[COMMENT(0)]] the Enthroned One reigns,the
        King-God rules with eternity at his side.
      comments:
      - number: 29:10
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cflood\u201D is found thirteen times
          in the Bible and is always used in connection to man\u2019s rebellion and
          turning away from God. Thirteen is the biblical number signifying apostasy.
          Sitting as King, he rules even over the dark flood of evil to make it end.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: This is the one who gives his strength and might to his people.This
        is the Lord giving us his kiss of peace. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 29:11
        content: "  In Jewish synagogues this psalm is read on the first day of the
          Feast of Pentecost. The Christian church was born on Pentecost two thousand
          years ago when the mighty \u201Cstorm\u201D of the Spirit came into the
          upper room. See  . The last word of this psalm is \u201Cpeace.\u201D It
          begins with a storm, but God brings his people peace even in the midst
          of storms.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: He Healed Me'
      title: He Healed Me
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic praise to GodA song for the Feast of Dedication
        of the dwelling placeLord, I will exalt you and lift you high,for you have
        lifted me up on high!Over all my boasting, gloating enemies,you made me to
        triumph."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: O&nbsp;Lord, my healing God,I cried out for a miracle and you healed
        me!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You brought me back from the brink of death,from the depths below.Now
        here I am, alive and well, fully restored!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: O&nbsp;sing and make melody, you steadfast lovers of God.Give thanks
        to him every time you reflect on his holiness!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I\u2019ve learned that his anger lasts for a moment,but his loving
        favor lasts a lifetime! [[COMMENT(0)]]We may weep through the night,but at
        daybreak it will turn into shouts of ecstatic joy."
      comments:
      - number: 30:5
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CThere is wrath in his anger but life
          in his will [promise].\u201D  "
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "I remember boasting, \u201CI\u2019ve got it made!Nothing can stop
        me now!I\u2019m God\u2019s favored one; he\u2019s made me steady as a mountain!\u201DBut
        then suddenly, you hid your face from me.I was panic-stricken and became
        depressed."
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "I remember boasting, \u201CI\u2019ve got it made!Nothing can stop
        me now!I\u2019m God\u2019s favored one; he\u2019s made me steady as a mountain!\u201DBut
        then suddenly, you hid your face from me.I was panic-stricken and became
        depressed."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Still I cried out to you, Lord God. I shouted out for mercy, saying,
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhat would you gain in my death,if I were to go down to the
        depths of darkness?Will a grave sing your song?How could death\u2019s dust
        declare your faithfulness?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So hear me now, Lord; show me your famous mercy.O&nbsp;God, be my
        Savior and rescue me!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then he broke through and transformed all my wailinginto a whirling
        dance of ecstatic praise!He has torn the veil and lifted from methe sad heaviness
        of mourning.He wrapped me in the glory-garments of gladness.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "How could I be silent when it\u2019s time to praise you?Now my heart
        sings out, bursting with joy\u2014a bliss inside that keeps me singing,\u201CI
        can never thank you enough!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: How Great Is Your Goodness'
      title: How Great Is Your Goodness
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA song of poetic praise by King DavidI
        trust you, Lord, to be my hiding place.Don\u2019t let me down.Don\u2019t
        let my enemies bring me to shame.Come and rescue me, for you are the only
        Godwho always does what is right."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Rescue me quickly when I cry out to you.At the sound of my prayer
        may your ear be turned to me.Be my strong shelter and hiding place on high.Pull
        me into victory and breakthrough.
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "For you are my high fortress, where I\u2019m kept safe.You are to
        me a stronghold of salvation.When you deliver me out of this peril,it will
        bring glory to your name.As you guide me forth I\u2019ll be kept safefrom
        the hidden snares of the enemy\u2014the secret traps that lie before me\u2014for
        you have become my rock of strength."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "For you are my high fortress, where I\u2019m kept safe.You are to
        me a stronghold of salvation.When you deliver me out of this peril,it will
        bring glory to your name.As you guide me forth I\u2019ll be kept safefrom
        the hidden snares of the enemy\u2014the secret traps that lie before me\u2014for
        you have become my rock of strength."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Into your hands I now entrust my spirit. [[COMMENT(0)]]O&nbsp;Lord,
        the God of faithfulness,you have rescued and redeemed me.
      comments:
      - number: 31:5
        content: '  This was quoted by Jesus as he was dying on the cross. See  .    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I despise these deceptive illusions,all this pretense and nonsense,for
        I worship only you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In mercy you have seen my troubles, and you have cared for me;even
        during this crisis in my soul I will be radiant with joy,filled with praise
        for your love and mercy.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have kept me from being conquered by my enemy;you broke open
        the way to bring me to freedom, [[COMMENT(0)]]into a beautiful, broad place. '
      comments:
      - number: 31:8
        content: '  This is a picture of the stone rolled away from the tomb of Jesus.     
          This could be the throne room where Jesus ascended after his death.    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "O&nbsp;Lord, help me again! Keep showing me such mercy.For I am in
        anguish, always in tears,and I\u2019m worn out with weeping.I\u2019m becoming
        old because of grief; my health is broken."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I\u2019m exhausted! My life is spent with sorrow,my years with sighing
        and sadness.Because of all these troubles, I have no more strength.My inner
        being [[COMMENT(0)]] is so weak and frail."
      comments:
      - number: 31:10
        content: "  The Hebrew text reads \u201CMy bones grow weak.\u201D Bones in
          the Bible are symbols of our inner being.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "My enemies say, \u201CYou are nothing!\u201DEven my friends and neighbors
        hold me in contempt!They dread seeing me,and they look the other way when
        I pass by."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: I am totally forgotten, buried away like a dead man,discarded like
        a broken dish thrown in the trash.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I overheard their whispered threats, the slander of my enemies.I\u2019m
        terrified as they plot and scheme to take my life."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I\u2019m desperate, Lord! I throw myself upon you,for you alone are
        my God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "My life, my every moment, my destiny\u2014it\u2019s all in your hands.So
        I know you can deliver mefrom those who persecute me relentlessly."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Smile [[COMMENT(0)]] on me, your servant.Let your undying love and
        glorious gracesave me from all this gloom.
      comments:
      - number: 31:16
        content: "  Or \u201CCause your face to shine.\u201D  "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "As I call upon you, let my shame and disgracebe replaced by your
        favor once again.But let shame and disgrace fall instead upon the wicked\u2014those
        going to their own doom,drifting down in silence to the dust of death."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: At last their lying lips will be muted in their graves.For they are
        arrogant, filled with contempt and conceitas they speak against the godly.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Lord, how wonderful you are!You have stored up so many good things
        for us,like a treasure chest heaped up and spilling over with blessings\u2014all
        for those who honor and worship you!Everybody knows what you can dofor those
        who turn and hide themselves in you."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So hide all your beloved onesin the sheltered, secret place before
        your face.Overshadow them with your glory-presence.Keep them from these accusations,
        the brutal insults of evil men.Tuck them safely away in the tabernacle where
        you dwell.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The name of the Lord is blessed and lifted high!For his marvelous
        miracle of mercy protected mewhen I was overwhelmed by my enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I spoke hastily when I said, \u201CThe Lord has deserted me.\u201DFor
        in truth, you did hear my prayer and came to rescue me."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Listen to me, all you godly ones: Love the Lord with passion!The
        Lord protects and preserves all those who are loyal to him.But he pays back
        in full all those who reject him in their pride.'
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So cheer up! Take courage, all you who love him.Wait for him to break
        through for you, all who trust in him!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Forgiven'
      title: Forgiven
      number: 1
      content: A poem of insight and instruction by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]What
        bliss belongs to the onewhose rebellion has been forgiven, [[COMMENT(1)]]those
        whose sins are covered by blood.
      comments:
      - number: 32
        content: "  David wrote this psalm after he seduced the wife of his most
          loyal soldier, then had him killed to try to keep her pregnancy a secret.
          This sin with Bathsheba brought great disgrace to David, yet he found complete
          forgiveness in God\u2019s mercy. The apostle Paul chose the first two verses
          of    to support the important doctrine of salvation by grace through faith.
          See  . This was Augustine\u2019s favorite psalm. He had it written on the
          wall near his bed before he died so he could meditate on it.    "
      - number: 32:1
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cforgiven\u201D means \u201Clifted off.\u201D
          Sin\u2019s guilt is a burden that must be lifted off our souls. The Septuagint
          reads \u201Cbecause they have not hidden their sins.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: What bliss belongs to thosewho have confessed their corruption [[COMMENT(0)]]
        to God!For he wipes their slates cleanand removes hypocrisy from their hearts.
      comments:
      - number: 32:2
        content: "  David used three Hebrew words to describe sin in these first
          two verses: \u201Crebellion,\u201D \u201Csins\u201D (failures, falling
          short), and \u201Ccorruption\u201D (crookedness, the twisting of right
          standards).  "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Before I confessed my sins, I kept it all inside;my dishonesty devastated
        my inner life,causing my life to be filled with frustration,irrepressible
        anguish, and misery.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The pain never let up, for your hand of convictionwas heavy on my
        heart.My strength was sapped, my inner life dried uplike a spiritual drought
        within my soul.Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I finally admitted to you all my sins,refusing to hide them
        any longer.I said, \u201CMy life-giving God,I will openly acknowledge my
        evil actions.\u201DAnd you forgave me!All at once the guilt of my sin washed
        awayand all my pain disappeared!Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "This is what I\u2019ve learned through it all:All believers should
        confess their sins to God;do it every time God has uncovered youin the time
        of exposing.For if you do this, when sudden storms of life overwhelm,you\u2019ll
        be kept safe."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Lord, you are my secret hiding place,protecting me from these troubles,surrounding
        me with songs of gladness!Your joyous shouts of rescue release my breakthrough.Pause
        in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: "I hear the Lord saying, \u201CI will stay close to you,instructing
        and guiding you along the pathway for your life.I will advise you along the
        wayand lead you forth with my eyes as your guide.So don\u2019t make it difficult;
        don\u2019t be stubbornwhen I take you where you\u2019ve not been before.Don\u2019t
        make me tug you and pull you along.Just come with me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: "I hear the Lord saying, \u201CI will stay close to you,instructing
        and guiding you along the pathway for your life.I will advise you along the
        wayand lead you forth with my eyes as your guide.So don\u2019t make it difficult;
        don\u2019t be stubbornwhen I take you where you\u2019ve not been before.Don\u2019t
        make me tug you and pull you along.Just come with me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So my conclusion is this:Many are the sorrows and frustrationsof
        those who don\u2019t come clean with God.But when you trust in the Lord for
        forgiveness,his wraparound love will surround you."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So celebrate the goodness of God!He shows this kindness to everyone
        who is his.Go ahead\u2014shout for joy,all you upright ones who want to please
        him!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Song of Praise'
      title: A Song of Praise
      number: 1
      content: "Poetic praise by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]It\u2019s time to sing
        and shout for joy!Go ahead, all you redeemed ones, do it!Praise him with
        all you have,for praise looks lovely on the lips of God\u2019s devoted lovers."
      comments:
      - number: 33
        content: '  Most manuscripts have no inscription for this psalm. However,
          ancient Qumran evidence suggests this is the original inscription that
          was later omitted.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Play the guitar as you lift your praises loaded with thanksgiving.Sing
        and make joyous music with all you\u2019ve got inside."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Compose new melodies [[COMMENT(0)]] that release new praises to the
        Lord.Play his praises on instrumentswith the anointing and skill he gives
        you.Sing and shout with passion; make a spectacular sound of joy\u2014"
      comments:
      - number: 33:3
        content: '  There are seven new songs mentioned in the Bible. Six are in
          the Psalms (;  ;  ;  ;  ;  ) and one is in Isaiah ().  '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For God\u2019s Word is something to sing about!He is true to his
        promises, his word can be trusted,and everything he does is reliable and
        right."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Lord loves seeing justice on the earth.Anywhere and everywhere
        you can find his faithful, unfailing love!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: All he had to do was speak by his Spirit-Wind command,and God created
        the heavenlies.Filled with galaxies and stars,the vast cosmos he wonderfully
        made.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: His voice scooped out the seas.The ocean depths he poured into vast
        reservoirs.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: With breathtaking wonder,let everyone worship <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        this awe-inspiring Creator.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He breathed words and worlds were birthed.\u201CLet there be,\u201D
        and there it was\u2014springing forth the moment he spoke,no sooner said
        than done!"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: With his breath he scatters the schemes of nations who oppose him;they
        will never succeed.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: His destiny-plan for the earth stands sure.His forever-plan remains
        in place and will never fail.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Blessed and prosperous is that nation who has God as their Lord!They
        will be the people he has chosen for his own.
      comments: []
    - name: '13-15: '
      title: 
      number: 13-15
      content: The Lord looks over us from where he rules in heaven.Gazing into every
        heart from his lofty dwelling place,he observes all the peoples of the earth.The
        Creator of our hearts considers and examines everything we do.
      comments: []
    - name: '13-15: '
      title: 
      number: 13-15
      content: The Lord looks over us from where he rules in heaven.Gazing into every
        heart from his lofty dwelling place,he observes all the peoples of the earth.The
        Creator of our hearts considers and examines everything we do.
      comments: []
    - name: '13-15: '
      title: 
      number: 13-15
      content: The Lord looks over us from where he rules in heaven.Gazing into every
        heart from his lofty dwelling place,he observes all the peoples of the earth.The
        Creator of our hearts considers and examines everything we do.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Even if a king had the best-equipped army,it would never be enough
        to save him.Even if the best warrior went to battle,he could not be saved
        simply by his strength alone.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Human strength and the weapons of manare false hopes for victory;they
        may seem mighty, but they will always disappoint.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The eyes of the Lord are uponeven the weakest worshipers who love
        him\u2014those who wait in hope and expectationfor the strong, steady love
        of God."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: God will deliver them from death,even the certain death of famine,
        with no one to help.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The Lord alone is our radiant hopeand we trust in him with all our
        hearts.His wraparound presence will strengthen us.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: As we trust, we rejoice with an uncontained joyflowing from <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Let your love and steadfast kindness overshadow us continually,for
        we trust and we wait upon you!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Goodness"
      title: "God\u2019s Goodness"
      number: 1
      content: "A song by King David composed after his escape from the king when
        he pretended to be insaneLord! I\u2019m bursting with joy over what you\u2019ve
        done for me!My lips are full of perpetual praise."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I\u2019m boasting of you and all your works,so let all who are discouraged
        take heart."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Join me, everyone! Let\u2019s praise the Lord together.Let\u2019s
        make him famous!Let\u2019s make his name glorious to all."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Listen to my testimony: I cried to God in my distressand he answered
        me. He freed me from all my fears!'
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Gaze upon him, join your life with his, and joy will come.Your faces
        will glisten with glory.You\u2019ll never wear that shame-face again."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: When I had nothing, desperate and defeated,I cried out to the Lord
        and he heard me,bringing his miracle-deliverance when I needed it most. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 34:6
        content: "  David wrote this psalm at perhaps the lowest point in his life.
          He was alone. He had to part from Jonathan, his dearest friend. He was
          being chased by Saul and his paid assassins. He had run to hide in the
          cave of Adullam (meaning \u201Ctheir prey\u201D). Yet the beautiful sounds
          of praise were heard echoing in his cavern. This is a lesson for all of
          us: we praise our way out of our difficulties into his light.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The angel of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> stooped down to listen
        as I prayed,encircling me, empowering me, and showing me how to escape.He
        will do this for everyone who fears God.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Drink deeply [[COMMENT(0)]] of the pleasures of this God.Experience
        for yourself the joyous mercies he givesto all who turn to hide themselves
        in him.
      comments:
      - number: 34:8
        content: "  Many translations read \u201CTaste and see.\u201D The Hebrew
          root word for \u201Csee\u201D is taken from a word that means \u201Cto
          drink deeply.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Worship in awe and wonder, all you who\u2019ve been made holy!For
        all who fear him will feast with plenty."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Even the strong and the wealthy [[COMMENT(0)]] grow weak and hungry,but
        those who passionately pursue the Lordwill never lack any good thing.
      comments:
      - number: 34:10
        content: "  Following the ancient versions (Septuagint, Syriac, and Vulgate),
          this phrase is translated \u201Crich ones.\u201D Modern translations read
          \u201Cyoung lions.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Come, children of God, and listen to me.I\u2019ll share the lesson
        I\u2019ve learned of fearing the Lord:"
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: Do you want to live a long, good life,enjoying the beauty that fills
        each day?Then never speak a lie or allow wicked wordsto come from your mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: Do you want to live a long, good life,enjoying the beauty that fills
        each day?Then never speak a lie or allow wicked wordsto come from your mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Keep turning your back on every sin,and make \u201Cpeace\u201D your
        life motto.Practice being at peace with everyone. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 34:14
        content: "  Twice in this verse David used the Hebrew word  . This word means
          much more than \u201Cpeace.\u201D It means wholeness, wellness, well-being,
          safe, happy, friendly, favor, completeness, to make peace, peace offering,
          secure, to prosper, to be victorious, to be content, tranquil, quiet, and
          restful. So    is used to describe those of us who have been provided all
          that is needed to be whole and complete and break off all authority that
          would attempt to bind us to chaos.    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The Lord sees all we do;he watches over his friends day and night.His
        godly ones receive the answers they seekwhenever they cry out to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But the Lord has made up his mind to oppose evildoersand to wipe out
        even the memory of themfrom the face of the earth. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 34:16
        content: '  See  .  '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Yet when holy lovers of God cry outto him with all their hearts,the
        Lord will hear them and come to rescue themfrom all their troubles.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The Lord is close to all whose hearts are crushed by pain,and he is
        always ready to restore the repentant one.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Even when bad things happen to the good and godly ones,the Lord will
        save them and not let them be defeatedby what they face.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: God will be your bodyguard to protect youwhen trouble is near.Not
        one bone will be broken.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Evil will cause the death of the wicked,for they hate and persecute
        the devoted lovers of God.Make no mistake about it:God will hold them guilty
        and punish them;they will pay the penalty!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: But the Lord has paid for the freedom of his servants,and he will
        freely pardon those who love him.He will declare them free and innocentwhen
        they turn to hide themselves in him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Rescue MePart One \u2013 David, a Warrior"
      title: "Rescue MePart One \u2013 David, a Warrior"
      number: 1
      content: A poetic song by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]O&nbsp;Lord, fight for me!
        Harass the hecklers; accuse my accusers.Fight those who fight against me.
      comments:
      - number: 35
        content: '  This is the first of seven Psalms in which David cried out for
          vengeance upon his enemies (see  ;  ;  ;  ;  ;  ).    '
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Put on your armor, Lord; take up your shield and protect me.Rise
        up, mighty God! Grab your weapons of warand block the way of the wicked who
        come to fight me.Stand for me when they stand against me!Speak over my soul:
        \u201CI am your strong Savior!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "35:2\u20133"
        content: "  The Aramaic word used here is found thirty-three times in the
          Psalms and clearly means \u201CSavior.\u201D Although a New Testament concept,
          David had a deep understanding almost one thousand years before the Savior
          was born that God would become his Savior. The Hebrew word for \u201CSavior,\u201D 
          , is very similar to the name Jesus,  .  "
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Put on your armor, Lord; take up your shield and protect me.Rise
        up, mighty God! Grab your weapons of warand block the way of the wicked who
        come to fight me.Stand for me when they stand against me!Speak over my soul:
        \u201CI am your strong Savior!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "35:2\u20133"
        content: "  The Aramaic word used here is found thirty-three times in the
          Psalms and clearly means \u201CSavior.\u201D Although a New Testament concept,
          David had a deep understanding almost one thousand years before the Savior
          was born that God would become his Savior. The Hebrew word for \u201CSavior,\u201D 
          , is very similar to the name Jesus,  .  "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Humiliate those who seek my harm. Defeat them all!Frustrate their
        plans to defeat me and drive them back.Disgrace them all as they have devised
        their plans to disgrace me.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Blow them away like dust in the wind,with the angel of Almighty God
        driving them back!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Make the road in front of them nothing but slippery darkness,with
        the angel of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> behind them, chasing them away!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For though I did nothing wrong to them, they set a trap for me,wanting
        me to fail and fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Surprise them with your ambush, Lord,and catch them in the very trap
        they set for me.Let them be the ones to fail and fall into destruction!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then my fears will dissolve into limitless joy;my whole being will
        overflow with gladnessbecause of your mighty deliverance.
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Part Two \u2013 David, a Witness"
      title: "Part Two \u2013 David, a Witness"
      number: 10
      content: "Everything inside of me will shout it out:\u201CThere\u2019s no one
        like you, Lord!\u201DFor look at how you protect the weak and helplessfrom
        the strong and heartless who oppress them."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: They are malicious men, hostile witnesses of wrong.They rise up against
        me, accusers appearing out of nowhere.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When I show them mercy, they bring me misery.I\u2019m forsaken and
        forlorn, like a motherless child."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I even prayed over them when they were sick.I was burdened and bowed
        low with fastingand interceded for their healing,and I didn\u2019t stop praying."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I grieved for them, heavyhearted,as though they were my dearest family
        membersor my good friends who were sick,nearing death, needing prayer.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But when I was the one who tripped up and stumbled,they came together
        to slander me,rejoicing in my time of trouble, tearing me to shredswith their
        lies and betrayal.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "These nameless ruffians,mocking me like godless fools at a feast\u2014how
        they delight in throwing mud on my name."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: God, how long can you just stand there doing nothing?Now is the time
        to act.Rescue me from these brutal men,for I am being torn to shreds by these
        beastswho are out to get me.Save me from their rage, their cruel grasp.
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Part Three \u2013 David, a Worshiper"
      title: "Part Three \u2013 David, a Worshiper"
      number: 18
      content: Then I will praise you wherever I go.And when everyone gathers for
        worship,I will lift up your praise with a shoutin front of the largest crowd
        I can find!
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Don\u2019t let those who fight me for no reason be victorious.Don\u2019t
        let them succeed, these heartless haterswho come against me with their gloating
        sneers."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: They are the ones who would never seek peace as friends,for they are
        ever devising deceit against the innocent oneswho mind their own business.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "They open their mouths with ugly grins,gloating with glee over my
        every fault.\u201CLook,\u201D they say, \u201Cwe caught him red-handed!We
        saw him fall with our own eyes!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, my caring God, you have been there
        all along.You have seen their hypocrisy.<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, don\u2019t
        let them get away with this.Don\u2019t walk away without doing something."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Now is the time to awake! Rise up, Lord!Vindicate me, my Lord and
        my God!
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "You have every right to judge me, Lord,according to your righteousness,but
        don\u2019t let them rejoice over me when I stumble."
      comments: []
    - name: '25-26: '
      title: 
      number: 25-26
      content: "Let them all be ashamed of themselves,humiliated when they rejoice
        over my every blunder.Shame them, Lord, when they say, \u201CWe saw what
        he did.Now we have him right where we want him.Let\u2019s get him while he\u2019s
        down!\u201DMake them look ridiculous when they exalt themselves over me.May
        they all be disgraced and dishonored!"
      comments: []
    - name: '25-26: '
      title: 
      number: 25-26
      content: "Let them all be ashamed of themselves,humiliated when they rejoice
        over my every blunder.Shame them, Lord, when they say, \u201CWe saw what
        he did.Now we have him right where we want him.Let\u2019s get him while he\u2019s
        down!\u201DMake them look ridiculous when they exalt themselves over me.May
        they all be disgraced and dishonored!"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But let all my true friends shout for joy,all those who know and
        love what I do for you.Let them all say, \u201CThe Lord is great,and he delights
        in the prosperity of his servant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then I won\u2019t be able to hold it in\u2014everyone will hear my
        joyous praises all day long!Your righteousness will be the theme of my glory-song
        of praise!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Blessing of the Wise'
      title: The Blessing of the Wise
      number: 1
      content: A poetic song by King David, the servant of the LordThe rebellion
        of sin speaks as an oracle of God,speaking deeply to the conscience of wicked
        men. [[COMMENT(0)]]Yet they are still eager to sin,for the fear of God is
        not before their eyes.
      comments:
      - number: 36:1
        content: "  Or \u201CThe heart of the wicked is rebellious to the core.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: See how they flatter themselves,unable to detect and detest their
        sins.They are crooked and conceited,convinced they can get away with anything.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Their wicked words are nothing but lies.Wisdom is far from them.Goodness
        is both forgotten and forsaken.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They lie awake at night to hatch their evil plots,always planning
        their schemes of darkness,and never once do they consider the evil of their
        ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But you, O&nbsp;Lord, your mercy-seat love is limitless,reaching higher
        than the highest heavens.Your great faithfulness is infinite,stretching over
        the whole earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Your righteousness is unmovable,just like the mighty mountains.Your
        judgments are as full of wisdomas the oceans are full of water.Your tender
        care and kindness leave no one forgotten,not a man or even a mouse.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: O&nbsp;God, how extravagant is your cherishing love!All mankind can
        find a hiding placeunder the shadow of your wings.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All may drink of the anointing from the abundance [[COMMENT(0)]]
        of your house. All may drink their fill from the rivers of Eden. '
      comments:
      - number: 36:8
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Cabundance\u201D is literally
          \u201Cbutterfat\u201D or \u201Coil.\u201D It is a symbol of the anointing
          of the Holy Spirit.      Or \u201CThey will be satisfied [or watered] in
          the abundance of your house.\u201D      Or \u201CEden\u2019s rivers of
          pleasure.\u201D The garden of Eden had flowing rivers of delight. Eden
          means \u201Cpleasure.\u201D The Hebrew word used here is the plural form
          of Eden.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The fountain of life flows from you [[COMMENT(0)]]  to satisfy me.In
        your light of holiness we receive the light of revelation.
      comments:
      - number: 36:9
        content: '  See  ;  ;  .  '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Lord, keep pouring out your unfailing loveon those who are near you.Release
        more of your blessings to those who are loyal to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Don\u2019t let these proud boasters trample me down;don\u2019t let
        them push me aroundby the sheer strength of their wickedness."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: There they lie in the dirt, these evil ones,thrown down to the ground,
        never to arise again!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Song of Wisdom'
      title: A Song of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: "Poetic praise by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]Don\u2019t follow after
        the wicked ones or be jealous of their wealth.Don\u2019t think for a moment
        they\u2019re better off than you."
      comments:
      - number: 37
        content: '    is an acrostic psalm, in which every other verse begins with
          a successive letter of the Hebrew alphabet.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: They and their short-lived successwill soon shrivel up and quickly
        fade away,like grass clippings in the hot sun.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Keep trusting in the Lord and do what is right in his eyes.Fix your
        heart on the promises of God, and you will dwell in the land,feasting on
        his faithfulness.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Find your delight [[COMMENT(0)]] and true pleasure in <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,and
        he will give you what you desire the most.
      comments:
      - number: 37:4
        content: "  The word    means \u201Cto be soft or tender.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Give [[COMMENT(0)]] God the right to direct your life,and as you
        trust him along the way,you\u2019ll find he pulled it off perfectly!"
      comments:
      - number: 37:5
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here can be translated \u201Ccommit,\u201D
          which means \u201Cto roll over your burdens on the Lord.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He will appear [[COMMENT(0)]] as your righteousness,as sure as the
        dawning of a new day.He will manifest as your justice,as sure and strong
        as the noonday sun.
      comments:
      - number: 37:6
        content: '  The Hebrew verb found here is also used for giving birth. Perhaps
          this is a reference to the birth of Christ, our righteousness.    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Quiet your heart in his presenceand wait [[COMMENT(0)]] patiently
        for <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>.And don\u2019t think for a moment that
        the wicked, in their prosperity,are better off than you."
      comments:
      - number: 37:7
        content: "  The root word of the word for \u201Cwait\u201D can mean \u201Cto
          whirl\u201D or \u201Cto be in labor [give birth].\u201D What an unusual
          concept for waiting on God. We may feel like we\u2019re being    around
          by our circumstances, but in the end, our season of waiting    to greater
          things.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Stay away from anger and revenge.Keep envy far from you, for it only
        leads you into lies.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For one day the wicked will be destroyed,but those who trust in the
        Lordwill inherit the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Just a little while longer and the ungodly will vanish;you will look
        for them in vain.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: But the humble of heart will inherit every promise [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        enjoy abundant peace.
      comments:
      - number: 37:11
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Let the wicked keep plotting against the godlywith all their sneers
        and arrogant jeers.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: God laughs at the wicked and their plans,for he knows their day is
        coming!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Evil ones take aim at the poor and helpless;they are ready to slaughter
        those who do right.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But the Lord will turn all their weapons of wickedness back on themselves,piercing
        their pride-filled hearts until they are helpless.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: It is much better to have littlecombined with much of Godthan to have
        the fabulous wealth of the wicked and nothing else.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For the Lord takes care of all his forgiven oneswhile the strength
        of evil men will surely slip away.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Day by day the Lord watches the good deeds of the godly,and he prepares
        for them his forever-reward.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Even in a time of disaster he will watch over them,and they will always
        have more than enoughno matter what happens.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: All the enemies of God will perish.For the wicked have only a momentary
        value, a fading glory.Then one day they vanish! Here today, gone tomorrow.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: They break their promises, borrowing moneybut never paying it back.The
        good man returns what he owes with some extra besides.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s blessed ones receive the land,but
        the cursed ones will be cut offwith nothing to show for themselves."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: When <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> delights in how you live your life,he
        establishes your every step.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: If they stumble badly they will still survive,for the Lord lifts them
        up with his hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I was once inexperienced, [[COMMENT(0)]] but now I\u2019m old.Not
        once have I found a lover of God forsaken by him,nor have any of their children
        gone hungry."
      comments:
      - number: 37:25
        content: "  Or \u201Cimmature.\u201D The Hebrew word    has a homonym that
          means \u201Cto be driven out,\u201D which may be a reference to David being
          driven out of Jerusalem by Absalom.  "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Instead, I\u2019ve found the godly onesto be the generous ones who
        give freely to others.Their children are blessed and become a blessing."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If you truly want to dwell forever in God\u2019s presence,forsake
        evil and do what is right in his eyes."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The Lord loves it when he sees us walking in his justice.He will never
        desert his devoted lovers;they will be kept forever in his faithful care,but
        the descendants of the wicked will be banished.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The faithful lovers of God will inherit the earthand enjoy every
        promise of God\u2019s care,dwelling in peace forever."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: God-lovers make the best counselors.Their words possess wisdom and
        are right and trustworthy.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The ways of God are in their heartsand they won\u2019t swerve from
        the paths of steadfast righteousness."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Evil ones spy on the godly ones, stalking themto find something they
        could use to accuse them.They\u2019re out for the kill!"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: But God will foil all their plots.The godly will not stand condemned
        when brought to trial.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So don\u2019t be impatient for <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> to act;keep
        moving forward steadily in his ways,and he will exalt you to possess the
        land.You\u2019ll watch with your own eyesand see the wicked lose everything."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "I\u2019ve already seen this happen.Once I saw a wicked and violent
        manoverpower all who were around him,a domineering tyrant with his prideful
        and oppressive ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Then he died and was forgotten.Now no one cares that he is gone forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: But you can tell who are the blameless and spiritually mature.What
        a different story with them!The godly ones will have a peaceful, prosperous
        futurewith a happy ending.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Every evil sinner will be destroyed, obliterated.They\u2019ll be
        utter failures with no future!"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: But the Lord will be the Savior of all who love him.Even in their
        time of trouble, God will live in them as strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Because of their faith in him, their daily portion will bea Father\u2019s
        help and deliverance from evil.This is true for all who turn to hide themselves
        in him!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Groan before the Throne'
      title: A Groan before the Throne
      number: 1
      content: "A poetic lament to remember, by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]O&nbsp;Lord,
        don\u2019t punish me angrily for what I\u2019ve done.Don\u2019t let my sin
        inflame your wrath against me."
      comments:
      - number: 38
        content: "  The Septuagint has in the inscription \u201CTo be remembered
          on the Sabbath.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For the arrows of your conviction have pierced me deeply.Your blows
        have struck my soul and crushed me.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now my body is sick.My health is totally broken because of your anger,and
        it\u2019s all due to my sins!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I\u2019m overwhelmed, swamped, and submergedbeneath the heavy burden
        of my guilt.It clings to me and won\u2019t let me go."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: My rotting wounds are a witness against me.They are severe and getting
        worse,reminding me of my failure and folly.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I am completely broken because of what I\u2019ve done.Gloom is all
        around me.My sins have bent me over to the ground."
      comments: []
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "My inner being is shriveled up;my self-confidence crushed.Sick with
        fever, I\u2019m left exhausted.Now I\u2019m as cold as a corpse, and nothing
        is left inside mebut great groaning filled with anguish."
      comments: []
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "My inner being is shriveled up;my self-confidence crushed.Sick with
        fever, I\u2019m left exhausted.Now I\u2019m as cold as a corpse, and nothing
        is left inside mebut great groaning filled with anguish."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Lord, you know all my desires and deepest longings.My tears are liquid
        words, and you can read them all.
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: My heart beats wildly, my strength is sapped,and the light of my eyes
        is going out.My friends stay far away from me, avoiding me like the plague.Even
        my family wants nothing to do with me.
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: My heart beats wildly, my strength is sapped,and the light of my eyes
        is going out.My friends stay far away from me, avoiding me like the plague.Even
        my family wants nothing to do with me.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Meanwhile my enemies are out to kill me,plotting my ruin, speaking
        of my doomas they spend every waking momentplanning how to finish me off.
      comments: []
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "I\u2019m like a deaf man who no longer hears.I can\u2019t even speak
        up, and words fail me;I have no argument to counter their threats."
      comments: []
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "I\u2019m like a deaf man who no longer hears.I can\u2019t even speak
        up, and words fail me;I have no argument to counter their threats."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Lord, the only thing I can do is wait and put my hope in you.I wait
        for your help, my God.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So hear my cry and put an end to their strutting in pride,to those
        who gloat when I stumble in pain.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I\u2019m slipping away and on the verge of a breakdown,with nothing
        but sorrow and sighing. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 38:17
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CI am prepared for all of their whips\u2014prepared
          to suffer.\u201D  "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I confess all my sin to you; I can\u2019t hold it in any longer.My
        agonizing thoughts punish me for my wrongdoing;I feel condemned as I consider
        all I\u2019ve done."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "My enemies are many.They hate me and persecute me,though I\u2019ve
        done nothing against them to deserve it."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: I show goodness to them and get paid evil in return.And they hate
        me even more when I stand for what is right.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So don\u2019t forsake me now, Lord!Don\u2019t leave me in this condition."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "God, hurry to help me. Run to my rescue!For you\u2019re my Savior
        and my only hope!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: A Cry for Help'
      title: A Cry for Help
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA song of praising by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]Here\u2019s
        my life motto, the truth I live by:I will guard my ways for all my days.I
        will speak only what is right, guarding what I speak.Like a watchman guards
        against an attack of the enemy,I\u2019ll guard and muzzle my mouthwhen the
        wicked are around me.I will remain silent and will not grumbleor speak out
        of my disappointment.But the longer I\u2019m silent, the more my pain grows
        worse!"
      comments:
      - number: 39
        content: "  The Hebrew inscription includes the name Jeduthun, which can
          be translated \u201Cpraising.\u201D    "
    - name: '1-2: A Cry for Help'
      title: A Cry for Help
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA song of praising by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]Here\u2019s
        my life motto, the truth I live by:I will guard my ways for all my days.I
        will speak only what is right, guarding what I speak.Like a watchman guards
        against an attack of the enemy,I\u2019ll guard and muzzle my mouthwhen the
        wicked are around me.I will remain silent and will not grumbleor speak out
        of my disappointment.But the longer I\u2019m silent, the more my pain grows
        worse!"
      comments:
      - number: 39
        content: "  The Hebrew inscription includes the name Jeduthun, which can
          be translated \u201Cpraising.\u201D    "
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "My heart burned with a fire within me,and my thoughts eventually
        boiled overuntil they finally came rolling out of my mouth:\u201CLord, help
        me to know how fleeting my time on earth is.Help me to know how limited is
        my lifeand that I\u2019m only here but for a moment more."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "My heart burned with a fire within me,and my thoughts eventually
        boiled overuntil they finally came rolling out of my mouth:\u201CLord, help
        me to know how fleeting my time on earth is.Help me to know how limited is
        my lifeand that I\u2019m only here but for a moment more."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "What a brief [[COMMENT(0)]] time you\u2019ve given me to live!Compared
        to you my lifetime is nothing at all!Nothing more than a puff of air\u2014I\u2019m
        gone so swiftly.So too are the grandest of men;they are nothing but a fleeting
        shadow!\u201DPause in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 39:5
        content: "  Interestingly, the Hebrew word for \u201Cbrief\u201D in this
          verse is \u201Ca handbreadth,\u201D or the span of a man\u2019s hand. Our
          life\u2019s duration is compared to a mere six-inch span!    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: We live our lives like those living in shadows. [[COMMENT(0)]]All
        our activities and energies are spent for things that pass away.We gather,
        we hoard, we cling to our things,only to leave them all behind for who knows
        who.
      comments:
      - number: 39:6
        content: "  Or \u201Clike phantoms going to and fro.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And now, God, [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>.</smallcaps>
        I\u2019m left with one conclusion:my only hope is to hope in you alone!"
      comments:
      - number: 39:7
        content: '  The Aramaic is  , the Aramaic form of  or Lord    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Save me from being overpowered by my sin;don\u2019t make me a disgrace
        before the degenerate."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Lord, I\u2019m left speechless and I have no excuse,so I\u2019ll
        not complain any longer.Now I know you\u2019re the one who is behind it all."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But I can\u2019t take it much longer.Spare me these blows from your
        discipline-rod.For if you are against me, I will waste away to nothing."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "No one endures when you rebuke and discipline us for our sins.Like
        a cobweb is swept away with a wave of the hand,you sweep away all that we
        once called dear.How fleeting and frail our lives!We\u2019re nothing more
        than a puff of air.Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Lord, listen to all my tender cries.Read my every tear, like liquid
        words that plead for your help.I feel all alone at times, like a stranger
        to you,passing through this life just like all those before me.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Don\u2019t let me die without restoringjoy and gladness to my soul.May
        your frown over my failurebecome a smile over my success."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Joyful Salvation'
      title: A Joyful Salvation
      number: 1
      content: For the Pure and Shining OneA song of poetic praise by King DavidI
        waited and waited and waited some more,patiently, knowing God would come
        through for me.Then, at last, he bent down and listened to my cry.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He stooped down to lift me out of dangerfrom the desolate pit I was
        in,out of the muddy mess I had fallen into.Now he\u2019s lifted me up into
        a firm, secure placeand steadied me while I walk along his ascending path."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A new song for a new day rises up in meevery time I think about how
        he breaks through for me!Ecstatic praise pours out of my mouth untileveryone
        hears how God has set me free.Many will see his miracles;they\u2019ll stand
        in awe of God and fall in love with him!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Blessing after blessing comes to those who love and trust the Lord.They
        will not fall away,for they refuse to listen to the lies of the proud.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "O Lord, our God, no one can compare with you.Such wonderful works
        and miracles are all found with you!And you think of us all the timewith
        your countless expressions of love\u2014far exceeding our expectations!"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "It\u2019s not sacrifices that really move your heart.Burnt offerings,
        sin offerings\u2014those aren\u2019t what bring you joy.But when you open
        my ears and speak to me,I become your willing servant, your prisoner of love
        for life. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 40:6
        content: "  The Septuagint is \u201Ca body you have prepared for me.\u201D
          The Hebrew reads \u201CYou have pierced my ear.\u201D This is a Hebraic
          reference to being a bond servant whose ear has been pierced by his master
          to signify the servant\u2019s desire to serve for life. See  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So I said, \u201CHere I am! I\u2019m coming to you as a sacrifice,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]for in the prophetic scrolls of your bookyou have written about
        me."
      comments:
      - number: 40:7
        content: '  Implied in the context. See  .    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I delight to fulfill your will, my God,for your living words are
        written upon the pages of my heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "I tell everyone everywhere the truth of your righteousness.And you
        know I haven\u2019t held back in telling the message to all."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I don\u2019t keep it a secret or hide the truth.I preach of your
        faithfulness and kindness,proclaiming your extravagant love to the largest
        crowd I can find!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Lord, don\u2019t hold back your love or withholdyour tender mercies
        from me.Keep me in your truth and let your compassion overflow to meno matter
        what I face."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Evil surrounds me; problems greater than I can solvecome one after
        another.Without you, I know I can\u2019t make it.My sins are so many!I\u2019m
        so ashamed to lift my face to you.For my guilt grabs me and stings my souluntil
        I am weakened and spent."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Please, Lord! Come quickly and rescue me!Take pleasure in showing
        me your favor and restore me.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Let all who seek my life be humiliated!Let them be confused and ashamed,
        God.Scatter those who wish me evil; they just want me dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Scoff at every scoffer and cause them all to be utter failures.Let
        them be ashamed and horrified by their complete defeat.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But let all who passionately seek youerupt with excitement and joy
        over what you\u2019ve done!Let all your devoted lovers rejoice continually
        in the Savior, [[COMMENT(0)]] saying,\u201CHow great and glorious is our
        God!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 40:16
        content: '  This verse contains the root word for Yeshua in Hebrew.  '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Lord, in my place of weakness and need, I ask again:Will you come
        and help me?I know I\u2019m always in your thoughts.You are my true Savior
        and hero,so don\u2019t delay to deliver me now, for you are my God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: I Need You, Lord'
      title: I Need You, Lord
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic song for the Pure and Shining OneGod always
        blesses those who are kind to the poor and helpless.They\u2019re the first
        ones God helpswhen they find themselves in any trouble."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord will preserve and protect them.They\u2019ll be honored and
        esteemed [[COMMENT(0)]]while their enemies are defeated."
      comments:
      - number: 41:2
        content: "  Or \u201CThey will be blessed in the land.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: When they are sick, lying upon their bed of suffering,God will restore
        them.He will raise them up again and restore them back to health.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So in my sickness I say to you,\u201CLord, be my kind healer.Heal
        my body and soul; heal me, God!For I have confessed my sins to you.\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 41:4
        content: "  Or \u201CFor I have sinned against you.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But those who hate me wish the worst for me, saying,\u201CWhen will
        he die and be forgotten?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when these \u201Cfriends\u201D come to visit mewith their pious
        sympathy and their hollow wordsand with hypocrisy hidden in their hearts,I
        can see right through it all.For they come merely to gather gossip about
        me,using all they find to mock me with malicious hearts of slander."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They are wicked whisperers who imagine the worst for me,repeating
        their rumors, saying,
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CHe got what he deserved; it\u2019s over for him!The spirit
        of infirmity [[COMMENT(0)]] is upon him,and he\u2019ll never get over this
        illness.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 41:8
        content: "  Or \u201CA thing of Belial\u201D or \u201CAn affliction from
          the abandoned one.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Even my ally, my friend, has turned against me.He was one I totally
        trusted with my life,sharing supper with him, [[COMMENT(0)]]and now he shows
        me nothing but betrayal and treachery.He has sold me as an enemy. '
      comments:
      - number: 41:9
        content: "  In the ancient Near Eastern culture, sharing a meal together
          was a sign of covenant friendship.      The Hebrew literally reads \u201CHe
          lifted up his heel against me.\u201D This is a powerful figure of speech
          meaning he was sold as an enemy and was treated treacherously. This verse
          was quoted, in part, by Jesus at the Last Supper (see    and footnote).    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Lord, please don\u2019t desert me when I need you!Give me grace
        and get me back on my feetso I can triumph over them all."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I\u2019ll know you\u2019re pleased with mewhen you allow me
        to taste victory over all my foes."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now stand up for me and don\u2019t let me fall,for I\u2019ve walked
        with integrity.Keep me before your face forever."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Book 2The Exodus PsalmsPsalms of suffering and redemption'
      title: Book 2The Exodus PsalmsPsalms of suffering and redemption
      number: 13
      content: "Everyone praise the Lord God of Israel, always and forever!For he
        is from eternity pastand will remain for the eternity to come.That\u2019s
        the way it will be forever.Faithful is our King! Amen! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 41:13
        content: "  Some scholars believe this last verse was added as a \u201Cdoxology
          of praise,\u201D marking the end of the first book of Psalms. The word   
          could be translated as \u201CFaithful is our King!\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Cry for Revival 42Psalms 42and43were originally composed as one
        psalm and later made into two.'
      title: A Cry for Revival 42Psalms 42and43were originally composed as one psalm
        and later made into two.
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]For the Pure and Shining OneA contemplative poem for
        instruction by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s clan [[COMMENT(1)]]I
        long to drink of you, O&nbsp;God,to drink deeply from the streams of pleasureflowing
        from your presence.My longings overwhelm me for more of you! [[COMMENT(2)]]"
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">42</span>
        content: '    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">and</span>    <span
          class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">were originally composed as one psalm
          and later made into two.</span>    '
      - number: 42
        content: "  Korah was the great-grandson of Levi. The sons of Korah (translated
          here as the \u201Cprophetic singers of Korah\u2019s clan\u201D) were Levitical
          singers. David chose them to preside over the music of the tabernacle-tent
          on Mount Zion.    "
      - number: 42:1
        content: "  The literal Hebrew is \u201Cas the deer pants for the riverbank
          [water\u2019s edge].\u201D This translation takes the metaphor of a hunted
          deer and puts it into terms that transfer the meaning into today\u2019s
          context. David was describing the passion and longing he had that was yet
          unfulfilled.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: My soul thirsts, pants, and longs for the living God.I want to come
        and see the face of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Day and night my tears keep fallingand my heart keeps crying for
        your help,while my enemies mock me over and over, saying,\u201CWhere is this
        God of yours? Why doesn\u2019t he help you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So I speak over my heartbroken soul,\u201CTake courage. Remember
        when you used to beright out front leading the procession of praisewhen the
        great crowd of worshipersgathered to go into the presence of the Lord?You
        shouted with joy as the sound of passionate celebrationfilled the air and
        the joyous multitude of lovershonored the feast of the Lord!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: So then, my soul, why would you be depressed?Why would you sink into
        despair?Just keep hoping and waiting on God, your Savior.For no matter what,
        I will still sing with praise,for you are my saving grace!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Here I am depressed and downcast.Yet I will still remember you as
        I ponder the placewhere your glory streams down from the mighty mountaintops,
        lofty and majestic\u2014the mountains of your awesome presence. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 42:6
        content: "  The Hebrew text contains \u201CMount Hermon\u201D and \u201CMount
          Mizar,\u201D considered to be sacred mountains in the Hebrew culture.   
          means \u201Clofty and majestic.\u201D    means \u201Clittleness.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: My deep need calls out to the deep kindness of your love.Your waterfall
        of weeping sent waves of sorrowover my soul, carrying me away,cascading over
        me like a thundering cataract.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: All through the day <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> has commanded his
        endless love to pour over me.Through the night I sing his songsand my praises
        [[COMMENT(0)]] to the living God.
      comments:
      - number: 42:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cmy prayer.\u201D  "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "I will say to God, \u201CYou are my mountain of strength;how could
        you forget me?Why must I suffer this vile oppression of my enemies\u2014these
        heartless tormentors who are out to kill me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Their wounding words pierce my heartover and over while they say,\u201CWhere
        is this God of yours?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So I say to my soul,\u201CDon\u2019t be discouraged. Don\u2019t be
        disturbed.For I know my God will break through for me.\u201DThen I\u2019ll
        have plenty of reasons to praise him all over again.Yes, he is my saving
        grace!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Light and Truth'
      title: Light and Truth
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s
        clan [[COMMENT(0)]]A contemplative poem for instructionGod, clear my name.Plead
        my case against the unjust chargesof these ungodly workers of wickedness.Deliver
        me from these lying degenerates."
      comments:
      - number: 43
        content: '  Originally there was no inscription for this psalm as it was
          part of  .    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For you are where my strength comes from [[COMMENT(0)]] and my protector,so
        why would you leave me now?Must I be covered with gloomwhile the enemy comes
        after me, gloating with glee?
      comments:
      - number: 43:2
        content: "  Or \u201CGod of my strength.\u201D  "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Pour into me the brightness of your daybreak!Pour into me your rays
        of revelation-truth!Let them comfort and gently lead me onto the shining
        path,showing the way into your burning presence,into your many sanctuaries
        of holiness.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Then I will come closer to your very altaruntil I come before you,
        the God of my ecstatic joy!I will praise you with the harp that plays in
        my heart to you,my God, my magnificent God!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I will say to my soul,\u201CDon\u2019t be discouraged; don\u2019t
        be disturbed,for I fully expect my Savior-God to break through for me.Then
        I\u2019ll have plenty of reasons to praise him all over again.\u201DYes,
        he is my saving grace!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1-2: Wake Up, Lord, We\u2019re in TroubleThe Past"
      title: "Wake Up, Lord, We\u2019re in TroubleThe Past"
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s
        clanA contemplative poem for instructionGod, we\u2019ve heard about all the
        glorious miraclesyou\u2019ve done for our ancestors in days gone by.They
        told us about the ancient times, how by your poweryou drove out the ungodly
        nations from this land,crushing all their strongholds and giving the land
        to us.Now the people of Israel cover the landfrom one end to the other,all
        because of your grace and power!"
      comments: []
    - name: "1-2: Wake Up, Lord, We\u2019re in TroubleThe Past"
      title: "Wake Up, Lord, We\u2019re in TroubleThe Past"
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s
        clanA contemplative poem for instructionGod, we\u2019ve heard about all the
        glorious miraclesyou\u2019ve done for our ancestors in days gone by.They
        told us about the ancient times, how by your poweryou drove out the ungodly
        nations from this land,crushing all their strongholds and giving the land
        to us.Now the people of Israel cover the landfrom one end to the other,all
        because of your grace and power!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Our forefathers didn\u2019t take the land by their own strengthor
        their own skill or strategy.But it was through the shining forth of your
        radiant presenceand the display of your mighty power.You loved to give them
        victory,for you took great delight in them."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You are my God, my King!It\u2019s now time to decree majesties for
        Jacob!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Through your glorious name and your awesome power,we can push through
        to any victory and defeat every enemy.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For I will not trust in the weapons of the world; [[COMMENT(0)]]I
        know they will never save me.
      comments:
      - number: 44:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cbow and sword.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Only you will be our Savior from all our enemies.All those who hate
        us you have brought to shame.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Present'
      title: The Present
      number: 8
      content: So now I constantly boast in you.I can never thank you enough!Pause
        in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But you have turned your back on us; you walked off and left us!You\u2019ve
        rejected us, tossing us aside in humiliating shame.You don\u2019t go before
        us anymore in our battles."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: We retreat before our enemies in defeat,for you are no longer helping
        us.Those who hate us have invaded our landand plundered our people.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "You have treated us like sheep in the slaughter pen,ready to be butchered.You\u2019ve
        scattered us to the four winds."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: You have sold us as slaves for nothing!You have counted us, your precious
        ones, as worthless.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: You have caused our neighbors to despise and scorn us.All those around
        us mock and curse us.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: You have made us the butt of their jokes.Disliked by all, we are the
        laughingstock of the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: "There\u2019s no escape from this constant curse, this humiliation!We
        are despised, jeered, overwhelmed by shame,and overcome at every turnby our
        hateful and heartless enemies."
      comments: []
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: "There\u2019s no escape from this constant curse, this humiliation!We
        are despised, jeered, overwhelmed by shame,and overcome at every turnby our
        hateful and heartless enemies."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Despite all of this, we have not forgotten you;we have not broken
        covenant with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: We have not betrayed you; our hearts are still yours.Our steps have
        not strayed from your path.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Yet you have crushed us,leaving us in this wilderness place of misery
        and desperation. [[COMMENT(0)]]With nowhere else to turn,death\u2019s dark
        door seems to be the only way out."
      comments:
      - number: 44:19
        content: "  Or \u201Cin this place of jackals.\u201D  "
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: "If we had forsaken your holy name, wouldn\u2019t you know it?You\u2019d
        be right in leaving us.If we had worshiped before other gods,no one would
        blame you for punishing us.God, you know our every heart-secret.You know
        we still want you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: "If we had forsaken your holy name, wouldn\u2019t you know it?You\u2019d
        be right in leaving us.If we had worshiped before other gods,no one would
        blame you for punishing us.God, you know our every heart-secret.You know
        we still want you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Future'
      title: The Future
      number: 22
      content: Because of you we face death threats every day.Like martyrs we are
        dying daily.We are seen as lambs lined up to be slaughtered as sacrifices.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So wake up, Lord God!Why would you sleep when we\u2019re in trouble?Are
        you forsaking us forever?"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "You can\u2019t hide your face any longer from us!How could you forget
        our agonizing sorrow?"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Now we lay facedown, sinking into the dust of death,the quicksand
        of the grave.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Arise, awake, and come to help us, O&nbsp;Lord.Let your unfailing
        love save us from this sorrow!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wedding SongHis Royal Majesty'
      title: The Wedding SongHis Royal Majesty
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s
        clanA contemplative song of instruction for the Loved OneTo the melody of
        \u201CLilies\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]My heart is on fire, boiling over with passion.Bubbling
        up within me are these beautiful lyricsas a lovely poem to be sung for the
        King.Like a river bursting its banks, I\u2019m overflowing with words,spilling
        out into this sacred story. [[COMMENT(1)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 45
        content: "  Lilies in the Bible are metaphors of God\u2019s precious people.
          See  ;  ;  . Many believe this was the wedding song composed for Solomon
          as he married the princess of Egypt. But the language is so lofty and glorious
          that we see One greater than Solomon in its verses. This is a song of the
          wedding of Jesus and his bride, the church.    "
      - number: 45:1
        content: "  The Hebrew is literally \u201CMy tongue is the pen of a skillful
          [inspired] scribe.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Beautiful! Beautiful! Beyond the sons of men! [[COMMENT(0)]]Elegant
        grace pours out through every word you speak. Truly God has anointed you,
        his favored one, for eternity!
      comments:
      - number: 45:2
        content: "  Or \u201CYou are the most wonderful and winsome of all men.\u201D     
          See  ;  .    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Now strap your lightning-sword of judgment upon your side,O&nbsp;mighty
        warrior, so majestic!You are full of beauty and splendor as you go out to
        war!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: In your glory and grandeur go forth in victory!Through your faithfulness
        and meeknessthe cause of truth and justice will stand.Awe-inspiring miracles
        are accomplished by your power,leaving everyone dazed and astonished!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Your wounding leaves men\u2019s hearts defeatedas they fall before
        you broken."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Your glory-kingdom, O&nbsp;God, endures forever,for you are enthroned
        to rule with a justice-scepter in your hand!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You are passionate for righteousness, and you hate lawlessness.This
        is why God, your God,crowns you with bliss above your fellow kings.He has
        anointed you, more than any other,with his oil of fervent joy,the very fragrance
        of heaven\u2019s gladness."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Her Royal Majesty'
      title: Her Royal Majesty
      number: 8
      content: Your royal robes release the scent of suffering love [[COMMENT(0)]]
        for your bride;the odor of aromatic incense  is upon you.From the pure and
        shining place,  lovely musicthat makes you glad is played for your pleasure.
      comments:
      - number: 45:8
        content: "  The Hebrew word    is taken from a root word that means \u201Csuffering.\u201D
          Jewish rabbis refer to myrrh as \u201Ctears from a tree,\u201D a symbol
          of suffering love.      The Hebrew text reads \u201Caloes and cassia.\u201D
          Both are equated with the anointing spice, the incense burned in the Holy
          Place.      Or \u201Cfrom the ivory palaces.\u201D This is an obvious reference
          to the Holy Place, as our High Priest comes from the chamber of glory to
          be with us. The word    is taken from a Hebrew word for \u201Cwhite and
          glistening.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The daughters of kings, women of honor,are maidens in your courts.And
        standing beside you,glistening in your pure and golden glory,is the beautiful
        bride-to-be! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 45:9
        content: "  Or \u201Cqueen.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Now listen, daughter, pay attention, and forget about your past.Put
        behind you every attachment to the familiar,even those who once were close
        to you!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For your royal Bridegroom is ravished by your beautiful brightness.Bow
        in reverence before him, for he is your Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Wedding presents pour in from those of great wealth. [[COMMENT(0)]]The
        royal friends of the Bridegroom shower you with gifts.
      comments:
      - number: 45:12
        content: "  The Hebrew text is literally \u201Cthe daughter of Tyre.\u201D
          This was symbolic of the merchants of the earth, those possessing great
          wealth.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: As the princess-bride enters the palace,how glorious she appears within
        the holy chamber,robed with a wedding dress embroidered with pure gold!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Lovely and stunning, she leads the procession with all her bridesmaids
        [[COMMENT(0)]]as they come before you, her Bridegroom-King.
      comments:
      - number: 45:14
        content: "  Or \u201Cvirgins.\u201D (See  ; cf.  .)  "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: What a grand, majestic entrance!A joyful, glad procession as they
        enter the palace gates!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Your many sons will one day be kings, just like their Father.They
        will sit on royal thrones all around the world.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I will make sure the fame of your nameis honored in every generation,
        as all the people praise you,giving you thanks forever and ever!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God on Our Side'
      title: God on Our Side
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s
        clanA poetic song to the melody of \u201CHidden Things\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]God,
        you\u2019re such a safe and powerful place to find refuge!You\u2019re a proven
        help in time of trouble\u2014more than enough and always available whenever
        I need you."
      comments:
      - number: 46
        content: "  As translated in the Septuagint. Other versions read \u201Cfor
          the maidens.\u201D    is known as one of the Songs of Zion. The others
          are  ;  ;  ;  ;  . These are psalms that praise Jerusalem as God\u2019s
          dwelling place.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So we will never feareven if every structure of support [[COMMENT(0)]]
        were to crumble away.We will not fear even when the earth quakes and shakes,moving
        mountains and casting them into the sea.
      comments:
      - number: 46:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cearth itself.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For the raging roar of stormy winds and crashing wavescannot erode
        our faith in you.Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: God has a constantly flowing river whose sparkling streamsbring joy
        and delight to his people.His river flows right through the city of God Most
        High,into his holy dwelling places. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 46:4
        content: "  The plural \u201Cdwelling places\u201D points to believers today.
          Each believer is now the holy dwelling place of God. God\u2019s river flows
          into us and through us.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: God is in the midst of his city, [[COMMENT(0)]] secure and never shaken.At
        daybreak his help will be seen with the appearing of the dawn.
      comments:
      - number: 46:5
        content: "  This is a reference to Jerusalem, but today God calls his church
          a \u201Ccity\u201D on a hill.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: When the nations are in uproar with their tottering kingdoms,God simply
        raises his voice,and the earth begins to disintegrate before him.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Here he comes!The Commander!The mighty Lord of Angel Armies is on
        our side!The God of Jacob fights for us!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: "Everyone look!Come and see the breathtaking wonders of our God.For
        he brings both ruin and revival.He\u2019s the one who makes conflicts endthroughout
        the earth,breaking and burning every weapon of war."
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: "Everyone look!Come and see the breathtaking wonders of our God.For
        he brings both ruin and revival.He\u2019s the one who makes conflicts endthroughout
        the earth,breaking and burning every weapon of war."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Surrender your anxiety. [[COMMENT(0)]]Be still and realize that I
        am God.I am God above all the nations,and I am exalted throughout the whole
        earth.
      comments:
      - number: 46:10
        content: "  Or \u201CLet go!\u201D The Septuagint reads \u201Crelax.\u201D  "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Here he stands!The Commander!The mighty Lord of Angel Armies is on
        our side!The God of Jacob fights for us!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The King over All the Earth'
      title: The King over All the Earth
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining One by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s
        clanA poetic songGo ahead and celebrate!Come on and clap your hands, everyone!Shout
        to God with the raucous sounds of joy!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord God Most High is astonishing, awesome beyond words!He\u2019s
        the formidable and powerful King over all the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He\u2019s the one who conquered the nations before usand placed them
        all under our feet."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He\u2019s marked out our inheritance ahead of time,putting us in
        the front of the line, honoring Jacob, the one he loves. [[COMMENT(0)]]Pause
        in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 47:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe pride of Jacob.\u201D The Septuagint reads \u201Cthe
          beauty of Jacob.\u201D  "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: God arises with the earsplitting shout of his people!God goes up with
        a trumpet blast!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Sing and celebrate! Sing some more, celebrate some more!Sing your
        highest song of praise to our King!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For God is the triumphant King; all the powers of the earth are his.So
        sing your celebration songs of highest praiseto the glorious Enlightened
        One!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Our God reigns over every nation.He reigns on his holy throne over
        all.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "All the nobles and princes,the loving servants of the God of Abraham,they
        all gather to worship.Every warrior\u2019s shield is now loweredas surrendered
        trophies before this King.He has taken his throne, high and lofty, exalted
        over all!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Beautiful Zion'
      title: Beautiful Zion
      number: 1
      content: "A poetic song by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s clanThere
        are so many reasons to describe God as wonderful!So many reasons to praise
        him with unlimited praise! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 48:1
        content: '  This psalm was written to commemorate the defeat of the Assyrian
          army in the days of King Hezekiah.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Zion-City is his home; he lives on his holy mountain\u2014high and
        glorious, joy-filled and favored.Zion-Mountain looms in the farthest reaches
        of the north, [[COMMENT(0)]]the city of our incomparable King!"
      comments:
      - number: 48:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe sides of the north,\u201D a metaphor to describe
          God\u2019s heavenly home. See  .    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: This is his divine abode, an impenetrable citadel,for he is known
        to dwell in the highest place.
      comments: []
    - name: '4-6: '
      title: 
      number: 4-6
      content: See how the mighty kings united to come against Zion,yet when they
        saw God manifest in front of their eyes,they were stunned.Trembling, they
        all fled away, gripped with fear. [[COMMENT(0)]]Seized with panic, they doubled
        up in frightful anguish,like a woman in the labor pains of childbirth.
      comments:
      - number: "48:4\u20136"
        content: '  This no doubt refers to the night the angel of the Lord descended
          into the ranks of the Assyrians and killed 185,000 men. See  .    '
    - name: '4-6: '
      title: 
      number: 4-6
      content: See how the mighty kings united to come against Zion,yet when they
        saw God manifest in front of their eyes,they were stunned.Trembling, they
        all fled away, gripped with fear. [[COMMENT(0)]]Seized with panic, they doubled
        up in frightful anguish,like a woman in the labor pains of childbirth.
      comments:
      - number: "48:4\u20136"
        content: '  This no doubt refers to the night the angel of the Lord descended
          into the ranks of the Assyrians and killed 185,000 men. See  .    '
    - name: '4-6: '
      title: 
      number: 4-6
      content: See how the mighty kings united to come against Zion,yet when they
        saw God manifest in front of their eyes,they were stunned.Trembling, they
        all fled away, gripped with fear. [[COMMENT(0)]]Seized with panic, they doubled
        up in frightful anguish,like a woman in the labor pains of childbirth.
      comments:
      - number: "48:4\u20136"
        content: '  This no doubt refers to the night the angel of the Lord descended
          into the ranks of the Assyrians and killed 185,000 men. See  .    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Like a hurricane blowing and breaking the invading ships, [[COMMENT(0)]]God
        blows upon them and breaks them to pieces.
      comments:
      - number: 48:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cships of Tarshish.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: We have heard about these wonders,and then we saw them with our own
        eyes.For this is the city of the Commander of Angel Armies,the city of our
        God, safe and secure forever!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Lord, as we worship you in your temple,we recall over and over your
        kindness to usand your unending love.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The fame of your name echoes throughout the entire world,accompanied
        with praises.Your right hand is full of victory.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So let the people of Zion rejoice with gladness;let the daughters
        of praise [[COMMENT(0)]] leap for joy!For God will see to it that you are
        judged fairly.
      comments:
      - number: 48:11
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe daughters of Judah.\u201D  "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: Circle Zion; count her towers.Consider her walls, climb her palaces,and
        then go and tell the coming generationof the care and compassion of our God.
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: Circle Zion; count her towers.Consider her walls, climb her palaces,and
        then go and tell the coming generationof the care and compassion of our God.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Yes, this is our God, our great God forever.He will lead us onward
        until the end,through all time, beyond death,and into eternity!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: Wisdom Better Than Wealth'
      title: Wisdom Better Than Wealth
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA poetic song by the prophetic singers
        of Korah\u2019s clanListen, one and all!Both rich and poor together, all
        over the world\u2014everyone listen to what I have to say!"
      comments: []
    - name: '1-2: Wisdom Better Than Wealth'
      title: Wisdom Better Than Wealth
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA poetic song by the prophetic singers
        of Korah\u2019s clanListen, one and all!Both rich and poor together, all
        over the world\u2014everyone listen to what I have to say!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For wisdom will come from my mouth;words of insight and understanding
        will be heardfrom the musings of my heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I will break open mysteries with my music,and my song will release
        riddles solved.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "There\u2019s no reason to fear when troubling times come,even when
        you\u2019re surrounded with problemsand persecutors who chase at your heels.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 49:5
        content: "  This phrase contains a variant form of the name Jacob, which
          means \u201Cheel grabber.\u201D    "
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: They trust in their treasures and boast in their riches,yet not one
        of them, though rich as a king,could rescue his own brother from the guilt
        of his sins.No one could give God the ransom pricefor the soul of another,
        let alone for himself.
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: They trust in their treasures and boast in their riches,yet not one
        of them, though rich as a king,could rescue his own brother from the guilt
        of his sins.No one could give God the ransom pricefor the soul of another,
        let alone for himself.
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: "A soul\u2019s redemption is too costly and preciousfor anyone to
        pay with earthly wealth.The price to pay is never enoughto purchase eternal
        life for even one, to keep them out of hell."
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: "A soul\u2019s redemption is too costly and preciousfor anyone to
        pay with earthly wealth.The price to pay is never enoughto purchase eternal
        life for even one, to keep them out of hell."
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: The brightest and best, along with the foolish and senseless,God sees
        that they all will die one day,leaving their houses and wealth to others.Even
        though they name streets and lands after themselves, [[COMMENT(0)]]hoping
        to have their memory endure beyond the grave,becoming legends in their own
        minds,their home address is now the cemetery!
      comments:
      - number: "49:10\u201311"
        content: "  Or \u201CThey read their names in the ground.\u201D    "
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: The brightest and best, along with the foolish and senseless,God sees
        that they all will die one day,leaving their houses and wealth to others.Even
        though they name streets and lands after themselves, [[COMMENT(0)]]hoping
        to have their memory endure beyond the grave,becoming legends in their own
        minds,their home address is now the cemetery!
      comments:
      - number: "49:10\u201311"
        content: "  Or \u201CThey read their names in the ground.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The honor of man is short-lived and fleeting.There\u2019s little
        difference between man and beast,for both will one day perish."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Such is the path of foolish menand those who quote everything they
        say,for they are here today and gone tomorrow!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "A shepherd called \u201CDeath\u201D herds them,leading them straight
        to hell like mindless sheep.Yet at daybreak you will find the righteous ruling
        in their place.Every trace of them will be gone forever,with all their \u201Cglory\u201D
        lost in the darkness of their doom."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But I know the loving God will redeem my soul,raising me up from the
        dark power of death,taking me as his bridal partner. [[COMMENT(0)]]Pause
        in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 49:15
        content: "  Or \u201Che will offer his hand to me in marriage.\u201D  "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So don\u2019t be disturbed when you see the richsurround you with
        the \u201Cglory\u201D of their wealth on full display."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For when they die, they will carry nothing with them,and their riches
        will not follow them beyond the grave.
      comments: []
    - name: '18-19: '
      title: 
      number: 18-19
      content: Though they have the greatest rewards of this worldand all applaud
        them for their accomplishments,they will follow those who have gone before
        themand go straight into the realm of darkness,where they will never ever
        see the light again.
      comments: []
    - name: '18-19: '
      title: 
      number: 18-19
      content: Though they have the greatest rewards of this worldand all applaud
        them for their accomplishments,they will follow those who have gone before
        themand go straight into the realm of darkness,where they will never ever
        see the light again.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So this is the way of mortal man\u2014honored for a moment, yet without
        eternal insight,like a beast that will one day perish."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Has Spoken'
      title: God Has Spoken
      number: 1
      content: "A poetic song of Asaph, the gatherer [[COMMENT(0)]]The God of gods,
        the mighty Lord himself, has spoken!He shouts out over all the people of
        the earthin every brilliant sunrise and every beautiful sunset,saying, \u201CListen
        to me!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 50
        content: "  Asaph\u2019s name means \u201Cgatherer\u201D or \u201Cfulfilled
          prophecy.\u201D Like David, Asaph was anointed with the spirit of prophecy
          and wrote twelve psalms (;  ).    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "God\u2019s glory-light shines out of the Zion-realm [[COMMENT(0)]]with
        the radiance of perfect beauty."
      comments:
      - number: 50:2
        content: "  The Aramaic text can be translated \u201COut of Zion God has
          shown a glorious crown.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: With the rumble of thunder he approaches;he will not be silent, for
        he comes with an earsplitting sound!All around him are furious flames of
        fire,and preceding him is the dazzling blaze of his glory.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Here he comes to judge his people!He summons his court with heaven
        and earth as his jury, saying,
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGather all my devoted lovers,my godly ones whose hearts are
        one with me\u2014those who have entered into my holy covenantby sacrifices
        upon the altar.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the heavens declare his justice:\u201CGod himself will be their
        judge,and he will judge them with righteousness!\u201DPause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O&nbsp;my people! Listen well, for I am your
        God!I am bringing you to trial, and here are my charges. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 50:7
        content: "  This summons to judgment is not against the heathen nations but
          against God\u2019s people. See  .  "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: I do not rebuke you for your sacrifices,which you continually bring
        to my altar.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Do I need your young bulls or goats from your fieldsas if I were hungry?
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: Every animal of field and forest belongs to me, the Creator.I know
        every movement of the birds in the sky,and every animal of the field is in
        my thoughts.The entire world and everything it contains is mine.
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: Every animal of field and forest belongs to me, the Creator.I know
        every movement of the birds in the sky,and every animal of the field is in
        my thoughts.The entire world and everything it contains is mine.
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: If I were hungry, do you think I would tell you?For all that I have
        created, the fullness of the earth, is mine.Am I fed by your sacrifices?
        Of course not!
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: If I were hungry, do you think I would tell you?For all that I have
        created, the fullness of the earth, is mine.Am I fed by your sacrifices?
        Of course not!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Why don\u2019t you bring me the sacrifices I desire?Bring me your
        true and sincere thanks,and show your gratitude by keeping your promises
        to me,the Most High."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Honor me by trusting in me in your day of trouble.Cry aloud to me,
        and I will be there to rescue you.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And now I speak to the wicked. Listen to what I have to say to you!What
        right do you have to presume to speak for meand claim my covenant promises
        as yours?
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For you have hated my instruction and disregarded my words,throwing
        them away as worthless!
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: You forget to condemn the thief or adulterer.You are their friend,
        running alongside them into darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: The sins of your mouth multiply evil.You have a lifestyle of lies;you
        are devoted to deceit as you speak against others,even slandering those of
        your own household!
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: The sins of your mouth multiply evil.You have a lifestyle of lies;you
        are devoted to deceit as you speak against others,even slandering those of
        your own household!
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: All this you have done and I kept silent,so you thought that I was
        just like you, sanctioning evil.But now I will bring you to my courtroomand
        spell out clearly my charges before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: This is your last chance, my final warning. Your time is up!Turn away
        from all this evil, or the next time you hear from mewill be when I am coming
        to pass judgment upon you.I will snatch you away, and no one will be thereto
        help you escape my judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The life that pleases me is a life lived in the gratitude of grace,always
        choosing to walk with me in what is right.This is the sacrifice I desire
        from you.If you do this, more of my salvation will unfold for you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1-2: Pardon and PurityDavid\u2019s Confession"
      title: "Pardon and PurityDavid\u2019s Confession"
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA prayer of confession when the prophet
        Nathan exposed King David\u2019s adultery with Bathsheba [[COMMENT(0)]]God,
        give me mercy from your fountain of forgiveness!I know your abundant love
        is enough to wash away my guilt.Because your compassion is so great,take
        away this shameful guilt of sin.Forgive the full extent of my rebellious
        ways,and erase this deep stain on my conscience. [[COMMENT(1)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 51
        content: '  This psalm is based on the incident that is recorded in  . This
          is a psalm of confession that has been sung for ages. Imagine composing
          a song about your failure and making it public for all time. David was
          not so much concerned about what the people thought but about what God
          thought. He wanted to be clean before God.    '
      - number: "51:1\u20132"
        content: "  Or \u201Cwash me.\u201D David used the Hebrew word  , which was
          used for washing clothes, not for bathing. David was asking for his royal
          robes to be cleansed from the stains of his actions and publicly restored.    "
