      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Lord, I have been a sinner from birth,from the moment my mother conceived
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: "6: David\u2019s Cleansing"
      title: "David\u2019s Cleansing"
      number: 6
      content: I know that you delight to set your truth deep in my spirit. [[COMMENT(0)]]So
        come into the hidden places of my heartand teach me wisdom.
      comments:
      - number: 51:6
        content: "  The Hebrew word  , although difficult to translate, can mean
          \u201Csomething that is covered over, hidden, or concealed.\u201D This
          could be paraphrased as \u201Cyou desire light in my darkness\u201D or
          \u201Cyou want truth to expose my secrets.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Purify my conscience! Make this leper clean again! [[COMMENT(0)]]Wash
        me in your love until I am pure in heart. '
      comments:
      - number: 51:7
        content: "  The Hebrew text contains the word  . This was a bushy plant used
          for sprinkling blood on a healed leper to ceremonially cleanse him for
          the worship of God. See  ;  .      Or \u201CWash me with the snow from
          above so I can be whitened.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Satisfy me in your sweetness, and my song of joy will return.The places
        you have crushed within mewill rejoice in your healing touch. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 51:8
        content: "  In this beautiful verse, the broken places (\u201Cplaces you
          have crushed\u201D) are literally \u201Cbroken bones.\u201D Our bones speak
          allegorically of our inner being, our emotional strength.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Hide my sins from your face; [[COMMENT(0)]]erase all my guilt by your
        saving grace.
      comments:
      - number: 51:9
        content: '  David was ashamed not just of what others would think but also
          that he had been seen by God. A truly remorseful person has no thought
          for reputation but only for righteousness.    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Keep creating in me a clean heart. [[COMMENT(0)]]Fill me with pure
        thoughts and holy desires, ready to please you. '
      comments:
      - number: 51:10
        content: "  The word used for \u201Ccreate\u201D takes us back to  , and
          it means to create from nothing. David knew he had no goodness without
          God placing it within him. David wanted a new creation heart, not just
          the old one changed.      Or \u201CRenew a reliable spirit in my inner
          being.\u201D    "
    - name: "11: David\u2019s Consecration"
      title: "David\u2019s Consecration"
      number: 11
      content: May you never reject me!May you never take from me your sacred Spirit!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Let my passion for life be restored,tasting joy [[COMMENT(0)]] in
        every breakthrough you bring to me.Hold me close to you with a willing spiritthat
        obeys whatever you say.
      comments:
      - number: 51:12
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cjoy\u201D comes from two Hebrew roots:
          one means \u201Cbright\u201D and the other means \u201Clily [whiteness].\u201D
          David wanted to taste a joy that was bright, pure, and as beautiful as
          a lily.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Then I can show other guilty oneshow loving and merciful you are.They
        will find their way back home to you,knowing that you will forgive them.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: O&nbsp;God, my saving God,deliver me fully from every sin,even the
        sin that brought bloodguilt. [[COMMENT(0)]]Then my heart will once again
        be thrilled to singthe passionate songs of joy and deliverance!
      comments:
      - number: 51:14
        content: "  Or simply \u201Cblood.\u201D David could have been asking God
          to spare his life from death (that is, deliverance from death because of
          his sin).    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Lord God, unlock my heart, unlock my lips,and I will overcome with
        my joyous praise!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For the source of your pleasure is not in my performanceor the sacrifices
        I might offer to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The fountain of your pleasure is foundin the sacrifice of my shattered
        heart before you.You will not despise my tendernessas I bow down humbly at
        your feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Because you favor Zion, do what is good for her.Be the protecting
        wall around Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And when we are fully restored,you will rejoice and take delightin
        every offering of our livesas we bring our sacrifices of righteousness before
        you in love! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 51:19
        content: "  Or \u201Cthen they will offer up bulls on your altar.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fate of Cynics'
      title: The Fate of Cynics
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA song of instruction by King David composed
        when Doeg the Edomite betrayed David to Saul, saying, \u201CDavid has come
        to the house of Ahimilech!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]You call yourself a mighty
        man, a big shot?Why do you boast in the evil you have done?Yet God\u2019s
        loyal love will protect me and carry the day!"
      comments:
      - number: 52
        content: "  For this episode in David\u2019s life, see  ;  . The Edomites,
          although close relatives to the Hebrews, were bitter enemies to God\u2019s
          people. In spite of Doeg\u2019s lineage, he became a high-ranking official
          in Saul\u2019s kingdom. Herod the Great, who slaughtered the babies of
          Bethlehem, was an Edomite. At the time David wrote this psalm, Saul had
          already attempted to kill him sixteen times. Ahimilech, the caretaker of
          the sword of Goliath, was a descendant of Eli.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Listen, O&nbsp;deceiver, trickster of others:Your words are wicked,
        harming and hurting all who hear them.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You love evil and hate what is good and right.You would rather lie
        than tell the truth.Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: You love to distort, devour, and deceive,using your sly tongue to
        spin the truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But the Almighty will strike you down forever!He will pull you up
        by your rootsand drag you away to the darkness of death.Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The godly will see all this and will be awestruck.Then they will laugh
        at the wicked, saying,
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CSee what happens to those great in their own eyeswho don\u2019t
        trust in the Most High to save them!Look how they trusted only in their wealthand
        made their living from wickedness.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 52:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cand [was] strong in [his] destruction.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But I am like a flourishing olive tree, anointed in the house of God.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]I trust in the unending love of God;his passion toward me is
        forever and ever.
      comments:
      - number: 52:8
        content: '  The olive tree was the source of the sacred anointing oil.    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Because it is finished, [[COMMENT(0)]]I will praise you forever and
        give you thanks.Before all your godly lovers I will proclaim your beautiful
        name!
      comments:
      - number: 52:9
        content: "  Or \u201CYou have acted [finished it].\u201D The words \u201CIt
          is finished\u201D were the last words of Jesus on the cross.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wickedness of the World'
      title: The Wickedness of the World
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA contemplative song of instruction To
        the tune of \u201CThe Dancings of Mourning\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]Only the withering
        soul [[COMMENT(1)]] would say to himself,\u201CThere\u2019s no God for me!\u201DAnyone
        who thinks like that is corrupt and callous;depraved and detestable, they
        are devoid of what is good."
      comments:
      - number: 53
        content: "  Or \u201CThe Dance of Mourning.\u201D This could have been a
          footnote to    instead of an inscription for  . If so, read    and imagine
          the dancing that broke loose when David and his mighty men knew that Doeg
          had been judged by God for his murderous betrayal.    "
      - number: 53:1
        content: "  The word often translated as \u201Cfool\u201D comes from a Hebrew
          word meaning \u201Cwithering.\u201D If we make no room for God, we have
          withered hearts (or souls), our moral sense of righteousness is put to
          sleep, and the noble aspirations of the heart shrivel up and die.    clearly
          speaks of the downfall of those who oppose Israel.    and    are very similar
          psalms.    deals with God\u2019s verdict, while    speaks of God\u2019s
          vengeance. If God says it once, it is to believed. If he says it twice,
          it demands our utmost attention!    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord looks down in love, bending over heaven\u2019s balcony.God
        looks over all of Adam\u2019s sons and daughters,looking to see if there
        are any who are wise with insight\u2014any who search for him, wanting to
        please him."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But no, all have wandered astray, walking stubbornly toward evil.Not
        one is good; he can\u2019t even find one!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Look how they live in luxury while exploiting my people.Won\u2019t
        these workers of wickedness ever learn!They never even think of praying to
        God."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Soon, unheard-of terror will seize them while in their sins.God himself
        will one day scatter the bonesof those who rose up against you. [[COMMENT(0)]]Doomed
        and rejected, they will be put to shame,for God has despised them.
      comments:
      - number: 53:5
        content: '  This could refer to the scattering of the armies of Sennacherib
          in the days of Hezekiah. See  .    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Oh, I wish our time of rescue were already here.Oh, that God would
        come forth now [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014arising from the midst of his Zion-peopleto
        save and restore his very own.When God fully restores his people,Jacob will
        rejoice, and Israel will be filled with gladness!"
      comments:
      - number: 53:6
        content: '  This is considered to be an ecphonesis, a rhetorical literary
          device that amplifies the emotion of the text. It is equivalent to an emotional
          outburst. Clearly, this is a passionate psalm.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Defend Me'
      title: Defend Me
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneDavid\u2019s contemplative song of instructionA
        song of derision [[COMMENT(0)]] when the Ziphites betrayed David to Saul,
        saying, \u201CDavid is hiding among us; come and get him!\u201DGod, deliver
        me by your mighty name!Come with your glorious power and save me!"
      comments:
      - number: 54
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here and translated in some versions as
          \u201Cstringed instrument\u201D can also be rendered \u201Ca song of mocking.\u201D
          This is a psalm for anyone who feels betrayed, rejected, and stuck in a
          difficult situation with no one at his or her side.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Listen to my prayer; turn your ears to my cry!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: These violent men have risen up against me;heartless, ruthless men
        [[COMMENT(0)]] who care nothing about Godseek to take my life.Pause in his
        presence
      comments:
      - number: 54:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cforeigners.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But the Lord God has become my divine helper.He leans into my heart
        and lays his hands upon [[COMMENT(0)]] me!
      comments:
      - number: 54:4
        content: "  The word used here can be translated \u201Cuphold\u201D or \u201Csustain.\u201D
          It comes from a root word that means \u201Cto lean upon\u201D or \u201Cto
          lay hands upon.\u201D This translation includes both concepts in this verse.  "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: God will see to it that those who sow evil will reap evil.So Lord,
        in your great faithfulness, destroy them once and for all!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Lord, I will offer myself freely, and everything I am I give to you.I
        will worship and praise your name, O&nbsp;Lord,for it is precious to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Through you I\u2019m saved\u2014rescued from every trouble.I\u2019ve
        seen with my eyes the defeat of my enemies.I\u2019ve triumphed over them
        all!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Betrayed'
      title: Betrayed
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s song of derision for
        instructionGod, listen to my prayer!Don\u2019t hide your heart from me when
        I cry out to you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Come close to me and give me your answer.Here I am, moaning and restless.I\u2019m
        preoccupied with the threats of my enemiesand crushed by the pressure of
        their opposition.They surround me with trouble and terror.In their fury they
        rise up against me in an angry uproar."
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Come close to me and give me your answer.Here I am, moaning and restless.I\u2019m
        preoccupied with the threats of my enemiesand crushed by the pressure of
        their opposition.They surround me with trouble and terror.In their fury they
        rise up against me in an angry uproar."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: My heart is trembling inside my chestas the terror of death seizes
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Fear and dread overwhelm me. I shudder before the horror I face.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I say to myself, \u201CIf only I could fly away from all of this!If
        only I could run away to the place of rest and peace."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I would run far away where no one could find me,escaping to a wilderness
        retreat.\u201DPause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: I will hurry off to hide in the higher place,into my shelter, safe
        from this raging storm and tempest.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: God, confuse them until they quarrel with themselves.Destroy them
        with their own violent strife and slander.They have divided the city with
        their discord.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Though they patrol the walls night and day against invaders,the real
        danger is within the city\u2014the misery and strife in the hearts of its
        people."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Murder is in their midst.Wherever you turn, you find trouble and ruin.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It wasn\u2019t an enemy who taunted me.If it was my enemy, filled
        with pride and hatred,then I could have endured it. I would have just run
        away."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But it was you, my intimate friend\u2014one like a brother to me.It
        was you, my adviser, [[COMMENT(0)]] the companionI walked with and worked
        with!"
      comments:
      - number: 55:13
        content: "  The Greek word in the Septuagint can be translated as \u201Ca
          seer [prophet].\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "We once had sweet fellowship with each other.We worshiped in unity
        as one,celebrating together with God\u2019s people. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 55:14
        content: '  David was speaking of Ahithophel, who had once been his friend
          and adviser, only to betray him. This is foreshadowing of what would happen
          between Jesus and Judas.  '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Now desolation and darkness has come upon you.May you and all those
        like you descend into the pit of destruction!Since evil has been your home,
        may evil now bury you alive!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But as for me, I will call upon the Lord to save me, and I know he
        will!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Every evening I will explain my need to him.Every morning I will move
        my soul toward him.Every waking hour I will worship only him,and he will
        hear and respond to my cry.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Though many wish to fight and the tide of battle turns against me,by
        your power I will be safe and secure;peace will be my portion.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "God himself will hear me!God-Enthroned through everlasting ages,the
        God of unchanging faithfulness\u2014he will put them in their place,all those
        who refuse to love and revere him!Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: I was betrayed by my friend, though I lived in peace with him.While
        he was stretching out his hand of friendship,he was secretly breaking every
        promise he had ever made to me!
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "His words were smooth and charming.Yet his heart was disloyal and
        full of hatred\u2014his words soft as silk while all the time scheming my
        demise."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So here\u2019s what I\u2019ve learned through it all:Leave all your
        cares and anxieties at the feet of the Lord,and measureless grace will strengthen
        you."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He will watch over his devoted lovers,never letting them slip or
        be overthrown.He will send all my enemies to the pit of destruction.Murderers,
        liars, and betrayers will face an untimely death.My life\u2019s hope and
        trust is in you, and you\u2019ll never fail to rescue me!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Trusting in God'
      title: Trusting in God
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s golden song of instruction
        composed when the Philistines captured him in Gath To the tune of \u201CThe
        Oppression of the Princes to Come\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]Lord, show me your
        kindness and mercy,for these men oppose and oppress me all day long."
      comments:
      - number: 56
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe distant dove of silence.\u201D David was no more
          than twenty-two years old when he composed this psalm.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Not a day goes by without somebody harassing me.So many in their pride
        trample me under their feet. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 56:2
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CThey war with me in the high places.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But in the day that I\u2019m afraid, I lay all my fears before youand
        trust in you with all my heart."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: What harm could a man bring to me?With God on my side, I will not
        be afraid of what comes.The roaring praises of God fill my heartas I trust
        his promises.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Day after day cruel critics distort my words;constantly they plot
        my collapse.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They lurk in the dark, waiting, spying on my movements in secretto
        take me by surprise, ready to take my life.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They don\u2019t deserve to get away with this!Look at their wickedness,
        their injustice, Lord.In your fierce anger cast them down to defeat."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You\u2019ve kept track of all my wandering and my weeping.You\u2019ve
        stored my many tears in your bottle\u2014not one will be lost.For they are
        all recorded in your book of remembrance. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 56:8
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The very moment I call to you for a father\u2019s helpthe tide of
        battle turns and my enemies flee.This one thing I know: God is on my side!"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I trust in the Lord. And I praise him!I trust in the Word of God.
        And I praise him!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: What harm could man do to me?With God on my side, I will not be afraid
        of what comes.My heart overflows with praise to God and for his promises.I
        will always trust in him.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So I\u2019m thanking you with all my heart,with gratitude for all
        you\u2019ve done.I will do everything I\u2019ve promised you, Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For you have saved my soul from deathand my feet from stumblingso
        that I can walk before the Lordbathed in his life-giving light. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 56:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cin his fields of life.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Triumphant Faith'
      title: Triumphant Faith
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s golden song of instruction
        composed when he hid from Saul in a cave [[COMMENT(0)]]To the tune of \u201CDo
        Not Destroy\u201DPlease, God, show me mercy!Open your grace-fountain for
        me,for you are my soul\u2019s true shelter.I will hide beneath the shadow
        of your embrace,under the wings of your cherubim,until this terrible trouble
        is past."
      comments:
      - number: 57
        content: '  This incident is recorded in  .    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I will cry out to you, the God of the highest heaven,the mighty God,
        who performs all these wonders for me.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "From heaven he will send a father\u2019s help to save me.He will
        trample down those who trample me.Pause in his presenceHe will always show
        me loveby his gracious and constant care."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I am surrounded by these fierce and brutal men.They are like lions
        just wanting to tear me to shreds.Why must I continue to live among these
        seething terrorists,breathing out their angry threats and insults against
        me?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Lord God, be exalted as you soar throughout the heavens.May your shining
        glory be seen in the skies!Let it be seen high above over all the earth!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For they have set a trap for me. [[COMMENT(0)]]Frantic fear has me
        overwhelmed.But look! The very trap they set for mehas sprung shut upon themselves
        instead of me!Pause in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 57:6
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CThey have dug a cesspool in front
          of me.\u201D  "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: My heart, O&nbsp;God, is quiet and confident.Now I can sing with passion
        your wonderful praises!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Awake, O&nbsp;my soul, with the music of his splendor-song!Arise,
        my soul, and sing his praises!My worship will awaken the dawn,greeting the
        daybreak with my songs of praise!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Wherever I go, I will thank you, my God.Among all the nations they
        will hear my praise songs to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Your love is so extravagant it reaches to the heavens;your faithfulness
        so astonishing it stretches to the sky!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Lord God, be exalted as you soar throughout the heavens.May your shining
        glory be shown in the skies!Let it be seen high above all the earth!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: Judge of the Judges'
      title: Judge of the Judges
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s golden song of instructionTo
        the tune of \u201CDo Not Destroy\u201DGod\u2019s justice? You high and mighty
        politiciansknow nothing about it!Which one of you has walked in justice toward
        others?Which one of you has treated everyone right and fair?Not one! You
        only give \u201Cjustice\u201D in exchange for a bribe.For the right price
        you let others get away with murder."
      comments: []
    - name: '1-2: Judge of the Judges'
      title: Judge of the Judges
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s golden song of instructionTo
        the tune of \u201CDo Not Destroy\u201DGod\u2019s justice? You high and mighty
        politiciansknow nothing about it!Which one of you has walked in justice toward
        others?Which one of you has treated everyone right and fair?Not one! You
        only give \u201Cjustice\u201D in exchange for a bribe.For the right price
        you let others get away with murder."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "Wicked wanderers even from the womb\u2014that\u2019s who you are!You
        lie with your words, and your teaching is poison. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "58:3\u20134"
        content: "  The Hebrew reads \u201Cvenom of a serpent,\u201D which is a clear
          metaphor for wrong teaching.    "
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "Wicked wanderers even from the womb\u2014that\u2019s who you are!You
        lie with your words, and your teaching is poison. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "58:3\u20134"
        content: "  The Hebrew reads \u201Cvenom of a serpent,\u201D which is a clear
          metaphor for wrong teaching.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Like cobras closing their ears to the most expert of the charmers,you
        strike out against all who are near.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: O&nbsp;God, break their fangs;shatter the teeth of these ravenous
        lions!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Let them disappear like water falling on thirsty ground.Let all their
        weapons be useless.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Let them be like snails dissolving into the slime.Let them be cut
        off, never seeing the light of day!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "God will sweep them away so fastthat they\u2019ll never know what
        hit them. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 58:9
        content: '  The Hebrew here is recognized by nearly every scholar to be one
          of the most difficult verses in the Psalms to translate.  '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The godly will celebrate in the triumph of good over evil,and the
        lovers of God will tramplethe wickedness of the wicked under their feet!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then everyone will say, \u201CThere is a God who judges the judges\u201Dand
        \u201CThere is a great reward in loving God!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Protect Me'
      title: Protect Me
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s song of instruction
        composed when Saul set an ambush for him at his home [[COMMENT(0)]]To the
        tune of \u201CDo Not Destroy\u201DMy God, protect me!Keep me safe from all
        my enemies, for they\u2019re coming to kill me.Put me in a high place out
        of their reach\u2014a place so high that these assassins will never find
        me."
      comments:
      - number: 59
        content: '  This incident is recorded in  .  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Save me from these murdering men, these bloodthirsty killers.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "See how they set an ambush for my life.They\u2019re fierce men ready
        to launch their attack against me.O&nbsp;Lord, I\u2019m innocent; protect
        me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I\u2019ve done nothing to deserve this,yet they are already plotting
        together to kill me.Arise, Lord, see what they\u2019re scheming, and come
        and meet with me."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Awaken, O&nbsp;God of Israel!Commander of Angel Armies,arise to punish
        these treacherous people who oppose you!Don\u2019t go soft on these hard-core
        killers!Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "After dark they came to spy, sneaking around the city,snarling, prowling
        like a pack of stray dogs in the night\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "boiling over with rage, shouting out their curses,convinced that
        they\u2019ll never get caught."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But you, Lord, break out laughing at their plans,amused by their arrogance,
        scoffing at their sinful ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: My strength is found when I wait upon you.Watch over me, God, for
        you are my mountain fortress;you set me on high!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The God of passionate love will meet with me.My God will empower me
        to rise in triumph over my foes.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Don\u2019t kill them; stagger them all with a vivid display of powerand
        scatter them with your armies of angels,O&nbsp;mighty God, our protector!Use
        your awesome power to make them wanderers and vagabondsand then bring them
        down."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: They are nothing but proud, cursing liars.They sin in every word they
        speak, boasting in their blasphemies!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: May your wrath be kindled to destroy them; finish them off!Make an
        end of them and their deeds until they are no more!Let them all know and
        learnthat God is the ruler over Jacob,the God-King over all the earth!Pause
        in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Here they come again\u2014prowling, growling like a pack of stray
        dogs in the city."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Drifting, devouring, and coming in for the kill,they refuse to sleep
        until they\u2019ve eaten their fill."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But as for me, your strength shall be my song of joy.At each and every
        sunrise, my lyrics of your love will fill the air!For you have been my glory-fortress,a
        stronghold in my day of distress.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: O&nbsp;my strength, I sing with joy your praises.O&nbsp;my stronghold,
        I sing with joy your song!O&nbsp;my Savior, I sing with joy the lyrics of
        your faithful love for me!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Has God Forgotten Us?'
      title: Has God Forgotten Us?
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s poem for instruction
        [[COMMENT(0)]] composed when he fought against the Syrians with the outcome
        still uncertain and Joab turned back to kill twelve thousand descendants
        of Esau in the Valley of SaltTo the tune of \u201CLily of the Covenant\u201DGod,
        it seems like you walked off and left us!Why have you turned against us?You
        have been angry with us.O&nbsp;Lord, we plead, come back and help us as a
        father."
      comments:
      - number: 60
        content: "  Or \u201CAccording to Shushan Eduth. A Mikhtam of David, to teach.\u201D
          There is no scholarly consensus about what    means. Some have concluded
          it refers to a specific tune or possibly an instrument, but it remains
          a mystery.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The earth quivers and quakes before you,splitting open and breaking
        apart.Now come and heal it, for it is shaken to its depths.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You have taught us hard lessonsand made us drink the wine of bewilderment.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: You have given miraculous signs to those who love you.As we follow
        you, we fly the flag of truth,and all who love the truth will rally to it.Pause
        in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Come to your beloved ones and gently draw us out.For Lord, you save
        those whom you love.Come with your might and strength!
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "Then I heard the Lord speak in his holy splendor.From his sanctuary
        I heard the Lord promise:\u201CIn my triumph I will be the one to measure
        outthe portion of my inheritance to my people,and I will secure the land
        as I promised you.Shechem, Succoth, Gilead, Manasseh,they are all still mine!\u201D
        he says.\u201CJudah will continue to produce kings and lawgivers,and Ephraim
        will produce great warriors."
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "Then I heard the Lord speak in his holy splendor.From his sanctuary
        I heard the Lord promise:\u201CIn my triumph I will be the one to measure
        outthe portion of my inheritance to my people,and I will secure the land
        as I promised you.Shechem, Succoth, Gilead, Manasseh,they are all still mine!\u201D
        he says.\u201CJudah will continue to produce kings and lawgivers,and Ephraim
        will produce great warriors."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Moab will become my lowly servant.Edom will likewise serve my purposes.I
        will lift up a shout of victory over the land of Philistia!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But who will bring my triumph into the strong city?Who will lead
        me into Edom\u2019s [[COMMENT(0)]] fortresses?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 60:9
        content: '  Edom is a variant form of the name Adam.  '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Have you really rejected us, refusing to fight our battles?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Give us a father\u2019s help when we face our enemies.For to trust
        in any man is an empty hope."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "With God\u2019s help we will fight like heroes,and he will trample
        down our every foe!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prayer for Protection'
      title: Prayer for Protection
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneA song for the guitar by King DavidO&nbsp;God,
        hear my prayer. Listen to my heart\u2019s cry."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For no matter where I am, even when I\u2019m far from home,I will
        cry out to you for a father\u2019s help.When I\u2019m feeble and overwhelmed
        by life,guide me into your glory, where I am safe and sheltered."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Lord, you are a paradise of protection to me.You lift me high above
        the fray.None of my foes can touch mewhen I\u2019m held firmly in your wraparound
        presence!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Keep me in this glory.Let me live continually under your splendor-shadow,hiding
        my life in you forever.Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You have heard my sweet resolutionsto love and serve you, for I am
        your beloved.And you have given me an inheritance of rich treasures,which
        you give to all your devoted lovers.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: You treat me like a king, giving me a full and abundant life,years
        and years of reigning, [[COMMENT(0)]]like many generations rolled into one.
      comments:
      - number: 61:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cadd to the days of the king.\u201D  "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: I will live enthroned with you forever!Guard me, God, with your unending,
        unfailing love.Let me live my days walking in grace and truth before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And my praises will fill the heavens forever,fulfilling my vow to
        make every day a love-gift to you!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Unshakable Faith'
      title: Unshakable Faith
      number: 1
      content: To the Pure and Shining OneBy David, for the one who praises [[COMMENT(0)]]I
        stand silently to listen for the one I love,waiting as long as it takes for
        the Lord to rescue me.For God alone has become my Savior.
      comments:
      - number: 62
        content: "  The inscription includes the name Jeduthun, which means \u201Cone
          who praises.\u201D  "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He alone is my safe place;his wraparound presence always protects
        me.For he is my champion defender;there\u2019s no risk of failure with God.So
        why would I let worry paralyze me,even when troubles multiply around me?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But look at these who want me dead,shouting their vicious threats
        at me!The moment they discover my weakness,they all begin plotting to take
        me down.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Liars, hypocrites, with nothing good to say\u2014all their energies
        are spenton moving me from this exalted place.Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I am standing in absolute stillness, silent before the one I love,waiting
        as long as it takes for him to rescue me.Only God is my Savior, and he will
        not fail me.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For he alone is my safe place.His wraparound presence always protects
        meas my champion defender.There\u2019s no risk of failure with God!So why
        would I let worry paralyze me,even when troubles multiply around me?"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "God\u2019s glory is all around me!His wraparound presence is all
        I need,for the Lord is my Savior, my hero, and my life-giving strength."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Trust only in God every moment!Tell him all your troubles and pour
        out your heart-longings to him.Believe me when I tell you\u2014he will help
        you!Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Before God all the people of the earth, high or low,are like smoke
        that disappears,like a vapor that quickly vanishes away.Compared to God they\u2019re
        nothing but vanity, nothing at all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The wealth of the world is nothing to God.So if your wealth increases,
        don\u2019t be boastful orput your trust in your money.And don\u2019t you
        think for a moment thatyou can get away with stealing by overcharging othersjust
        to get more for yourself!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "God said to me once and for all,\u201CAll the strength and power
        you need flows from me!\u201DAnd again I heard it clearly said,"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAll the love you need is found in me!\u201DAnd it\u2019s true
        that you repay people for what they do."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Thirsting for God'
      title: Thirsting for God
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s song when he was exiled
        in the Judean wildernessO&nbsp;God of my life, I\u2019m lovesick for you
        in this weary wilderness.I thirst with the deepest longings to love you more,with
        cravings in my heart that can\u2019t be described.Such yearning grips my
        soul for you, my God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I\u2019m energized every time I enteryour heavenly sanctuary to seek
        more of your powerand drink in more of your glory."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For your tender mercies mean more to me than life itself.How I love
        and praise you, God!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Daily I will worship you passionately and with all my heart.My arms
        will wave to you like banners of praise.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I overflow with praise when I come before you,for the anointing of
        your presence satisfies me like nothing else.You are such a rich banquet
        of pleasure to my soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: I lie awake each night thinking of youand reflecting on how you help
        me like a father.I sing through the night under your splendor-shadow,offering
        up to you my songs of delight and joy!
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: I lie awake each night thinking of youand reflecting on how you help
        me like a father.I sing through the night under your splendor-shadow,offering
        up to you my songs of delight and joy!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: With passion I pursue and cling to you.Because I feel your grip on
        my life,I keep my soul close to your heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Those who plot to destroy me shall descend into the darkness of hell.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: They will be consumed by their own eviland become nothing more than
        dust under our feet. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 63:10
        content: "  Or \u201Cfood for foxes.\u201D  "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: These liars will be silenced forever!But with the anointing of a king
        I will dance and rejoicealong with all his devoted lovers who trust in him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: Victory over Evildoers'
      title: Victory over Evildoers
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s songLord, can\u2019t
        you hear my cry, my bitter complaint?Keep me safe from this band of criminals
        andfrom the conspiracy of these wicked men.They gather in their secret counsel
        to destroy me."
      comments: []
    - name: '1-2: Victory over Evildoers'
      title: Victory over Evildoers
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s songLord, can\u2019t
        you hear my cry, my bitter complaint?Keep me safe from this band of criminals
        andfrom the conspiracy of these wicked men.They gather in their secret counsel
        to destroy me."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "Can\u2019t you hear their slander, their lies?Their words are like
        poison-tipped arrowsshot from the shadows.They are unafraid and have no fear
        of consequences."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "Can\u2019t you hear their slander, their lies?Their words are like
        poison-tipped arrowsshot from the shadows.They are unafraid and have no fear
        of consequences."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They persist with their evil plansand plot together to hide their
        traps.They boast, \u201CNo one can see us or stop us!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They search out opportunities to pervert justiceas they plan the
        \u201Cperfect crime.\u201DHow unsearchable is their endless evil!They try
        desperately to hide the deep darkness of their hearts. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 64:6
        content: '  Scholars are unanimous in agreement that the meaning of the Hebrew
          text of this verse is uncertain.  '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But all the while God has his own fire-tipped arrows!Suddenly, without
        warning,they will be pierced and struck down.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Staggering backward, they will be destroyedby the very ones they spoke
        against.All who see this will view them with scorn.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then all will stand awestruck over what God has done,seeing how he
        vindicated the victims of these crimes.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The lovers of God will be glad, rejoicing in the Lord.They will be
        found in his glorious wraparound presence,singing songs of praise to God!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: What a Savior'
      title: What a Savior
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s poetic songO&nbsp;God
        in Zion, to you even silence is praise!You who answers prayer, [[COMMENT(0)]]all
        of humanity comes before you with their requests."
      comments:
      - number: "65:1\u20132"
        content: "  The root of the Hebrew word for \u201Cprayer\u201D is  , which
          also means \u201Ctent peg.\u201D Jewish tradition views    prayer (intercession)
          as a means of attaching yourself to God. In the same way a tent peg establishes
          a tent and fastens it securely, so    prayer fastens the soul to God.   
          prayer is when you grab hold of God and attach yourself to him in surrender
          and humility. Hold on to God like a tent peg holds on to a tent.    "
    - name: '1-2: What a Savior'
      title: What a Savior
      number: 1-2
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s poetic songO&nbsp;God
        in Zion, to you even silence is praise!You who answers prayer, [[COMMENT(0)]]all
        of humanity comes before you with their requests."
      comments:
      - number: "65:1\u20132"
        content: "  The root of the Hebrew word for \u201Cprayer\u201D is  , which
          also means \u201Ctent peg.\u201D Jewish tradition views    prayer (intercession)
          as a means of attaching yourself to God. In the same way a tent peg establishes
          a tent and fastens it securely, so    prayer fastens the soul to God.   
          prayer is when you grab hold of God and attach yourself to him in surrender
          and humility. Hold on to God like a tent peg holds on to a tent.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Though we are overcome by our many sins,your sacrifice covers over
        them all.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: How blessed is the one you chooseto live near you in your courts.The
        beauty of your house, your holy temple, satisfies us.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You answer our prayers with amazing wondersand with awe-inspiring
        displays of power.You are the righteous God who helps us like a father.Everyone
        everywhere looks to you,for you are the confidence of all the earth,even
        to the farthest islands of the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: What jaw-dropping, astounding power is yours!You are the mountain
        maker who sets them all in place.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: You muzzle the roar of the mighty seasand the rage of mobs with their
        noisy riots.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: O&nbsp;God, to the farthest corners of the planetpeople will stand
        in awe,startled and stunned by your signs and wonders.Sunrise brilliance
        and sunset beautyboth take turns singing their songs of joy to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Your visitations of glory bless the earth; [[COMMENT(0)]]the rivers
        of God overflow and enrich it.You paint the wheat fields golden as you provide
        rich harvests.
      comments:
      - number: 65:9
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CYou\u2019ve made the earth drunk with
          your visitations.\u201D  "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Every field is watered with the abundance of rain\u2014showers soaking
        the earth and softening its clods,causing seeds to sprout throughout the
        land."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: You crown the earth with the fruits of your goodness.Wherever you
        go, the tracks of your chariot wheels drip with oil.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Luxuriant green pastures boast of your bountyas you make every hillside
        blossom with joy.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The grazing meadows are covered with flocks,and the fertile valleys
        are clothed with grain,each one dancing and shouting for joy, creation\u2019s
        celebration!They\u2019re all singing their songs of praise to you!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Thank You, Lord'
      title: Thank You, Lord
      number: 1
      content: For the Pure and Shining OneA song of awakening [[COMMENT(0)]]Everyone
        everywhere, lift up your joyful shout to God!
      comments:
      - number: 66
        content: '  As translated from the inscription found in the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Sing your songs tuned to his glory!Tell the world how wonderful he
        is.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For he\u2019s the awe-inspiring God, great and glorious in power!We\u2019ve
        never seen anything like him!Mighty in miracles, you cause your enemies to
        tremble.No wonder they all surrender and bow before you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: All the earth will bow down to worship;all the earth will sing your
        glories forever!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Everyone will say, \u201CCome and see the incredible things God has
        done;it will take your breath away!He multiplies miracles for his people!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 66:5
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CHis works are more to be feared than
          the decisions of men.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He made a highway going right through the Red Seaas the Hebrews passed
        through on dry ground,exploding with joyous excitement over the miracles
        of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In his great and mighty power he rules forever,watching over every
        movement of every nation.So beware, rebel lands; he knows how to humble you!Pause
        in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Praise God, all you peoples.Praise him everywhere and let everyone
        know you love him!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "There\u2019s no doubt about it: God holds our lives safely in his
        hands.He\u2019s the one who keeps us faithfully following him."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "O&nbsp;Lord, we have passed through your fire;like precious metal
        made pure,you\u2019ve proved us, perfected us, and made us holy."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "You\u2019ve captured us, ensnared us in your net.Then, like prisoners,
        you placed chains around our necks. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 66:11
        content: "  Or \u201Cyou attached suffering to our hips.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You\u2019ve allowed our enemies to prevail against us.We\u2019ve
        passed through fire and flood,yet in the end you always bring us out better
        than we were before,saturated with your goodness. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 66:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cyou brought us out into a wide-open space [a place of
          rest].\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I come before your presence with my sacrifice.I\u2019ll give you
        all that I\u2019ve promised, everything I have."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: When I was overcome in my anguish,I promised to give you my sacrifice.Here
        it is! All that I said I would offer you is yours.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I\u2019ll throw it all\u2014the best I have to bring\u2014into the
        fireas the fragrance of my sacrifice ascends unto you. [[COMMENT(0)]]Pause
        in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 66:15
        content: "  The literal Hebrew describes the sacrifice as \u201Cburnt offerings
          of fat beasts and the smoke of rams, bulls, and male goats.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "All you lovers of God who want to please him,come and listen, and
        I\u2019ll tell you what he did for me."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I cried aloud to him with all my heart, and he answered me!Now my
        mouth overflows with the highest praise.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Yet if I had closed my eyes to my sin, [[COMMENT(0)]]the Lord God
        would have closed his ears to my prayer.
      comments:
      - number: 66:18
        content: "  Or \u201CIf I had cherished iniquity in my heart.\u201D  "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: But praises rise to God,for he paid attention to my prayer and answered
        my cry to him!
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "I will forever praise this God who didn\u2019t close his heart when
        I prayedand never said no when I asked him for help.He never once refused
        to show me his tender love."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: It\u2019s Time to Praise Him"
      title: "It\u2019s Time to Praise Him"
      number: 1
      content: For the Pure and Shining OneA poetic song of praise for guitarGod,
        keep us near your mercy-fountain and bless us!And when you look down on us,
        may your face beam with joy! [[COMMENT(0)]]Pause in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 67:1
        content: "  Or \u201CMay he cause his face to shine with us\u201D or \u201CMay
          he smile on us.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Send us out all over the world so that everyone everywherewill discover
        your ways and know who you areand see your power to save.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Let all the nations burst forth with praise;let everyone everywhere
        love and enjoy you!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Then how glad the nations will be when you are their King.They will
        sing, they will shout, for you give true justice to the people.Yes! You,
        Lord, are the shepherd of the nations!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: No wonder the peoples praise you!Let all the people praise you more!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 67:5
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CLet all the people come to know you.\u201D  "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The harvest of the earth is here!God, the very God we worship,keeps
        us satisfied at his banquet of blessings.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And the blessings keep coming!All the ends of the earth will give
        himthe honor he deserves and be in awe of him!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Song of Triumph'
      title: A Song of Triumph
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneDavid\u2019s poetic song of praiseGod!
        Arise with awesome power,and every one of your enemies will scatter in fear!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Chase them away\u2014all these God-haters.Blow them away as a puff
        of smoke.Melt them away like wax in the fire.One good look at you and the
        wicked vanish."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But let all the righteous be glad!Yes, let them all rejoice in your
        presenceand be carried away with gladness. [[COMMENT(0)]]Let them laugh and
        be radiant with joy!
      comments:
      - number: 68:3
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Aramaic is \u201Cthey
          rejoice in his sweetness.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Let them sing their celebration-songsfor the coming of the cloud rider
        whose name is Yah! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 68:4
        content: '  More than an abbreviation, the name Yah is associated with the
          God of heaven, the God of highest glory and power.    '
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: 'To the fatherless he is a father.To the widow he is a champion friend.The
        lonely he makes part of a family.The prisoners [[COMMENT(0)]] he leads into
        prosperity until they sing for joy.This is our Holy God in his Holy Place!But
        for the rebels there is heartache and despair. '
      comments:
      - number: "68:5\u20136"
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201Cthe bitter ones.\u201D      Or \u201Cthey
          will live in a sun-scorched land.\u201D    "
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: 'To the fatherless he is a father.To the widow he is a champion friend.The
        lonely he makes part of a family.The prisoners [[COMMENT(0)]] he leads into
        prosperity until they sing for joy.This is our Holy God in his Holy Place!But
        for the rebels there is heartache and despair. '
      comments:
      - number: "68:5\u20136"
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201Cthe bitter ones.\u201D      Or \u201Cthey
          will live in a sun-scorched land.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: O&nbsp;Lord, it was you who marched in front of your people,leading
        them through the wasteland.Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The earth shook beneath your feet; the heavens filled with cloudsbefore
        the presence of the God of Sinai.The sacred mountain shook at the sight of
        the face of Israel\u2019s God."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You, O&nbsp;God, sent the reviving rain upon your weary inheritance,showers
        of blessing to refresh it.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So there your people settled. [[COMMENT(0)]]And in your kindness you
        provided  the poor with abundance.
      comments:
      - number: 68:10
        content: "  Or \u201CFor you live among them [in community].\u201D The Hebrew
          is uncertain.      Or \u201Csustain.\u201D God anticipates our needs and
          has gone before us to provide for and sustain us in our journey.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'God Almighty declares the word of the gospel with power, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        the warring women of Zion deliver its message: '
      comments:
      - number: 68:11
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.      As translated from the Masoretic
          Text.    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThe conquering legions have themselves been conquered.Look
        at them flee!\u201DNow Zion\u2019s women are left to gather the spoils."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When you sleep between sharpened stakes, [[COMMENT(0)]]I see you
        sparkling like silver and glistening like gold,covered by the beautiful wings
        of a dove! '
      comments:
      - number: 68:13
        content: "  The Aramaic word    can be translated \u201Csharpened stakes\u201D
          or \u201Cthorns.\u201D This is an obvious prophecy of the cross and our
          union with Christ as he was crucified.      As translated from the Aramaic
          text, this verse contains prophetic hints of Calvary, where Jesus \u201Cslept\u201D
          the sleep of death between the \u201Csharpened stakes\u201D of the cross.
          The word    is plural and points us to our co-crucifixion with Christ.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: When the Almighty found a king for himself,it became white as snow
        in his shade. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 68:14
        content: "  Every scholar consulted concludes that this verse is difficult,
          if not impossible, to interpret properly and translate accurately. The
          last words are literally \u201CSnow fell in Zalmon.\u201D Zalmon (or Salmon)
          was a wooded area and means \u201Cshady.\u201D    "
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: O&nbsp;huge, magnificent mountain,you are the mighty kingdom of God!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]All the other peaks, though impressive and imposing,look with
        envy on you, Mount Zion!For Zion is the mountain where God has chosen to
        live forever.
      comments:
      - number: "68:15\u201316"
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201Cmountain of provision.\u201D    "
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: O&nbsp;huge, magnificent mountain,you are the mighty kingdom of God!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]All the other peaks, though impressive and imposing,look with
        envy on you, Mount Zion!For Zion is the mountain where God has chosen to
        live forever.
      comments:
      - number: "68:15\u201316"
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201Cmountain of provision.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Look! The mighty chariots of God!Ten thousands upon ten thousands,more
        than anyone could ever number.God is at the front,leading them all from Mount
        Sinai into his sanctuarywith the radiance of holiness upon him. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 68:17
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CThe Lord sends his provisions from
          his Holy Place on Mount Sinai.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He ascends into the heavenly heights,taking his many captured ones
        with him,leading them in triumphal procession.And gifts were given to men,
        even the once rebellious,so that they may dwell with Yah.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: What a glorious God! [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>.</smallcaps>He
        gives us salvation over and over, then daily he carries our burdens! Pause
        in his presence
      comments:
      - number: 68:19
        content: "  The Aramaic is  , the Aramaic form of  or Lord          is in
          the plural form in the Hebrew text (\u201Csalvations\u201D).      Or \u201Cdaily
          loads us with benefits.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Our God is a mighty God who saves us over and over!For the Lord, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        rescues usfrom the ways of death many times.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But he will crush every enemy, shattering their strength.He will make
        heads rollfor they refuse to repent of their stubborn, sinful ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I hear the Lord God saying to all the enemies of his people,\u201CYou\u2019d
        better come out of your hiding places,all of you who are doing your best
        to stay far away from me. [[COMMENT(0)]]Don\u2019t you know there\u2019s
        no place to hide?"
      comments:
      - number: 68:22
        content: "  The Hebrew text makes reference to Bashan (a high mountain) and
          to the depths of the sea. In other words, there\u2019s no place to hide.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For my people will be the conquerors;they will soon have you under
        their feet.They will crush you until there is nothing left!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 68:23
        content: "  The Hebrew text is literally \u201CYour enemies will be food
          for the dogs.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "O&nbsp;God, my King, your triumphal processionskeep moving onward
        in holiness;you\u2019re moving onward toward the Holy Place!"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Leaders in front, [[COMMENT(0)]] then musicians,with young maidens
        in between, striking their tambourines.
      comments:
      - number: 68:25
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew is \u201CSingers
          in front.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they sing, \u201CLet all God\u2019s princely people rejoice!Let
        all the congregations bring their blessing to God, saying,\u2018The Lord
        of the fountain! The Lord of the fountain of life!The Lord of the fountain
        of Israel!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Astonishingly, it\u2019s the favored youth leading the way: [[COMMENT(0)]]princes
        of praise in their royal robesand exalted princes are among them,along with
        princes who have wrestled with God."
      comments:
      - number: 68:27
        content: "  The Hebrew includes the names of four sons of Jacob, representing
          four tribes. Benjamin, the youngest son, means \u201Cson of my right hand\u201D
          or \u201Cthe favored one.\u201D Judah means \u201Cpraise.\u201D Zebulon\u2019s
          name is the word for \u201Cexalted.\u201D Naphtali means \u201Cobtained
          by wrestling.\u201D Each name speaks of a princely group and is used here
          poetically not only for Israel but for all of God\u2019s \u201Cprincely
          people\u201D in this holy procession of worship.    "
    - name: '28-29: '
      title: 
      number: 28-29
      content: "Display your strength, God, and we\u2019ll be strong! [[COMMENT(0)]]For
        your miracles have made us who we are.Lord, do it againand parade from your
        temple your mighty power.By your command even kings will bring gifts to you."
      comments:
      - number: "68:28\u201329"
        content: "  The Great Bible translated by Miles Coverdale (1488\u20131569)
          translates this as \u201CYour God has sent forth strength for you.\u201D    "
    - name: '28-29: '
      title: 
      number: 28-29
      content: "Display your strength, God, and we\u2019ll be strong! [[COMMENT(0)]]For
        your miracles have made us who we are.Lord, do it againand parade from your
        temple your mighty power.By your command even kings will bring gifts to you."
      comments:
      - number: "68:28\u201329"
        content: "  The Great Bible translated by Miles Coverdale (1488\u20131569)
          translates this as \u201CYour God has sent forth strength for you.\u201D    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "God, rebuke the beast-life that hides within us! [[COMMENT(0)]]Rebuke
        those who claim to be \u201Cstrong ones,\u201D who lurk within the congregationand
        abuse the people out of their love for money.God scatters the people who
        are spoiling for a fight."
      comments:
      - number: 68:30
        content: "  Literal Hebrew is \u201Crebuke the beasts in the reeds.\u201D     
          This verse has puzzled scholars, and many conclude that the Hebrew text
          is nearly incomprehensible, with tremendous variations in the translation.  "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Africa will send her noble envoys to you, O&nbsp;God.They will come
        running, stretching out their hands in love to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Let all the nations of the earth sing songs of praise to Almighty
        God!Go ahead, all you nations\u2014sing your praise to the Lord!Pause in
        his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Make music for the one who strides the ancient skies.Listen to his
        thunderous voice of might split open the heavens.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Give it up for God, for he alone has all the strength and power!Proclaim
        his majesty! For his glory shines down on Israel.His mighty strength soars
        in the clouds of glory.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: God, we are consumed with awe, trembling before youas your glory streams
        from your Holy Place.The God of power shares his mighty strength with Israeland
        with all his people.God, we give our highest praise to you!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: A Cry of Distress 69Psalm 69is considered one of the most outstanding
        messianic psalms, with obvious prophetic references to the sufferings and
        cross of Jesus Christ.'
      title: A Cry of Distress 69Psalm 69is considered one of the most outstanding
        messianic psalms, with obvious prophetic references to the sufferings and
        cross of Jesus Christ.
      number: 1-2
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]To the Pure and Shining OneDavid\u2019s poetic song
        of praise To the tune of \u201CLilies\u201DGod, my God, come and save me!These
        floods of trouble have risen higher and higher.The water is up to my neck!
        [[COMMENT(1)]]I\u2019m sinking into the mud with no place to stand,and I\u2019m
        about to drown in this storm."
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">69</span>
        content: '    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">is considered one
          of the most outstanding messianic psalms, with obvious prophetic references
          to the sufferings and cross of Jesus Christ.</span>    '
      - number: "69:1\u20132"
        content: "  Or \u201Cthroat.\u201D    "
    - name: '1-2: A Cry of Distress 69Psalm 69is considered one of the most outstanding
        messianic psalms, with obvious prophetic references to the sufferings and
        cross of Jesus Christ.'
      title: A Cry of Distress 69Psalm 69is considered one of the most outstanding
        messianic psalms, with obvious prophetic references to the sufferings and
        cross of Jesus Christ.
      number: 1-2
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]To the Pure and Shining OneDavid\u2019s poetic song
        of praise To the tune of \u201CLilies\u201DGod, my God, come and save me!These
        floods of trouble have risen higher and higher.The water is up to my neck!
        [[COMMENT(1)]]I\u2019m sinking into the mud with no place to stand,and I\u2019m
        about to drown in this storm."
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">69</span>
        content: '    <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">is considered one
          of the most outstanding messianic psalms, with obvious prophetic references
          to the sufferings and cross of Jesus Christ.</span>    '
      - number: "69:1\u20132"
        content: "  Or \u201Cthroat.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I\u2019m weary, exhausted with weeping.My throat is dry, my voice
        is gone, my eyes are swollen with sorrow,and I\u2019m waiting for you, God,
        to come through for me."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I can\u2019t even count all those who hate me for no reason.Many
        influential men want me silenced,yet I\u2019ve done nothing against them.Must
        I restore what I never took away?"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "God, my life is an open book to you.You know every sin I\u2019ve
        ever done.For nothing within me is hidden from your sight!"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> of Angel Armies,keep me from ever
        being a stumbling block to others,to those who love you.Lord God of Israel,
        don\u2019t let what happens to mebe the source of confusion to those who
        are passionate for you."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Because of my love for you, Lord,I have been mocked, cursed, and disgraced.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Even my own brothers, those of my family,act as though they don\u2019t
        want anything to do with me."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: My love for you has my heart on fire!My passion for your house consumes
        me!Nothing will turn me away,even though I endure all the insults of those
        who insult you.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When they see me seeking for more of you with weeping [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and fasting,they all just scoff and scorn at my passion.
      comments:
      - number: 69:10
        content: "  Or \u201CWhen I pour out my soul\u201D or \u201CWhen I weep soul-tears.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: When I humble myself with sorrow over my sin,it gives them a reason
        to mock me even more.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The leaders, the influential ones\u2014how they scorn my passion
        for you!I\u2019ve become the talk of the town, the theme of drunkards\u2019
        songs."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: But I keep calling out to you, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!I know
        you will bend down to listen to me,for now is the season of favor.Because
        of your faithful love for me,your answer to my prayer will be my sure salvation.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Pull me out of this mess! Don\u2019t let me sink!Rescue me from those
        who hate me and from all this trouble I\u2019m in!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Don\u2019t let this flood drown me.Save me from these deep watersor
        I\u2019ll go down to the pit of destruction."
      comments: []
    - name: '16-17: '
      title: 
      number: 16-17
      content: Oh, Lord God, answer my prayers!I need to see your tender kindness,
        your grace,your compassion, and your constant love.Just let me see your face,
        and turn your heart toward me.Come running quickly to your servant.In this
        deep distress, come and answer my prayer.
      comments: []
    - name: '16-17: '
      title: 
      number: 16-17
      content: Oh, Lord God, answer my prayers!I need to see your tender kindness,
        your grace,your compassion, and your constant love.Just let me see your face,
        and turn your heart toward me.Come running quickly to your servant.In this
        deep distress, come and answer my prayer.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Come closer as a friend and redeem me.Set me free so my enemies cannot
        say that you are powerless.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "See how they dishonor me in shame and disgrace?You know, Lord, what
        I\u2019m going through, and you see it all."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "I\u2019m heartsick and heartbroken by it all.Their contempt has crushed
        my soul.I looked for sympathy and compassionbut found only empty stares."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I was hungry and they gave me bitter food.I was thirsty and they offered
        me vinegar. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 69:21
        content: '  This was fulfilled with Jesus being offered vinegar on the cross.
          See  .    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Let their \u201Cfeasts\u201D turn to ashes.Let their \u201Cpeace
        and security\u201D become their downfall."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Make them blind as bats, groping in the dark.Let them be feeble, trembling
        continually.
      comments: []
    - name: '24-25: '
      title: 
      number: 24-25
      content: Pour out your fury on them all!Consume them with the fire of your
        anger!Burn down the walled palace where they live!Leave them homeless and
        desolate!
      comments: []
    - name: '24-25: '
      title: 
      number: 24-25
      content: Pour out your fury on them all!Consume them with the fire of your
        anger!Burn down the walled palace where they live!Leave them homeless and
        desolate!
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "For they come against the one you yourself have struck,and they scorn
        the pain of those you\u2019ve pierced."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Pile on them the guilt of their sins.Don\u2019t let them ever go
        free."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Leave them out of your list of the living!Blot them out of your Book
        of Life!Never name them as your own!
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: I am burdened and broken by this pain.When your miracle rescue comes
        to me,it will lift me to the highest place.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then my song will be a burst of praise to you.My glory-shouts will
        make your fame even more gloriousto all who hear my praises!
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: For I know, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, that my praises mean more
        to youthan all my gifts and sacrifices.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "All who seek you will see God do this for them,and they\u2019ll overflow
        with gladness.Let this revive your hearts, all you lovers of God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> does listen to the poor and needyand
        will not abandon his prisoners of love. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 69:33
        content: "  Or \u201Cthose wearing shackles.\u201D  "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Let all the universe praise him!The high heavens and everyone on earth,
        praise him!Let the oceans deep, with everything in them, keep it up!
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: God will come to save his Zion-people.God will build up his cities
        of Judah,for there his people will live in peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: All their children will inherit the land,and the lovers of his name
        will live there safe and secure.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Cry for Help'
      title: A Cry for Help
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneDavid\u2019s poetic lament to always rememberPlease,
        Lord! Come quickly and rescue me!God, show me your favor and restore me."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Let all who seek my life be humiliated and confused.God, send them
        sprawling, all who wish me evil;they just want me dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Scoff at every scoffer and cause them all to be utter failures!Let
        them be ashamed and horrified over their complete defeat.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But let all who passionately seek you erupt with excitement and joyover
        what you\u2019ve done!Let all your devoted lovers, who continually rejoice
        in the Savior, [[COMMENT(0)]]say aloud, \u201CHow great and glorious is our
        God!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 70:4
        content: '  This verse contains the Hebrew root word for Yeshua.  '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Lord, in my place of weakness and need,won\u2019t you turn your heart
        toward me and hurry to help me?For you are my Savior, and I\u2019m always
        in your thoughts.So don\u2019t delay to deliver me now, for you are my God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Psalm of Old Age'
      title: The Psalm of Old Age
      number: 1
      content: "Lord, you are my secure shelter. Don\u2019t ever let me down!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Let your justice be my breakthrough.Bend low to my whispered cryand
        save me from all my enemies!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You\u2019re the only place of protection for me.I keep coming back
        to hide myself in you,for you are like a mountain-cliff fortress where I\u2019m
        kept safe."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Let me escape from these cruel and wicked men,and save me from the
        hands of the evil one.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For you are my only hope, Lord!I\u2019ve hung on to you, trusting
        in you all my life."
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "It was you who supported me from the day I was born,loving me, helping
        me through my life\u2019s journey.You\u2019ve made me into a miracle;no wonder
        I trust you and praise you forever!Many marvel at my success,but I know it
        is all because of you, my mighty protector!"
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "It was you who supported me from the day I was born,loving me, helping
        me through my life\u2019s journey.You\u2019ve made me into a miracle;no wonder
        I trust you and praise you forever!Many marvel at my success,but I know it
        is all because of you, my mighty protector!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I\u2019m overflowing with your praise for all you\u2019ve done,and
        your splendor thrills me all day long."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now that I\u2019m old, don\u2019t set me aside.Don\u2019t let go
        of me when my strength is spent."
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: "For all my enemies whisper behind my back.They\u2019re waiting for
        me to fall so they can finish me off.They\u2019re convinced you\u2019ve left
        meand that you\u2019ll never come to my rescue.They\u2019re saying, \u201CLet\u2019s
        get him now! He has no savior!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: "For all my enemies whisper behind my back.They\u2019re waiting for
        me to fall so they can finish me off.They\u2019re convinced you\u2019ve left
        meand that you\u2019ll never come to my rescue.They\u2019re saying, \u201CLet\u2019s
        get him now! He has no savior!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O&nbsp;God, stay close to me!Don\u2019t just watch from a distance!
        Hurry to help me, my God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Cover these accusers of mine with shame and failure!Destroy them all,
        for they only want to kill me!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "No matter what, I\u2019ll trust in you to help me.Nothing will stop
        me from praising you to magnify your glory!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I couldn\u2019t begin to count the times you\u2019ve been there for
        me.With the skill of a poet I\u2019ll never run out of things to sayabout
        how you faithfully kept me from danger."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will come forth in your mighty strength, O&nbsp;my Lord God. [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>.\u201D</smallcaps>I\u2019ll
        tell everyone that you alone are the perfect one."
      comments:
      - number: 71:16
        content: "  Or \u201CI will enter into the manliness of Lord    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "From my childhood you\u2019ve been my teacher,and I\u2019m still
        telling everyone of your miracle-wonders!"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "God, now that I\u2019m old and gray, don\u2019t walk away.Give me
        grace to demonstrate to the next generationall your mighty miracles and your
        excitement,to show them your magnificent power!"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: For your glorious righteousness reaches up to the high heavens.No
        one could ever be compared to you!Who is your equal, O&nbsp;God of marvels
        and wonders?
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Even though you\u2019ve let us sink down with trials and troubles,I
        know you will revive us again,lifting us up from the dust of death."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Give us even more greatness than before.Turn and comfort us once again.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: My loving God, the harp in my heart will praise you.Your faithful
        heart toward us will be the theme of my song.Melodies and music will rise
        to you, the Holy One of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will shout and sing your praises for all you are to me\u2014Savior,
        lover of my soul!"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I\u2019ll never stop telling others how perfect you are,while all
        those who seek my harm slink away ashamed and defeated!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Righteous King'
      title: The Righteous King
      number: 1
      content: "Solomon\u2019s psalm [[COMMENT(0)]]O&nbsp;God, make the king a godly
        judge like youand give the king\u2019s son the gift of justice too."
      comments:
      - number: 72
        content: "  The Septuagint indicates this could be a psalm written by David
          for his son Solomon. This royal psalm is a prayer for the king. Read through
          it as though it is referring to King Jesus\u2014One who is greater than
          Solomon.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Help him to give true justice to your people,honorably and equally
        to all.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Then the mountains of influence will be fruitful,and from your righteousnessprosperity
        and peace will flow to all the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: May the poor and humble have an advocate with the king.May he consider
        the children of the poorand crush the cruel oppressor.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The sun and moon will stop shiningbefore your devoted lovers will
        stop worshiping;for ages upon ages the people will love and adore you!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Your favor will fall like rain upon our surrendered lives, [[COMMENT(0)]]like
        showers reviving the earth.
      comments:
      - number: 72:6
        content: "  Or \u201Clike rain on mown grass.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In the days of his reign the righteous will spring forthwith the abundance
        of peace and prosperity forevermore.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: May he subdue and take dominion from sea to sea;may he rule from the
        river to the rim.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Desert nomads are bowing at his feet;every enemy is falling facedown,
        biting the dust!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Distant kings [[COMMENT(0)]] will surrender and come with their giftsfrom
        every continent and coastland;they will offer their tribute to you.
      comments:
      - number: 72:10
        content: '  Included in the Hebrew text are kings of Tarshish (Spain) and
          kings of Sheba and Seba (Ethiopia).    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: O&nbsp;King of kings, they will all bow before you.O&nbsp;King of
        kings, every nation will one day serve you.
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "He will care for the needy and neglectedwhen they cry to him for
        help.The humble and helpless will know his kindness,for with a father\u2019s
        compassion he will save their souls."
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "He will care for the needy and neglectedwhen they cry to him for
        help.The humble and helpless will know his kindness,for with a father\u2019s
        compassion he will save their souls."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They will be rescued from tyranny and torture,for their lifeblood
        is precious in his eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Long live this King!May the wealth of the world [[COMMENT(0)]] be
        laid before him.May there be ceaseless praise and prayer to him.May all the
        blessing be brought to him.
      comments:
      - number: 72:15
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe gold of Sheba.\u201D  "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Bless us with a bountiful harvest,with golden grain swaying on the
        mountain fields!May the cities be full of praising people, fruitful and filled\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: so that his name may be honored forever!May the fame of his name spring
        forth!May it shine on, like the sunshine!In him all will be blessed to bless
        others,and may all the people bless the One who blessed them.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Praise <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> forever, the God of Israel!He
        is the one and only God of wonders,surpassing every expectation.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The blazing glory of his name will be praised forever!May all the
        earth overflow with his glory!Faithful is our King! Amen!
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Book 3The Leviticus PsalmsPsalms of worship and God\u2019s house"
      title: "Book 3The Leviticus PsalmsPsalms of worship and God\u2019s house"
      number: 20
      content: "This concludes the poetry sung by David, Jesse\u2019s son."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Justice"
      title: "God\u2019s Justice"
      number: 1
      content: "Asaph\u2019s psalm [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>. However, it is possible
        that Asaph was an office not an individual\u2014Asaphites who were part of
        a prophetic company of composers. The name Asaph means \u201Ca harvest\u201D
        or \u201Cfulfilled prophecy.\u201D Asaph possibly comes from a Semitic root
        word for \u201Cportal.\u201D Perhaps the Asaphites were named such because
        their music opened a portal into the heavenly realm.</smallcaps>No one can
        deny it\u2014God is really good to Israeland to all those with pure hearts.But
        I nearly missed seeing it for myself."
      comments:
      - number: 73
        content: '  Asaph was one of three Levites that David set over the worship
          of      '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Here\u2019s my story: I narrowly missed losing it all."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I was stumbling over what I saw the wicked doing.For when I saw the
        boasters with such wealth and prosperity,I became jealous over their smug
        security.
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "Indulging in whatever they wanted, going where they wanted,doing
        what they wanted, and with no care in the world,no pain, no problems\u2014they
        seemed to have it made.They lived as though life would never end."
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "Indulging in whatever they wanted, going where they wanted,doing
        what they wanted, and with no care in the world,no pain, no problems\u2014they
        seemed to have it made.They lived as though life would never end."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They didn\u2019t even try to hide their pride and opulence.Cruelty
        and violence are parts of their lifestyle."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Pampered and pompous, vice oozes from their souls;they overflow with
        vanity.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They\u2019re such snobs\u2014looking down their noses.They even scoff
        at God!They are nothing but bullies threatening God\u2019s people."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They are loudmouths with no fear of God, pretending to know it all\u2014windbags
        full of hot air, impressing only themselves."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Yet the people keep coming back to listento more of their nonsense.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They tell their cohorts, \u201CGod will never know.See, he has no
        clue of what we\u2019re doing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "These are the wicked ones I\u2019m talking about!They never have
        to lift a finger,living a life of ease while their riches multiply."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Have I been foolish to play by the rules and keep my life pure?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Here I am suffering under your discipline day after day.I feel like
        I\u2019m being punished all day long."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: If I had given in to my pain and spoken of what I was really feeling,it
        would have sounded like unfaithfulness to the next generation.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When I tried to understand it all, I just couldn\u2019t.It was too
        puzzling\u2014too much of a riddle to me."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But then one day I was brought into the sanctuaries of God,and in
        the light of glory, my distorted perspective vanished.Then I understood that
        the destiny of the wicked was near!
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "They\u2019re the ones who are on the slippery path,and God will suddenly
        let them slide off into destructionto be consumed with terrors forever!"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "It will be an instant end to all their life of ease;a blink of the
        eye and they\u2019re swept away by sudden calamity!They\u2019re all nothing
        more than momentary monarchs\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "soon to disappear like a dream when one awakes.When the rooster crows,Lord
        God, you\u2019ll despise their life of fantasies. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 73:20
        content: "  Or \u201Cshadows.\u201D  "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: When I saw all of this, what turmoil filled my heart,piercing my opinions
        with your truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: I was so stupid. I was senseless and ignorant,acting like a brute
        beast before you, Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Yet, in spite of all this, I still belong to you;you hold me by my
        right hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: You lead me with your secret wisdom.And following you brings me into
        your brightness and glory!
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Whom have I in heaven but you? You\u2019re all I want!No one on earth
        means as much to me as you."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Lord, so many times I fail; I fall into disgrace.But when I trust
        in you, I have a strong and glorious presenceprotecting and anointing me.
        Forever you\u2019re all I need!"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Those who abandon the worship of God will perish.The false and unfaithful
        will be silenced, never heard from again.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But I\u2019ll keep coming closer and closer to you, Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,for
        your name is good to me. I\u2019ll keep telling the world ofyour awesome
        works, my faithful and glorious God!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: We Need You Now'
      title: We Need You Now
      number: 1
      content: "Asaph\u2019s poem of instructionAre you really going to leave us,
        God?Would you turn your back on us, rejecting your people?We are yours, your
        very own. [[COMMENT(0)]]Will your anger smolder against us forever?"
      comments:
      - number: 74:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe sheep of your pasture.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Don\u2019t forget that we are your beloved ones.Wrap us back into
        your heart again, for you chose us.You brought us out of our slavery and
        bondageand made us your favored ones, your Zion-people,your home on earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Turn your steps toward this devastation.Come running to bring your
        restoring grace to these ruins, [[COMMENT(0)]]to what the enemy has done
        to devastate your Holy Place.
      comments:
      - number: 74:3
        content: "  This verse reads differently in the Aramaic: \u201CLift up your
          servants with your might above those who take them captive, for those who
          oppress us are enemies to your holiness.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They have come into the very midst of your dwelling place,roaring
        like beasts, setting up their banners to flaunt their conquest.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now everything is in shambles! They\u2019ve totally destroyed it.Like
        a forest chopped down to the ground,there\u2019s nothing left."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: All of the beauty of the craftsmanshipof the inner place has been
        ruined,smashed, broken, and shattered. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 74:6
        content: "  This psalm describes physical destruction as well as what the
          enemy of our souls has done spiritually to mar the image of God in the
          \u201Cinner place\u201D of man\u2019s spirit. God will fully restore all
          things, including his image within us, as our hearts become his Holy Place
          on the earth.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They\u2019ve burned it all to the ground.They\u2019ve violated your
        sanctuary,the very dwelling place of your glory and your name."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They boasted, \u201CLet\u2019s completely crush them!Let\u2019s wipe
        out every trace of this God.Let\u2019s burn up every sacred place where they
        worship this God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "We don\u2019t see any miraculous signs anymore.There\u2019s no longer
        a prophet among uswho can tell us how long this devastation will continue."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: God, how much longer will you let this go onand allow these barbarians
        to blaspheme your name?Will you stand back and watch them get away with this
        forever?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Why don\u2019t you do something?You have the power to break in,so
        why would you hide your great power from us?Don\u2019t hold back! Unleash
        your might and give them a final blow."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: You have always been, and always will be, my King.You are the mighty
        conqueror, working wonders all over the world.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: It was you who split the sea in two by your glorious strength.You
        smashed the power of Tannin, the sea monster.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: You crushed the might of Leviathan, [[COMMENT(0)]] the great dragon,then
        you took the crumbs and fed them to the sharks.
      comments:
      - number: 74:14
        content: "  Leviathan is mentioned six times in  . Leviathan means \u201Ctwisted\u201D
          or \u201Ccoiled\u201D and is considered to be a sea monster. See  .    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: With your glory you opened up springs and fountains,then you spoke,
        and the ever-flowing springs of Jordandried up so we could cross over.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: You own the day and the night.Sunlight and starlight call you Creator.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The four corners of the earth were formed by your hands,and every
        changing season owes its beauty to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "O&nbsp; <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, don\u2019t ever forget how
        these arrogant enemies,like fools, have mocked your name."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Lord, aren\u2019t we your beloved dove that praises you? [[COMMENT(0)]]Protect
        us from these wild beasts who want to harm us.Don\u2019t leave us as lambs
        among wolves!You can\u2019t abandon us after all we\u2019ve been through!"
      comments:
      - number: 74:19
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint, Syriac, and one Hebrew manuscript.  '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Remember your promises to us,for darkness covers the land,giving the
        violent ones a hiding place.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Don\u2019t let these insults continue.Can\u2019t you see that we
        are your downtroddenand oppressed people?Make the poor and needy into a choir
        of praise to you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Don\u2019t ignore these ignorant words, this continual mocking.Rise
        up, God; it\u2019s time to defend yourself from all this."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Never forget what your adversaries are saying.For their rage and
        uproar rise continually against you.It\u2019s time to stand up to them!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: A Cup in God\u2019s Hand"
      title: "A Cup in God\u2019s Hand"
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneAsaph\u2019s poetic song To the tune of
        \u201CDo Not Destroy\u201DGod, our hearts spill over with praise to you!We
        overflow with thanks, for your name is the \u201CNear One.\u201DAll we want
        to talk about is your wonderful works!And we hear your reply:"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWhen the time is ripe I will arise,and I will judge the world
        with perfect righteousness."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Though I have set the earth firmly on its pillars,I will shake it
        until it totters, and everyone\u2019s hearts will tremble.\u201DPause in
        his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "God warns the proud, \u201CStop your arrogant boasting!\u201DAnd
        he warns the wicked,\u201CDon\u2019t think for a moment you can resist me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Why would you speak with such stubborn pride?Don\u2019t you dare
        raise your fist against me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "This I know:the favor that brings promotion and powerdoesn\u2019t
        come from anywhere on earth,for no one exalts a person but God, the true
        judge of all.He alone determines where favor rests.He anoints one for greatnessand
        brings another down to his knees."
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "This I know:the favor that brings promotion and powerdoesn\u2019t
        come from anywhere on earth,for no one exalts a person but God, the true
        judge of all.He alone determines where favor rests.He anoints one for greatnessand
        brings another down to his knees."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: A foaming cup filled with judgment mixed with furyis in the hands
        of the Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,full to the brim and ready to run
        over.He filled it up for the wicked, and they will drink itdown to the very
        last drop!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: But I will proclaim the victory of the God of Jacob.My melodies of
        praise will make him known.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: My praises will break the powers of wickedness,while the righteous
        will be promoted and become powerful!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Awe-Inspiring Power'
      title: Awe-Inspiring Power
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneAsaph\u2019s poetic tune, a song of smitingGod
        is well known in the land of Judah.He is famous throughout Israel,"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: making his home in Jerusalem, [[COMMENT(0)]] living here on Mount
        Zion.
      comments:
      - number: 76:2
        content: "  Or \u201CSalem,\u201D the ancient name of Jerusalem.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "That\u2019s where he smashes every weapon of warthat comes against
        him.That\u2019s where he uses the broken arrowsas kindling for his mighty
        bonfire.Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: God, you are so resplendent and radiant! [[COMMENT(0)]]Your majesty
        shines from your everlasting mountain.Nothing could be compared to you in
        glory!
      comments:
      - number: 76:4
        content: "  The word used here is often translated as \u201Canointed\u201D
          when taken from either the Hebrew or the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Even the mightiest of men have been paralyzed by your presence.They
        were so stunned and lifeless,not even the strongest one could lift a hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Jacob\u2019s God roared his rebuke,soldiers and their steeds
        all fell to the ground,stunned and lying still."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: No wonder you are greatly feared! You are the awe-inspiring God!For
        who could ever stand before your facewhen your fierce anger burns and live
        to tell about it.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: As the earth itself holds its breath in awe before you,judgment is
        decreed from heaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You arise to punish evil and defend the gentle upon the earth.Pause
        in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You have power to transform man\u2019s futile anger into praise.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]The fury of your enemies only causes your fame to increase. "
      comments:
      - number: 76:10
        content: "  Or \u201CThe counsel of men will praise you.\u201D      The Septuagint
          reads \u201CSurvivors of your wrath keep your festivals.\u201D  "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So you\u2019d better keep every promise you\u2019ve ever madeto the
        Awesome One, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!Let all people bring their extravagant
        gifts to him alone."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He is famous for breaking the spirit of the powers that be.And the
        kings of the earth will know him as the Fearsome One!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Cry to God'
      title: A Cry to God
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneAsaph\u2019s song of love\u2019s celebrationI
        poured out my complaint to you, God.I lifted up my voice, shouting out for
        your help."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: When I was in deep distress, in my day of trouble,I reached out for
        you with hands stretched out to heaven.Over and over I kept looking for you,
        God,but your comforting grace was nowhere to be found.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "As I thought of you I moaned, \u201CGod, where are you?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]I\u2019m
        overwhelmed with despair as I wait for your help to arrive.Pause in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 77:3
        content: "  Or \u201CWhen I am in heaviness [depressed], I will think upon
          God.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I can\u2019t get a wink of sleep until you come and comfort me.Now
        I\u2019m too burdened to even pray!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "My mind wandered, thinking of days gone by\u2014the years long since
        passed."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Then I remembered the worship songs I used to singin the night seasons,and
        my heart began to fill again with thoughts of you.So my spirit went out once
        more in search of you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Would you really walk off and leave me forever, my Lord God?Won\u2019t
        you show me your kind favor, delighting in me again?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Has your well of sweet mercy dried up?Will your promises never come
        true?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Have you somehow forgotten to show me love?Are you so angry that
        you\u2019ve closedyour heart of compassion toward me?Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Lord, what wounds me most is that it\u2019s somehow my fault thatyou\u2019ve
        changed your heart toward meand I no longer see the years of the Mighty Oneor
        your right hand of power. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 77:10
        content: "  This difficult verse has a number of alternate translations,
          including \u201CYour right hand has changed [or withered].\u201D The implication
          is that God\u2019s power and protection are no longer being seen.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Yet I could never forget all your miracles, my God,as I remember all
        your wonders of old.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I ponder all you\u2019ve done, Lord, musing on all your miracles."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "It\u2019s here in your presence, in your sanctuary,where I learn
        more of your ways, [[COMMENT(0)]]for holiness is revealed in everything you
        do.Lord, you\u2019re the one and only, the great and glorious God!"
      comments:
      - number: 77:13
        content: '  This is an alternative translation.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Your display of wonders, miracles, and powermakes the nations acknowledge
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "By your glory-bursts you\u2019ve rescued us over and over.Just ask
        the sons of Jacob orthe sons of Joseph, and they will tell you!And all of
        us, your beloved ones, know that it\u2019s true!Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the many waters of the Red Sea took one look at you, [[COMMENT(0)]]they
        were afraid and ran away to hide\u2014trembling to its depths!"
      comments:
      - number: 77:16
        content: '  Although the Red Sea is not mentioned in the verse, it is implied
          in the context.    '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Storm clouds filled with water high in the skies;cloudbursts and thunderclaps
        announced your approach.Lightning-flashes lit up the landscape.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Rolling whirlwinds exploded with sonic booms of thunder,rumbling as
        the skies shouted out your storywith light and sound and wind.Everything
        on earth shook and trembled as you drew near.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Your steps formed a highway through the seaswith footprints on a pathway
        no one even knew was there. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 77:19
        content: '  This could be a prophecy of Jesus one day walking on water.  '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You led your people forward by your loving hand,blessed by the leadership
        of Moses and Aaron.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Lessons from History'
      title: Lessons from History
      number: 1
      content: "Asaph\u2019s poetic song of instructionBeloved ones, listen to this
        instruction.Open your heart to the revelationof this mystery that I share
        with you."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "A parable and a proverb are hidden in what I say\u2014an intriguing
        riddle [[COMMENT(0)]] from the past."
      comments:
      - number: 78:2
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Criddle\u201D () comes from the verb
          meaning \u201Cto tie a knot.\u201D It is something that must be untied
          and unraveled by the Spirit of God. One of these riddles or wordplays is
          the name of Jesus hidden in plain sight (see v.    and footnote).    "
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "We\u2019ve heard true stories from our fathers about our rich heritage.We
        will continue to tell our childrenand not hide from the rising generationthe
        great marvels of our God\u2014his miracles and power that have brought us
        all this far."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "We\u2019ve heard true stories from our fathers about our rich heritage.We
        will continue to tell our childrenand not hide from the rising generationthe
        great marvels of our God\u2014his miracles and power that have brought us
        all this far."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The story of Israel is a lesson in God\u2019s ways.He established
        decrees for Jacob and established the law in Israel,and he commanded our
        forefathers to teach them to their children."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For perpetuity God\u2019s ways will be passed downfrom one generation
        to the next, even to those not yet born."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In this way, every generation will set its hope in Godand not forget
        his wonderful works but keep his commandments.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: By following his ways they will break the past bondageof their fickle
        fathers, who were a stubborn, rebellious generationand whose spirits strayed
        from the eternal God.They refused to love him with all their hearts.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Take, for example, the sons of Ephraim.Though they were all equipped
        warriors, each with weapons,when the battle began they retreated and ran
        away in fear.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They didn\u2019t really believe the promises of God;they refused
        to trust him and move forward in faith."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: They forgot his wonderful works and the miracles of the past,
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: even their exodus from Egypt, the epic miracle of his might.They forgot
        the glories of his power at the place of passing over. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 78:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe fields of Zoan.\u201D    means \u201Ccrossing place\u201D
          or \u201Cplace of departure.\u201D (See v.  .)    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: God split the sea wide open, andthe waters stood at attention on either
        sideas the people passed on through!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: By day the moving glory-cloud led them forward.And all through the
        night the fire-cloud stood as a sentry of light.
      comments: []
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: In the days of desert dryness, he split open the mighty rock,and the
        waters flowed like a river before their very eyes.He gave them all they wanted
        to drink from his living springs.
      comments: []
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: In the days of desert dryness, he split open the mighty rock,and the
        waters flowed like a river before their very eyes.He gave them all they wanted
        to drink from his living springs.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Yet they kept their rebellion alive against God Most High,and their
        sins against God continued to be counted.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: In their hearts they tested God just to get what they wanted,asking
        for the food their hearts craved.
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "Like spoiled children they grumbled against God,demanding he prove
        his love by saying,\u201CCan\u2019t God provide for us in this barren wilderness?Will
        he give us food, or will he only give us water?Where\u2019s our meal?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "Like spoiled children they grumbled against God,demanding he prove
        his love by saying,\u201CCan\u2019t God provide for us in this barren wilderness?Will
        he give us food, or will he only give us water?Where\u2019s our meal?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Then God heard all their complaining and was furious!His anger flared
        up against his people.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For they turned away from faith and walked away in fear;they failed
        to trust in his power to save [[COMMENT(0)]] them when he was near.
      comments:
      - number: 78:22
        content: "  The word for \u201Csave\u201D looks and sounds like Yeshua (Jesus).    "
    - name: '23-24: '
      title: 
      number: 23-24
      content: Still he spoke on their behalf, and the skies opened up;the windows
        of heaven poured out food,the mercy bread-manna.The grain of grace fell from
        the clouds.
      comments: []
    - name: '23-24: '
      title: 
      number: 23-24
      content: Still he spoke on their behalf, and the skies opened up;the windows
        of heaven poured out food,the mercy bread-manna.The grain of grace fell from
        the clouds.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Humans ate angels\u2019 food\u2014the meal of the mighty ones. [[COMMENT(0)]]His
        grace gave them more than enough!"
      comments:
      - number: 78:25
        content: "  The word for \u201Cangels\u201D is    which means \u201Cbrave,\u201D
          \u201Cnoble,\u201D or \u201Cstrong.\u201D The psalmist was saying that
          God gave them the best, most delicious food imaginable, a meal eaten by
          the mighty ones, and yet the people grew tired of it and began to complain
          and demanded some variety.    "
    - name: '26-27: '
      title: 
      number: 26-27
      content: The heavenly winds of miracle power blew in their favor,and food rained
        down upon them;succulent quail quieted their hunger as they ate all they
        wanted.
      comments: []
    - name: '26-27: '
      title: 
      number: 26-27
      content: The heavenly winds of miracle power blew in their favor,and food rained
        down upon them;succulent quail quieted their hunger as they ate all they
        wanted.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Food fell from the skies, thick as clouds;their provision floated
        down right in front of their eyes!
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: He gave them all they desired, and they ate to their fill.
      comments: []
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: "But before they had even finished,even with their food still in their
        mouths,God\u2019s fiery anger arose against them,killing the finest of their
        mighty men."
      comments: []
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: "But before they had even finished,even with their food still in their
        mouths,God\u2019s fiery anger arose against them,killing the finest of their
        mighty men."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Yet in spite of all this, they kept right on sinning.Even when they
        saw God\u2019s marvels,they refused to believe God could care for them."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So God cut their lives short with sudden disaster,with nothing to
        show for their lives but fear and failure.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: When he cared for them they ignored him,but when he began to kill
        them, ending their lives in a moment,they came running back to God, pleading
        for mercy.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: They remembered that God, the Mighty One,was their strong protector,the
        Hero-God who would come to their rescue.
      comments: []
    - name: '36-37: '
      title: 
      number: 36-37
      content: But their repentance lasted only as long as they were in danger;they
        lied through their teeth to the true God of the Covenant.So quickly they
        wandered away from his promises,following God with their words and not their
        hearts!Their worship was only flattery.
      comments: []
    - name: '36-37: '
      title: 
      number: 36-37
      content: But their repentance lasted only as long as they were in danger;they
        lied through their teeth to the true God of the Covenant.So quickly they
        wandered away from his promises,following God with their words and not their
        hearts!Their worship was only flattery.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But amazingly, God\u2014so full of compassion\u2014still forgave
        them.He covered over their sins with his love,refusing to destroy them all.Over
        and over he held back his anger,restraining wrath to show them mercy."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "He knew that they were made from mere dust\u2014frail, fragile, and
        short-lived, here today and gone tomorrow."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: How many times they rebelled in their desert days!How they grieved
        him with their grumblings.
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: Again and again they limited God, preventing him from blessing them.Continually
        they turned back from himand provoked [[COMMENT(0)]] the Holy One of Israel!
      comments:
      - number: 78:41
        content: "  The Hebrew verb for \u201Cprovoked\u201D is a hapax legomenon
          and comes from a root word for \u201Cmarked.\u201D It is as though Israel\u2019s
          behavior wounded the heart of God.    "
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "They forgot his great love, how he took them by his hand,and with
        redemption\u2019s kiss he delivered them from their enemies."
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "They disregarded all the epic signs and marvels they sawwhen they
        escaped from Egypt\u2019s bondage.They forgot the judgment of the plagues
        that set them free."
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: God turned their rivers into blood, leaving the people thirsty.
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: He sent them vast swarms of filthy flies that sucked their blood.He
        sent hordes of frogs, ruining their lives.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: Grasshoppers consumed all their crops.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Every garden and every orchardwas flattened with blasts of hailstones,their
        fruit trees ruined by a killing frost.
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: Even their cattle fell prey, pounded by the falling hail;their livestock
        were struck with bolts of lightning.
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: Finally, he unleashed upon them the fierceness of his anger.Such fury!He
        sent them sorrow and devastating troubleby his mighty band of destroying
        angels;messengers of death were dispatched against them.
      comments: []
    - name: '50-51: '
      title: 
      number: 50-51
      content: "He lifted his mercy and let loose his fearful angerand did not spare
        their lives.He released the judgment-plagues to rage through their land.God
        struck down in death all the firstborn sons of Egypt\u2014the pride and joy
        of each family."
      comments: []
    - name: '50-51: '
      title: 
      number: 50-51
      content: "He lifted his mercy and let loose his fearful angerand did not spare
        their lives.He released the judgment-plagues to rage through their land.God
        struck down in death all the firstborn sons of Egypt\u2014the pride and joy
        of each family."
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: Then, like a shepherd leading his sheep, God led his peopleout of
        tyranny, guiding them through the wilderness like a flock.
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: Safely and carefully God led them out, with nothing to fear.But their
        enemies he led into the sea.He took care of them there once and for all!
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: Eventually God brought his people to the Holy Land,to a land of hills
        that he had prepared for them. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 78:54
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201CHe brought them to the border of his
          holiness, the mountain possessed by his right hand.\u201D    "
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "He drove out and scattered all the peoples occupying the land,staking
        out an inheritance, a portion for each of Israel\u2019s tribes."
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: Yet for all of this, they still rebelled and refused to follow his
        ways,provoking to anger the God Most High.
      comments: []
    - name: '57-58: '
      title: 
      number: 57-58
      content: Like traitors turning back, they forsook him.They were even worse
        than their fathers!They became treacherous deceivers, crooked and corrupt,and
        worshiped false gods in the high places,bringing low the name of God with
        every idol they erected.No wonder he was filled with jealousy and furious
        with anger!
      comments: []
    - name: '57-58: '
      title: 
      number: 57-58
      content: Like traitors turning back, they forsook him.They were even worse
        than their fathers!They became treacherous deceivers, crooked and corrupt,and
        worshiped false gods in the high places,bringing low the name of God with
        every idol they erected.No wonder he was filled with jealousy and furious
        with anger!
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: Enraged with anger, God turned his wrath on them,and he rejected his
        people with disgust.
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: God walked away from them and left his dwelling place at Shiloh,abandoning
        the place where he had lived among them,
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "allowing his emblem of strength, his glory-ark, to be captured.Enemies
        stole the very source of Israel\u2019s power."
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: God vented his rage, allowing his people to be butcheredwhen they
        went out to battle,for his anger was intense against his very own.
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: Their young men fell on the battlefield and never came back.Their
        daughters never heard their wedding songs,since there was no one left to
        marry!
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: Their priests were slaughtered and their widows were killedbefore
        they had time to weep.
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: Then all at once the Almighty awakenedas though he had been asleep.Like
        a mighty man he arose, roaring into action!
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: He blasted into battle, driving back every foe,defeating them and
        disgracing them for time and eternity.
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "He rejected Joseph\u2019s family, the tribe of Ephraim."
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: He chose instead the tribe of Judah [[COMMENT(0)]]and Mount Zion,
        which he loves.
      comments:
      - number: 78:68
        content: "  The place of God\u2019s dwelling was moved from the land of Ephraim
          (Shiloh) to the land of Judah (Jerusalem).  "
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: There he built his towering temple,strong and enduring as the earth
        itself.
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: God also chose his beloved one, David.He promoted him from caring
        for sheepand made him his prophetic servant.
      comments: []
    - name: '71-72: '
      title: 
      number: 71-72
      content: God prepared David and took this gentle shepherd-kingand presented
        him before the peopleas the one who would love and care for themwith integrity,
        a pure heart, and the anointingto lead Israel, his holy inheritance.
      comments: []
    - name: '71-72: '
      title: 
      number: 71-72
      content: God prepared David and took this gentle shepherd-kingand presented
        him before the peopleas the one who would love and care for themwith integrity,
        a pure heart, and the anointingto lead Israel, his holy inheritance.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prayer in a Time of National Disaster'
      title: Prayer in a Time of National Disaster
      number: 1
      content: "Asaph\u2019s poetic songGod, won\u2019t you do something?Barbarians
        have invaded your inheritance.Your temple of holiness has been violated,and
        Jerusalem has been left in ruins."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The corpses of your loving people are lying in the open\u2014food
        for the beasts and the birds."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The shed blood of your servants has soaked the city,with no one left
        to bury the dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Now the nearby nations heap their scorn upon us,scoffing, mocking
        us incessantly.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: How much longer, O&nbsp; <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, must we endure
        this?Does your anger have no end?Will your jealousy burn like a raging fire?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "If you\u2019re going to pour out your anger,pour it out on all these
        nations around us, not on us!They\u2019re the ones who do not love you like
        we do!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "See how they\u2019ve attacked us, consuming the land,leaving it desolate."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Please, God, don\u2019t hold the sins of our fathers against us.Don\u2019t
        make us pay for their sins.Hurry to our side, and let your tenderhearted
        mercymeet us in our need, for we are devastated beyond belief."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Our hero, come and rescue us!O&nbsp;God of the breakthrough, for the
        glory of your name,come and help us!Forgive and restore us; heal us and cover
        us in your love.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Why should all the nations sneer at us, saying,\u201CWhere is this
        God of yours?\u201DNow is the time, Lord.Show your people and all the world
        thatyou will avenge this slaughter and bloodshed once and for all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Listen, Lord! Hear the sighing of all the prisoners of war,all those
        doomed to die. Demonstrate your glory-power,and come and rescue your condemned
        children!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Lord God, take what these mocking masses have done to usand pay it
        all back to them seven times over.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Then we, your devoted lovers, will forever thank you,praising your
        name from generation to generation!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rescue and Restore'
      title: Rescue and Restore
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneAsaph\u2019s poetic song To the tune
        of \u201CYour Decrees Are like Lilies\u201DGod-Enthroned, be revealed in
        splendoras you ride upon the cherubim!How perfectly you lead us, a people
        set free. [[COMMENT(0)]]Loving shepherd of Israel\u2014listen to our hearts\u2019
        cry!Shine forth from your throne of dazzling light."
      comments:
      - number: 80:1
        content: "  Or \u201CYou lead Joseph like a flock.\u201D Joseph, as a metaphor,
          becomes a picture of the saga of God\u2019s people once imprisoned and
          now set free to rule and reign.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: In the sight of Benjamin, Ephraim, and Manasseh, [[COMMENT(0)]]stir
        up your mighty power in full display before our eyes.Break through and reveal
        yourself by coming to our rescue.
      comments:
      - number: 80:2
        content: "  The Hebrew text includes the names Ephraim (\u201Cdoubly fruitful\u201D),
          Benjamin (\u201Cson of my right hand\u201D), and Manasseh (\u201Cyou made
          me forget\u201D). These three sons of Rachel marched together behind the
          ark of glory (see  ) and became representatives of all who follow the glory
          of God. They will be \u201Cdoubly fruitful,\u201D \u201Csons of his right
          hand,\u201D and those who have \u201Cforgotten\u201D their lives in Adam.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Revive us, O&nbsp;God! Let your beaming face shine upon uswith the
        sunrise rays of glory;then nothing will be able to stop us.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: O&nbsp;God, the mighty Commander of Angel Armies,how much longer will
        you smolder in anger?How much longer will you be disgusted with your peopleeven
        when they pray?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You have fed us with sorrow and griefand made us drink our tears by
        the bowlful.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You\u2019ve made us a thorn in the side of all the neighboring lands,and
        now they just laugh at us with their mocking scorn."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Come back, come back, O&nbsp;God, and restore us!You are the Commander
        of Angel Armies.Let your beaming face shine upon us with the sunrise rays
        of glory,and then nothing will be able to stop us!
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: Remember how you transplanted us herelike a tender vine from Egypt.You
        cleared the land for your vineyard,evicting the nations from your land and
        planting us here.The roots of your vineyard went deep into the soiland filled
        the land with fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: Remember how you transplanted us herelike a tender vine from Egypt.You
        cleared the land for your vineyard,evicting the nations from your land and
        planting us here.The roots of your vineyard went deep into the soiland filled
        the land with fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: Because of your favor on your vineyard,blessing extended to every
        mountain of influence.Through this flourishing vineyard mighty ones were
        raised up.The nations were blessed by your fruitful vineyard of Israel,all
        the way from the Mediterranean Sea [[COMMENT(0)]] to the Euphrates.
      comments:
      - number: "80:10\u201311"
        content: "  This translation makes explicit the symbols in the text. The
          \u201Cvineyard\u201D is Israel, the mountains are the high places of influence
          in culture, the cedars (\u201Cmighty ones\u201D) are the mighty and powerful
          of men, and the \u201CSea\u201D speaks of the nations (sea of humanity).  "
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: Because of your favor on your vineyard,blessing extended to every
        mountain of influence.Through this flourishing vineyard mighty ones were
        raised up.The nations were blessed by your fruitful vineyard of Israel,all
        the way from the Mediterranean Sea [[COMMENT(0)]] to the Euphrates.
      comments:
      - number: "80:10\u201311"
        content: "  This translation makes explicit the symbols in the text. The
          \u201Cvineyard\u201D is Israel, the mountains are the high places of influence
          in culture, the cedars (\u201Cmighty ones\u201D) are the mighty and powerful
          of men, and the \u201CSea\u201D speaks of the nations (sea of humanity).  "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "So Lord, why have you broken downyour fence of favor around us?Trespassers
        can steal the fruit from off our vines,and now every wild beast comesbreaking
        through our wall to ravage us.You\u2019ve left us without protection!"
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "So Lord, why have you broken downyour fence of favor around us?Trespassers
        can steal the fruit from off our vines,and now every wild beast comesbreaking
        through our wall to ravage us.You\u2019ve left us without protection!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Come back, come back, O&nbsp;God to restore us!You are the Commander
        of Angel Armies.Look down from heaven and see our crisis.Come down and care
        for your lovely vineyard once again.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Nurture our root and our fruit with your loving care.Raise up the
        Branch-Man, the Son whom you\u2019ve made strong."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Enemies chopped down our vine and set it on fire;now show them your
        anger and let them perish by your frown.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Strengthen this Branch-Man, the Son of your love,the Son of Man who
        dwells at your right hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Then we will never turn back from you.Revive us again, that we may
        trust in you.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: O&nbsp;God, the mighty Commander of Angel Armies,come back and rescue
        us!Let your beaming face shine upon uswith the sunrise rays of glory.Then
        nothing will ever stop us again!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: For the Feast of Harvest'
      title: For the Feast of Harvest
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneAsaph\u2019s poetic song set to the melody
        of \u201CFor the Feast of Harvest\u201DLord, just singing about you makes
        me strong!So I\u2019ll keep shouting for joy to Jacob\u2019s God, my champion."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Let the celebration begin!I will sing with drum accompaniment and
        with the sweet soundof the harp and guitar strumming.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Go ahead! Blow the jubilee trumpet to begin the feast!Blow it before
        every joyous celebration and festival. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 81:3
        content: "  Or \u201Con the day of the new moon and the day of the full moon.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For God has given us these seasons of joy,days that the God of Jacob
        decreed for us to celebrate and rejoice.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He has given these feasts to remind us of his triumph over Egypt,when
        he went out to wage war against them.I heard the message in an unknown tongue
        as he said to me,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI have removed your backbreaking burdensand have freed your
        hands from the hard labor and toil. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 81:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cfrom holding the baskets,\u201D which alludes to the
          Hebrews carrying basket loads of burdens for their Egyptian masters.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You called out to me in your time of trouble, and I rescued you.I
        came down from the realm of the secret place of thunder,where mysteries hide.I
        came down to save you.I tested your hearts at the place where there was no
        water to drink,the place of your bitter argument with me.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]Pause
        in his presence"
      comments:
      - number: 81:7
        content: "  The Hebrew includes the word  , which means \u201Cthe place of
          strife and contention.\u201D  "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CListen to me, my dear people.For I\u2019m warning you, and
        you\u2019d better listen well!For I hold something against you."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Don\u2019t ever be guilty of worshiping any other god but me."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I am your only God, the living God.Wasn\u2019t I the one who broke
        the strongholds over youand raised you up out of bondage?Open your mouth
        with a mighty decree;I will fulfill it now, you\u2019ll see!The words that
        you speak, so shall it be!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But my people still wouldn\u2019t listen;my princely people would
        not yield to me."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: So I lifted my grace from off of their lives, and I surrendered themto
        the stubbornness of their hearts.For they were living according to their
        own selfish fantasies.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: O&nbsp;that my people would once and for all listen to meand walk
        faithfully in my footsteps, following my ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then and only then will I conquer your every foeand tell every one
        of them, \u2018You must go!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Those who hate my ways will cringe before meand their punishment will
        be eternal.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But I will feed you with my spiritual bread.You will feast and be
        satisfied with me,feeding on my revelation-truth like honeydripping from
        the cliffs of the high place.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: True Justice'
      title: True Justice
      number: 1
      content: "Asaph\u2019s poetic songAll rise! For God now comes to judgeas he
        convenes heaven\u2019s courtroom. [[COMMENT(0)]]He judges every judge and
        rules in the midst of the gods, saying,"
      comments:
      - number: 82:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe council of El.\u201D The Aramaic reads \u201CGod
          now stands in the assembly of the angels, and he will judge in their midst.\u201D  "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you judges refuse to listento the voice of true
        justice and continue to corrupt what is rightby judging in favor of the wrong?\u201DPause
        in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CDefend the defenseless, the fatherless and the forgotten,the
        disenfranchised and the destitute."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Your duty is to deliver the poor and the powerless;liberate them from
        the grasp of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But you continue in your darkness and ignorancewhile the foundations
        of society are shaken to the core!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Didn\u2019t I commission you as judges, saying,\u2018You are all
        like gods, since you judge on my behalf.You are all like sons of the Most
        High, my representatives.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Nevertheless, in death you are nothing but mere men!You will be laid
        in the ground like any prince and you will die.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All rise! For God now takes his place as judge of all the earth.Don\u2019t
        you know that everything and everyone belongs to him?The nations will be
        sifted in his hands!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God, Don\u2019t Be Silent 83The historical background to this psalm
        may be found in2&nbsp;Chron. 20:14\u201336."
      title: "God, Don\u2019t Be Silent 83The historical background to this psalm
        may be found in2&nbsp;Chron. 20:14\u201336."
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]Asaph\u2019s poetic songGod, you have to do something!
        [[COMMENT(1)]] Don\u2019t be silent and just sit idly by."
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">83</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">The historical background
          to this psalm may be found in</span>  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">.</span>    '
      - number: 83:1
        content: "  Both the Aramaic and the Septuagint add a line in verse  : \u201CGod,
          who is like you?\u201D    "
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Can\u2019t you see what they\u2019re doing?All your enemies are stirred
        up in an uproar!They despise you, Lord.In their defiant arrogance they rise
        upto host their secret council against your people.They conspire together
        to come and harmyour cherished ones\u2014your hidden ones."
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Can\u2019t you see what they\u2019re doing?All your enemies are stirred
        up in an uproar!They despise you, Lord.In their defiant arrogance they rise
        upto host their secret council against your people.They conspire together
        to come and harmyour cherished ones\u2014your hidden ones."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Our enemies keep saying,\u201CNow is the time to wipe Israel off
        the map.We\u2019ll destroy even the memory of her existence!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They\u2019ve made their pact, consulting and conspiring,aligning
        together in their covenant against God."
      comments: []
    - name: '6-8: '
      title: 
      number: 6-8
      content: "All the sons of Ishmael, the desert sheiks and the nomadic tribes,
        Amalekites, Canaanites, Moabites,and all the nations that surround us,Philistines,
        Phoenicians, Gadarenes, and Samaritans; [[COMMENT(0)]]allied together they\u2019re
        ready to attack!Pause in his presence"
      comments:
