        them by the Kishon River.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Do to your enemies what you did at Endor,whose rotting corpses fertilized
        the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "Repeat history, God! Make all their \u201Cnoble ones\u201Ddie like
        Oreb, Zebah, and Zalmunna, who said in their pride,\u201CWe will seize God\u2019s
        people along with all their pleasant lands!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "Repeat history, God! Make all their \u201Cnoble ones\u201Ddie like
        Oreb, Zebah, and Zalmunna, who said in their pride,\u201CWe will seize God\u2019s
        people along with all their pleasant lands!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Blow them away, God, like straw in the wind,like a tumbleweed in the
        wilderness!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Burn them up like a raging fire roaring down the mountainside;consume
        them all until only charred sticks remain!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Chase them away like before a mighty storm and terrifying tempest.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: O&nbsp;Lord, disgrace them until their faces fill with shame,and make
        them acknowledge the glory of your name.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Make them utter failures in everything they dountil they perish in
        total disgrace and humiliation,
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: so they will know that you, and you alone,are <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        the only Most High God exalted over all the earth!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Longing for God'
      title: Longing for God
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA prophetic song written by the prophetic
        singers of Korah\u2019s clanSet to the melody of \u201CFor the Feast of Harvest\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]God of Heaven\u2019s Armies, you find so much beauty in your
        people!They\u2019re like lovely [[COMMENT(1)]] sanctuaries of your presence."
      comments:
      - number: 84
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CFor the wine vats.\u201D    "
      - number: 84:1
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Clovely\u201D used here can also mean
          \u201Cbeloved.\u201D This translation includes both of these concepts in
          this verse.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Deep within me are these lovesick longings,desires and daydreams
        of living in union with you.When I\u2019m near you, my heart and my soulwill
        sing and worship with my joyful songs of you,my true source and spring of
        life!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "O&nbsp;Lord of Heaven\u2019s Armies, my King and my God,even the
        sparrows and swallows are welcome to build a nestamong your altars to raise
        their young."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: What pleasure fills those who live every day in your temple,enjoying
        you as they worship in your presence!Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'How enriched are they who find their strength in the Lord; [[COMMENT(0)]]within
        their hearts are the highways of holiness! '
      comments:
      - number: 84:5
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201CHow blessed is the Son of Man with you
          as his helper.\u201D      The Hebrew is literally \u201CRoads are in their
          hearts.\u201D It implies the ways [roads or \u201Chighways\u201D] that
          lead us to God\u2019s holy presence.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Even when their paths wind through the dark valley of tears,they dig
        deep to find a pleasant pool where others find only pain.He gives to them
        a brook of blessingfilled from the rain of an outpouring.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They grow stronger and stronger with every step forward,and the God
        of all gods will appear before them in Zion.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hear my cry, O&nbsp;God of Heaven\u2019s Armies!God of Jacob, listen
        to my loving prayer.Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: God, your wraparound presence is our defense.In your kindness look
        upon the faces of your anointed ones. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 84:9
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe face of your Anointed [Christ].\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For just one day of intimacy with you [[COMMENT(0)]] is likea thousand
        days of joy rolled into one!I\u2019d rather stand at the threshold in front
        of the Gate Beautiful,ready to go in and worship my God,than to live my life
        without youin the most beautiful palace of the wicked."
      comments:
      - number: 84:10
        content: "  Or \u201Cin your [temple] courts.\u201D  "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For the Lord God is brighter than the brilliance of a sunrise!Wrapping
        himself around me like a shield,he is so generous with his gifts of grace
        and glory.Those who walk along his paths with integritywill never lack one
        thing they need, for he provides it all!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O&nbsp;Lord of Heaven\u2019s Armies,what euphoria fills those who
        forever trust in you!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Mercy and Truth'
      title: Mercy and Truth
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneA prophetic song composed by the prophetic
        singers of Korah\u2019s clanLord, your love has poured outso many amazing
        blessings on our land!You\u2019ve restored Jacob\u2019s destiny from captivity."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "You\u2019ve forgiven our many sins and coveredevery one of them in
        your love.Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So now it\u2019s obvious that your blazing anger has ended andthe
        furious fire of wrath has been extinguished by your mercy."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So bring us back to loving you, God our Savior.Restore our hearts
        so that we\u2019ll never againfeel your anger rise against us."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Will you forever hold a grudge?Will your anger endure for all time?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Revive us again, O&nbsp;God! I know you will! Give us a fresh start!Then
        all your people will taste your joy and gladness.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Pour out even more of your love on us!Reveal more of your kindness
        and restore us back to you!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now I\u2019ll listen carefully for your voiceand wait to hear whatever
        you say.Let me hear your promise of peace\u2014the message every one of your
        godly lovers longs to hear.Don\u2019t let us in our ignorance turn back from
        following you."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For I know your power and presence shines on all your devoted lovers.Your
        glory always hovers over all who bow low before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Your mercy and your truth have married each other.Your righteousness
        and peace have kissed.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Flowers of your faithfulness are blooming on the earth.Righteousness
        shines down from the sky.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Yes, the Lord keeps raining down blessing after blessing,and prosperity
        will drench the land with a bountiful harvest.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For deliverance [[COMMENT(0)]] goes before him,preparing a path for
        his steps.
      comments:
      - number: 85:13
        content: "  Or \u201Crighteousness.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Prayer of Faith'
      title: A Prayer of Faith
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s prayerLord, bend down to listen to my prayer.I
        am in deep trouble. I\u2019m broken and humbled,and I desperately need your
        help."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Guard my life, for I\u2019m your faithful friend, your loyal servant
        for life.I turn to you in faith, my God, my hero; come and rescue me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Lord God, hear my constant cry for help;show me your favor and bring
        me to your fountain of grace!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Restore joy to your loving servant once again,for all I am is yours,
        O&nbsp;God.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Lord, you are so good to me, so kind in every way [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        ready to forgive,for your grace-fountain keeps overflowing,drenching all
        your devoted lovers who pray to you.
      comments:
      - number: 86:5
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CYou\u2019re my provider.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "God, won\u2019t you pay attention to this urgent cry?Lord, bend down
        to listen to my prayer."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Whenever trouble strikes, I will keep crying out to you,for I know
        your help is on the way.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "God, there\u2019s no one like you;there\u2019s no other god as famous
        as you.You outshine all others, and your miracles make it easy to know you."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Lord Almighty, you are the one who created all the nations.Look at
        them\u2014they\u2019re all on their way!Yes, the day will come when they
        all will worship youand put your glory on display."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: You are the one and only God.What miracles! What wonders! What greatness
        belongs to you!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Teach me more about you, how you work and how you move,so that I can
        walk onward in your truthuntil everything within me brings honor to your
        name.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: With all my heart and passion I will thank you, my God!I will give
        glory to your name, always and forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: You love me so much, and you have placed your greatness upon me. [[COMMENT(0)]]You
        rescued me from the deepest place of darkness,and you have delivered me from
        a certain death.
      comments:
      - number: 86:13
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "God, look at how these arrogant ones have defied me.Like a vicious
        band of violent men, they have tried to kill me.They wouldn\u2019t worry
        for a moment that they were sinning against you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But Lord, your nurturing love is tender and gentle.You are slow to
        get angry yet so swift to show your faithful love.You are full of abounding
        grace and truth. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 86:15
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic and the Septuagint.  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Bring me to your grace-fountainso that your strength becomes mine.Be
        my hero and come rescue your servant once again!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Send me a miraculous sign to show me how much you love me,so that
        those who hate me will see it and be ashamed.Don\u2019t they know that you,
        Lord, are my comforter,the one who comes to help me?"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Fountains of Delight'
      title: Fountains of Delight
      number: 1
      content: "A prophetic song composed by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s
        clanHigh upon his hills of holiness stands God\u2019s city. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 87:1
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201CHis foundations are in his holy mountains.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: How God loves the gates of Zion, his favorite place on earth. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 87:2
        content: "  Or \u201CThe Lord loves Zion\u2019s gates more than all the dwelling
          places of Jacob.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So many glorious things have been proclaimedover Zion, God\u2019s
        holy city!Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For the Lord says, \u201CHere are the nationswho will acknowledge
        me as God: [[COMMENT(0)]]Egypt,  Iraq,  Palestine,  and the Mediterranean
        people, even distant Ethiopia.They will all boast, \u2018I was born in Zion!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 87:4
        content: "  This is in anticipation of the nations of the earth coming to
          know Christ as the eternal King. See  .      Or \u201Cthe proud one,\u201D
          which is a title given to Egypt.      Or \u201CBabylon,\u201D which means
          \u201Cgate of God.\u201D      Or \u201CPhilistia,\u201D which means \u201Cland
          of sojourners.\u201D      Or \u201CTyre,\u201D which means \u201Ca rock.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But over Zion it will be said,\u201CThe mighty Man was born there,
        and he will establish it.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]For the God Most High will
        truly bless Jerusalem."
      comments:
      - number: 87:5
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Hebrew reads \u201CEach one
          is born in Zion, and the Most High makes her secure.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when he counts her citizens, recording them in his registry,he
        will write by their names: \u201CThis one was born again here!\u201DPause
        in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the princes of God\u2019s feasts will sing and dance, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        singing,\u201CEvery fountain of delight springs up from your life within
        me!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 87:7
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Save Me from This Sorrow 88This psalm has traditionally been used
        by Christians for reading on Good Friday. Many insights can be found here
        of the crucifixion of Jesus Christ.'
      title: Save Me from This Sorrow 88This psalm has traditionally been used by
        Christians for reading on Good Friday. Many insights can be found here of
        the crucifixion of Jesus Christ.
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]To the Pure and Shining OneA song, a psalm [[COMMENT(1)]]
        by the prophetic singers of Korah\u2019s clanTo the tune of \u201CPierced,\u201D
        for instruction by Heman the Ezrahite <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is the
        God who continually saves me.I weep before you night and day."
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">88</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">This psalm has traditionally
          been used by Christians for reading on Good Friday. Many insights can be
          found here of the crucifixion of Jesus Christ.</span>    '
      - number: 88
        content: "    is both a song and a psalm. The Hebrew for \u201Csong\u201D
          can also mean \u201Cwall.\u201D There are times that our purest music will
          come when we feel like we are up against a \u201Cwall.\u201D      Heman
          the Ezrahite was considered comparable to Solomon in his wisdom (). Jewish
          literature states that he was also a gifted musician and vocalist. But
          it also teaches that Heman was a leper, an outcast from society who lived
          in poverty, was shunned by all, and could not sing in the temple because
          of his disease. Read    with this background in mind.    can also be translated
          \u201CHe has been humbled more than any man.\u201D The Hebrew word for
          \u201Cinstruction\u201D () comes from a word that means \u201Cto prosper\u201D
          or \u201Cto understand.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Please bend down and listen to my sobbing,for my life is riddled with
        troublesand death is just around the corner!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Everyone sees my life ebbing out.They consider me a hopeless case
        and see me as a dead man.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They\u2019ve all left me here to die, helpless,like one who is doomed
        for death."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They\u2019re convinced you\u2019ve forsaken me,certain that you\u2019ve
        forgotten me completely\u2014abandoned, pierced, with nothing to look forward
        to but death."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They have discarded me [[COMMENT(0)]] and thrown me downinto the deepest
        darkness as into a bottomless pit.
      comments:
      - number: 88:6
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew reads \u201CYou
          have discarded me.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I feel your wrath, and it\u2019s a heavy weight upon me,drowning
        me beneath a sea of sorrow.Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Why did you turn all my friends against me?You\u2019ve made me like
        a cursed man in their eyes.No one wants to be with me now.You\u2019ve caught
        me in a trap with no way out."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Every day I beg for your help. Can\u2019t you see my tears?My eyes
        are swollen with weeping.My arms are wide, longing for mercy, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        you\u2019re nowhere to be found."
      comments:
      - number: 88:9
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Greek reads \u201CMy hands
          are stretched out to you.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: How can those who are cut off from your careeven know that you are
        there?Do departed spirits [[COMMENT(0)]] rise up to praise you?Pause in his
        presence
      comments:
      - number: 88:10
        content: "  Or \u201CRephaites.\u201D The Rephaites were giants that inhabited
          the region of Bashan east of the Jordan. See  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Who can give thanks for your love in the graveyard?Who preaches your
        faithfulness in the place of destruction?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Does death\u2019s darkness declare your miracles?How can anyone who\u2019s
        in the grave, where all is forgotten,remember how you keep your promises?"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Lord, you know my prayer before I even whisper it. [[COMMENT(0)]]At
        each and every sunrise you willcontinue to hear my cry until you answer.
      comments:
      - number: 88:13
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: O&nbsp;Lord, why have you thrown my life away?Will you keep turning
        the other way every time I call out to you?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I\u2019ve had to live in poverty and trouble all my life. [[COMMENT(0)]]Now
        I\u2019m humiliated, broken, and helpless before your terrorsand I can\u2019t
        take it anymore."
      comments:
      - number: 88:15
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Greek reads \u201Cclose
          to death all my life.\u201D  "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I\u2019m overwhelmed by your burning anger.I\u2019ve taken the worst
        you could give me,and I\u2019m speechless before you."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I\u2019m drowning beneath the waves of this sorrow,cut off with no
        one to help."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: All my loved ones and friends keep far away from me,leaving me all
        alone with only darkness as my friend.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Will You Reject Us Forever?First Poem \u2013 God\u2019s Promises
        to David"
      title: "Will You Reject Us Forever?First Poem \u2013 God\u2019s Promises to
        David"
      number: 1
      content: "Poems by Ethan the Ezrahite for instruction [[COMMENT(0)]]This forever-song
        I sing [[COMMENT(1)]] of the gentle love of God!Young and old alike will
        hear aboutyour faithful, steadfast love\u2014never failing!"
      comments:
      - number: 89
        content: '  Many scholars believe    contains four poems or stanzas. This
          translation signifies each poem with an inscription.    '
      - number: 89:1
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Csing\u201D has multiple homonyms.   
          can also mean \u201Cwall.\u201D When we feel like we are up against a wall,
          it is time to sing and see ourselves break through by faith. But    can
          also mean \u201Cto behold\u201D or \u201Cto perceive.\u201D As we sing
          to God in abandoned worship, we perceive that his glory is greater than
          the wall that stands before us. The root word of the word used here for
          \u201Csing\u201D is  , which is also the same word used for \u201Chaving
          dominion over.\u201D So many times when we sing in worship, exalting the
          loving-kindness of God, we establish dominion over any thoughts that God
          might not be faithful or that he may fail us. Sing when you feel defeated
          and watch as the walls come down and you rise to take dominion over your
          foes.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Here\u2019s my chorus: \u201CYour mercy grows through the ages. [[COMMENT(0)]]Your
        faithfulness is firm, rising up to the skies.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 89:2
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I heard the Lord say, \u201CMy covenant has been made,and I\u2019m
        committed forever to my chosen one, David."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I have made my oath that there will be sons of David forever,sons
        that are kings through every generation.\u201DPause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: Can you hear it? Heaven is filled with your praises, O&nbsp;Lord!All
        the holy ones are praising you for your miracles.The sons of God are all
        praising you for your mighty wonders.We could search the skies forever and
        never find one like you.All the mighty angels could not be compared to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: Can you hear it? Heaven is filled with your praises, O&nbsp;Lord!All
        the holy ones are praising you for your miracles.The sons of God are all
        praising you for your mighty wonders.We could search the skies forever and
        never find one like you.All the mighty angels could not be compared to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: You are a God who is greatly to be fearedas you preside over the council
        of holy ones.You are surrounded by trembling oneswho are overwhelmed with
        fear and dread,stunned as they stand in awe of you!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So awesome are you, O&nbsp; <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, Lord God
        of Angel Armies!Where could we find anyone as glorious as you?Your faithfulness
        shines all around you!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You rule over oceans and the swelling seas.When their stormy waves
        rise, you speak, and they lie still. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 89:9
        content: '  This is a prophecy of Jesus, who would one day calm the stormy
          seas. See  .    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: You crushed the strongholds of Egypt,and all your enemies were scatteredat
        the mighty display of your glory-power.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: All the heavens and everything on earth belong to you,for you are
        the Creator of all that is seen and unseen.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The four corners of the earth were put in place by you.You made the
        majestic mountainsthat are still shouting their praises to your name.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Breathtaking and awesome is your power!Astounding and unbelievableis
        your might and strength when it goes on display!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Your glorious throne rests on a foundationof righteousness and just
        verdicts.Grace and truth are the attendants who go before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'O&nbsp;Lord, how blessed are the peoplewho know the triumphant shout,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]for they walk in the radiance of your presence. '
      comments:
      - number: 89:15
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Ctriumphant shout\u201D is  , a homonym
          of the word for \u201Cbrokenness.\u201D Our triumphant shout can be powerful
          even in the midst of our brokenness.      Or \u201Cin the radiance of your
          face.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "We can do nothing but leap for joy all day long,for we know who you
        are and what you do,and you\u2019ve exalted us on high."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The glory of your splendor is our strength,and your marvelous favor
        makes us even stronger,lifting us even higher!
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Second Poem \u2013 God Keeps His Promises"
      title: "Second Poem \u2013 God Keeps His Promises"
      number: 18
      content: You are our King, the holiest one of all;your wraparound presence
        is our protection.
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "You spoke to your prophets in visions, saying,\u201CI have found
        a mighty hero for my people.I have chosen David as my loving servant and
        exalted him.I have anointed him as king with the oil of my holiness."
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "You spoke to your prophets in visions, saying,\u201CI have found
        a mighty hero for my people.I have chosen David as my loving servant and
        exalted him.I have anointed him as king with the oil of my holiness."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I will be strength to him, and I will give himmy grace to sustain
        him no matter what comes.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: None of his enemies will get the best of him,nor will the wicked one
        overpower him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For I will crush his every adversaryand do away with all who hate
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Because I love him and treasure him,my faithfulness will always protect
        him.I will place my great favor upon him,and I will cause his power and fame
        to increase.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: I will set his hand over the seaand his right hand over the rivers.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And he will come before me, saying,\u2018You truly are my Father,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] my only God, and my strong deliverer!\u2019"
      comments:
      - number: 89:26
        content: "  David was the first man in the Bible to address God as \u201Cmy
          Father.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: I am setting him apart, favoring him as my firstborn son.I will make
        him the most high king in all the earth!
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: I will love him forever and always show him kindness.My covenant with
        him will never be broken.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For I have decreed that he will always have an heir\u2014a dynasty
        that will release the days of heaven on earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '30-32: '
      title: 
      number: 30-32
      content: But if his children turn from me and forsake my words,refusing to
        walk in my truth, renouncing and violating my laws,then I will surely punish
        them for their sinswith my stern discipline until they regret it.
      comments: []
    - name: '30-32: '
      title: 
      number: 30-32
      content: But if his children turn from me and forsake my words,refusing to
        walk in my truth, renouncing and violating my laws,then I will surely punish
        them for their sinswith my stern discipline until they regret it.
      comments: []
    - name: '30-32: '
      title: 
      number: 30-32
      content: But if his children turn from me and forsake my words,refusing to
        walk in my truth, renouncing and violating my laws,then I will surely punish
        them for their sinswith my stern discipline until they regret it.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: But I will never, no never, lift my faithful love from off their lives.My
        kindness will prevail and I will never disown them.
      comments: []
    - name: '34-35: '
      title: 
      number: 34-35
      content: How could I revoke my covenant of love that I promised David?For I
        have given him my word, my holy, irrevocable word.How could I lie to my loving
        servant David?
      comments: []
    - name: '34-35: '
      title: 
      number: 34-35
      content: How could I revoke my covenant of love that I promised David?For I
        have given him my word, my holy, irrevocable word.How could I lie to my loving
        servant David?
      comments: []
    - name: "36-37: Third Poem \u2013 Why Has Our King Been Defeated?"
      title: "Third Poem \u2013 Why Has Our King Been Defeated?"
      number: 36-37
      content: "Sons of David will continue to reign on his throne,and their kingdom
        will endure as long as the sun is in the sky.This covenant will be an unbreakable
        promise thatI have established for all time.\u201DPause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: "36-37: Third Poem \u2013 Why Has Our King Been Defeated?"
      title: "Third Poem \u2013 Why Has Our King Been Defeated?"
      number: 36-37
      content: "Sons of David will continue to reign on his throne,and their kingdom
        will endure as long as the sun is in the sky.This covenant will be an unbreakable
        promise thatI have established for all time.\u201DPause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: Why have you rejected me, the one you anointed?Why would you cast
        me away?Why would you lose your temper with me?
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: You have torn up the contract you made with me, your servant.You have
        stripped away my crown [[COMMENT(0)]] and thrown it to the ground.
      comments:
      - number: 89:39
        content: "  In place of the word  , some translations render \u201Cmy dignity.\u201D  "
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: You have torn down all my walls of defenseand have made my every hiding
        place into ruins.
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: All the passersby attack and rob me while my neighbors mock!
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: Instead of fighting for me, you take the side of my enemies,even giving
        them strength to subdue me,and then watched them celebrate their victory!
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "You are no longer helping me in battle.You\u2019ve forsaken me to
        the swords of thosewho would strike me down."
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "You\u2019ve made my regal splendor to decreaseand allowed my rule
        to be overthrown."
      comments: []
    - name: "45: Fourth Poem \u2013 Save Us, God"
      title: "Fourth Poem \u2013 Save Us, God"
      number: 45
      content: "Because of you, I\u2019ve become old before my time,and I\u2019m
        publicly disgraced!Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: How long will you hide your love from me?Have you left me for good?How
        long will your anger continue to burn against me?
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Remember, Lord, I am nothing but dust,here today and so soon blown
        away.Is this all you\u2019ve created us for? For nothing but this?"
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: Which one of us will live forever?We are all mortal, terminal, for
        we will all one day die.Which one of us would ever escape our appointment
        with deathand dodge our own funeral?Pause in his presence
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: So God, where is all this love and kindness you promised us?What happened
        to your covenant with David?
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Have you forgotten how your own servants are being slandered?Lord
        God, it seems like I\u2019m carrying in my heartall the pain and abuse of
        many people."
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: They have relentlessly insulted and persecuted us,your anointed ones.
      comments: []
    - name: '52: Book 4The Numbers PsalmsPsalms of our pilgrimage on earth'
      title: Book 4The Numbers PsalmsPsalms of our pilgrimage on earth
      number: 52
      content: Nevertheless, blessed be our God forever and ever.Amen! Faithful is
        our King!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God, the Eternal'
      title: God, the Eternal
      number: 1
      content: "A prayer of Moses, God\u2019s prophetLord, you have always been our
        eternal home,our hiding place from generation to generation."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Long before you gave birth to the earthand before the mountains were
        born,you have been from everlasting to everlasting, [[COMMENT(0)]]the one
        and only true God.
      comments:
      - number: 90:2
        content: "  The Hebrew word often rendered \u201Ceternity\u201D [\u201Ceverlasting\u201D]
          is  , which can be translated \u201Cbeyond the horizon.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When you speak the words \u201CLife, return to me!\u201Dman turns
        back to dust."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "One thousand years pass before your eyeslike yesterday that quickly
        faded away,like a night\u2019s sleep soon forgotten. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 90:4
        content: "  Or \u201Clike divisions [watches] of the night.\u201D    "
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: "One day we will each be swept away into the sleep of death.We glide
        along through the tides of time\u2014so quickly gone, like a dream that fades
        at dawn, [[COMMENT(0)]]like glistening grass that springs up one dayand is
        dry and withered the next, ready to be cut down!"
      comments:
      - number: "90:5\u20136"
        content: '  A poetic description of what is implied in the context.    '
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: "One day we will each be swept away into the sleep of death.We glide
        along through the tides of time\u2014so quickly gone, like a dream that fades
        at dawn, [[COMMENT(0)]]like glistening grass that springs up one dayand is
        dry and withered the next, ready to be cut down!"
      comments:
      - number: "90:5\u20136"
        content: '  A poetic description of what is implied in the context.    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Terrified by your anger, confined beneath the curse,we live our lives
        knowing your wrath. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 90:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cworn out by your rage.\u201D Jesus has come and broken
          the curse and lifted the unbearable burden of our sins.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For all of our faults and flaws are in full view to you. [[COMMENT(0)]]Everything
        we want to hide, you search outand expose by the radiance of your face.
      comments:
      - number: 90:8
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CThe laws we have broken all stand
          before you.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: We are banished to live in the shadow of your anger.Our days soon
        become years until our lifetime comes to an end,finished with nothing but
        a sigh. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 90:9
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CAll our days have been filled with
          failures.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You\u2019ve limited our life span to a mere seventy years,yet some
        you give grace to live still longer. [[COMMENT(0)]]But even the best of years
        are marred by tears and toilsand in the end are nothing more than a gravestone
        in a graveyard! We\u2019re gone so quickly, so swiftly;we pass away and simply
        disappear."
      comments:
      - number: 90:10
        content: "  Or \u201Cif in strength eighty years.\u201D      A poetic description
          of what is implied in the context. The Septuagint has the phrase \u201Cuntil
          we mellow and accept your correction.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Lord, who fully knows the power of your passionand the intensity of
        your emotions? [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 90:11
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Hebrew can be translated
          \u201CWho could experience the strength of your anger? Who could endure
          the fear your fury can bring, and who truly comprehends the fear of God?\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Help us to remember that our days are numbered,and help us to interpret
        our lives correctly.Set your wisdom deeply in our heartsso that we may accept
        your correction. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 90:12
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Return to us again, O&nbsp;God!How much longer will it take until
        you show usyour abundant compassion?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Let the sunrise of your love end our dark night.Break through our
        clouded dawn again!Only you can satisfy our hearts,filling us with songs
        of joy to the end of our days.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "We\u2019ve been overwhelmed with grief;come now and overwhelm us
        with gladness.Replace our years of trouble with decades of delight."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Let us see your miracles again, and let the rising generationsee
        the glorious wonders you\u2019re famous for."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: O&nbsp;Lord our God, let your sweet beauty [[COMMENT(0)]] rest upon
        us.Come work with us, and then our works will endure;you will give us success
        in all we do.
      comments:
      - number: 90:17
        content: "  Or \u201Cfavor.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Safe and Secure'
      title: Safe and Secure
      number: 1
      content: When you abide under the shadow of Shaddai, [[COMMENT(0)]]you are
        hidden  in the strength of God Most High.
      comments:
      - number: 91:1
        content: "  Shaddai () is taken from a Hebrew root word with many expressive
          meanings. It can mean \u201CGod of the Mountain,\u201D \u201CGod the Destroyer
          of Enemies,\u201D \u201CGod the Self-Sufficient One,\u201D \u201CGod the
          Nurturer of Babies,\u201D or \u201CGod the Almighty.\u201D Moses the lawgiver
          is the author of this psalm, yet every verse seems to breathe the unlimited
          grace and mercy of God.      Or \u201C[I] endure through the night.\u201D
          See  , where the same Hebrew word is used for an eagle passing the night
          on the high cliffs.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He\u2019s the hope that holds me and the stronghold to shelter me,the
        only God for me, and my great confidence."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He will rescue you from every hidden trap of the enemy, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        he will protect you from false accusationand any deadly curse. '
      comments:
      - number: 91:3
        content: "  Or \u201Chunter.\u201D      As translated from the most ancient
          Hebrew manuscripts and the Septuagint. The Hebrew word can mean \u201Cpoisoned
          arrows.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: His massive arms [[COMMENT(0)]] are wrapped around you, protecting
        you.You can run under his covering of majesty and hide.His arms of faithfulness
        are a shield keeping you from harm.
      comments:
      - number: 91:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cwings.\u201D Also found in the next sentence, \u201Cunder
          his wings,\u201D which speaks not of God having wings, but of the wings
          of the cherubim resting on the mercy seat. The implication is that we can
          always come to the mercy seat and rest without fear.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You will never worry about an attack of demonic forces at nightnor
        have to fear a spirit of darkness coming against you.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Don\u2019t fear a thing!Whether by night or by day, demonic danger
        will not trouble you, [[COMMENT(0)]]nor will the powers of evil be launched
        against you."
      comments:
      - number: 91:6
        content: "  Verses    are seen by many Jewish scholars as a reference not
          merely to pestilence and natural dangers but to the realm of spiritual
          darkness that would come against God\u2019s servants. These spirits are
          equated to \u201Carrows that fly in daytime\u201D or \u201Ca pestilence
          that walks\u201D in the darkness. God\u2019s sheltered ones are kept from
          the harm that could come from natural sources or supernatural sources.
          What a wonderful place to hide and be secure!    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Even in a time of disaster, with thousands and thousands being killed,you
        will remain unscathed and unharmed.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You will be a spectator as the wicked perish in judgment,for they
        will be paid back for what they have done!
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: When we live our lives within the shadow of God Most High,our secret
        hiding place, we will always be shielded from harm.How then could evil prevail
        against us or disease infect us?
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: When we live our lives within the shadow of God Most High,our secret
        hiding place, we will always be shielded from harm.How then could evil prevail
        against us or disease infect us?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: God sends angels with special orders to protect you wherever you go,defending
        you from all harm.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If you walk into a trap, they\u2019ll be there for youand keep you
        from stumbling."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You\u2019ll even walk unharmed among the fiercest powers of darkness,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]trampling every one of them beneath your feet!"
      comments:
      - number: 91:13
        content: "  The Hebrew includes the words for \u201Clions,\u201D \u201Csnakes,\u201D
          and \u201Cdragons\u201D as the three great symbols of satanic power.  "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For here is what the Lord has spoken to me:\u201CBecause you loved
        me, delighted in me, and have been loyal to my name,I will greatly protect
        you."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I will answer your cry for help every time you pray,and you will feel
        my presencein your time of trouble.I will deliver you and bring you honor.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will satisfy you with a full life and with all that I do for you.For
        you will enjoy the fullness of my salvation!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Song of Praise'
      title: A Song of Praise
      number: 1
      content: "A song for the day of worship [[COMMENT(0)]]It\u2019s so enjoyable
        to come before youwith uncontainable praises spilling from our hearts!How
        we love to sing our praises over and over to you,to the matchless God, high
        and exalted over all!"
      comments:
      - number: 92
        content: '  Ancient Jewish tradition holds that Adam composed this psalm
          on the first Sabbath of creation, and it was to be sung by the Levites
          on the Sabbath in the temple.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "At each and every sunrise we will be thanking youfor your kindness
        and your love.As the sun sets and all through the night,we will keep proclaiming,
        \u201CYou are so faithful!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Melodies of praise will fill the air as every musical instrument,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]joined with every heart, overflows with worship.
      comments:
      - number: 92:3
        content: "  Or \u201Ca ten-stringed harp and lyre.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "No wonder I\u2019m so glad; I can\u2019t keep it in!Lord, I\u2019m
        shouting with glee over all you\u2019ve done,for all you\u2019ve done for
        me:"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "what mighty miracles and your power at work\u2014just to name a few!Depths
        of purpose and layers of meaningsaturate everything you do."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Such amazing mysteries are found within every miraclethat nearly everyone
        seems to miss.Those with no discernment can never really discoverthe deep
        and glorious secrets hidden in your ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It\u2019s true the wicked flourish, but only for a moment;they foolishly
        forget their destiny with death,that they will all one day be destroyed forevermore."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But you, O&nbsp;Lord, are exalted foreverin the highest place of endless
        glory,
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: while your opponents, the workers of wickedness,will all perish, forever
        separated from you.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Your anointing has made me strong and mighty.You\u2019ve empowered
        my life for triumph  [[COMMENT(0)]]by pouring fresh oil over me."
      comments:
      - number: 92:10
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201CI will raise my horn high like a rhinoceros
          [Hb. translated as \u201Cwild ox\u201D], and in my old age I will still
          have plenty of oil [anointing].\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "You\u2019ve said that those lying in wait to pounce on mewould be
        defeated,and now it\u2019s happened right in front of my eyes,and I\u2019ve
        heard their cries of surrender!"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Yes! Look how you\u2019ve made all your devoted loversto flourish
        like palm trees,each one growing in victory, standing with strength! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 92:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cgrowing high like a cedar in Lebanon.\u201D God makes
          us immortal and immovable.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You\u2019ve transplanted them into your heavenly courtyard,where
        they are thriving before you,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: for in your presence they will still overflow and be anointed.Even
        in their old age they will stay fresh,bearing luscious fruit and abiding
        faithfully.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Listen to them! With pleasure they still proclaim:\u201CYou\u2019re
        so good! You\u2019re my beautiful strength!You\u2019ve never made a mistake
        with me.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 92:15
        content: "  Or \u201CYou are just and never unfair.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Majesty of God'
      title: The Majesty of God
      number: 1
      content: "A Friday song composed by King David after being resettled in the
        land [[COMMENT(0)]]Look! <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> now reigns as King!He
        has covered himself with majesty and strength,wearing them as his splendor-garments.Regal
        power surrounds him as he sits securely on his throne.He\u2019s in charge
        of it all, the entire world,and he knows what he\u2019s doing!"
      comments:
      - number: 93
        content: "  This inscription is found in the Septuagint. Jews called this
          psalm \u201CThe Friday psalm.\u201D The Talmud indicates that this psalm
          was sung every Friday in the temple by the Levites.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Lord, you have reigned as King from the very beginning of time.Eternity
        is your home.
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "Chaos once challenged you.The raging waves lifted themselves over
        and over,high above the ocean\u2019s depths, letting out their mighty roar!Yet
        at the sound of your voice they were all stilled by your might.What a majestic
        King, filled with power!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "Chaos once challenged you.The raging waves lifted themselves over
        and over,high above the ocean\u2019s depths, letting out their mighty roar!Yet
        at the sound of your voice they were all stilled by your might.What a majestic
        King, filled with power!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Nothing could ever change your royal decrees;they will last forever!Holiness
        is the beauty that fills your house; [[COMMENT(0)]]you are the one who abides
        forevermore!
      comments:
      - number: 93:5
        content: "  Believers are now God\u2019s house, made holy by the blood of
          Jesus. See    and  .  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God of Vengeance'
      title: God of Vengeance
      number: 1
      content: "A Wednesday song composed by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]Lord God Almighty,
        you are the Godwho takes vengeance on your enemies.It\u2019s time for you
        to punish evil!Let your rays of revelation-light shine from your people andpierce
        the conscience of the wicked and punish them."
      comments:
      - number: 94
        content: '  This inscription is taken from the Septuagint. The Mishnah states
          that this psalm was sung by the Levites on the fourth day of the week,
          each Wednesday, in the temple.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It\u2019s time to arise as judge of all the earth;arise to punish
        the proud with the penalty they deserve!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: How much longer will you sit back and watch the wickedtriumph in their
        evil, boasting in all that is wrong?
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "Listen to them bragging among themselves,big in their own eyes, all
        because of the crimesthey\u2019ve committed against your people!See how they\u2019re
        crushing those who love you, God,cruelly oppressing those who belong to you.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "94:4\u20135"
        content: "  Or \u201C[the people of] his inheritance.\u201D (See also v. 
          .)    "
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "Listen to them bragging among themselves,big in their own eyes, all
        because of the crimesthey\u2019ve committed against your people!See how they\u2019re
        crushing those who love you, God,cruelly oppressing those who belong to you.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "94:4\u20135"
        content: "  Or \u201C[the people of] his inheritance.\u201D (See also v. 
          .)    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Heartlessly they murder the widows, the foreigners,and even the orphaned
        children.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They say to themselves, \u201CThe Lord God doesn\u2019t see this.Their
        God, the God of Jacob, he doesn\u2019t even care!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But you\u2019d better watch out, you stupid fools!You\u2019d better
        wise up! Why would you act like God doesn\u2019t exist?Do you really think
        that God can\u2019t hear their cries?"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "God isn\u2019t hard of hearing; he\u2019ll hear all their cries.God
        isn\u2019t blind. He who made the eye has superb vision,and he\u2019s watching
        all you do."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Won\u2019t the God who knows all things know what you\u2019ve done?The
        God who punishes nations will surely punish you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The Lord has fully examined every thought of manand found them all
        to be empty and futile.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Lord Yah, there\u2019s such a blessing that comeswhen you teach us
        your Word and your ways. [[COMMENT(0)]]Even the sting of your correction
        can be sweet."
      comments:
      - number: 94:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cfrom your Torah.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: It rescues us from our days of troubleuntil you are ready to punish
        the wicked. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 94:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cuntil a pit is dug for the wicked.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For the Lord will never walk away from his cherished ones,nor would
        he forsake his chosen ones who belong to him. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 94:14
        content: "  Or \u201C[the people of] his inheritance.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Whenever you pronounce judgments, they reveal righteousness. [[COMMENT(0)]]All
        your devoted lovers will be pleased. '
      comments:
      - number: 94:15
        content: "  Or \u201Cjustice will prevail.\u201D      The Hebrew reads \u201Cand
          after it [judgment] are the pure in heart.\u201D  "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Lord, who will protect me from these wicked ones?If you don\u2019t
        stand to defend me, who will? I have no one but you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I would have been killed so many timesif you had not been there for
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When I screamed out, \u201CLord, I\u2019m doomed!\u201Dyour fiery
        love was stirred, and you raced to my rescue."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Whenever my busy thoughts were out of control,the soothing comfort
        of your presencecalmed me down and overwhelmed me with delight.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "It\u2019s obvious to all; you will have nothing to dowith corrupt
        rulers who pass laws that empower eviland defeat what is right."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For they gang up against the lovers of righteousnessand condemn the
        innocent to death.
      comments: []
    - name: '22-23: '
      title: 
      number: 22-23
      content: But I know that all their evil plans will boomerang back onto them.Every
        plot they hatch will simply seal their own doom.For you, my God, you will
        destroy them,giving them what they deserve.For you are my true tower of strength,my
        safe place, my hideout, and my true shelter.
      comments: []
    - name: '22-23: '
      title: 
      number: 22-23
      content: But I know that all their evil plans will boomerang back onto them.Every
        plot they hatch will simply seal their own doom.For you, my God, you will
        destroy them,giving them what they deserve.For you are my true tower of strength,my
        safe place, my hideout, and my true shelter.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: It\u2019s Time to Sing"
      title: "It\u2019s Time to Sing"
      number: 1
      content: "Come on, everyone! Let\u2019s sing for joy to the Lord!Let\u2019s
        shout our loudest praises to our God who saved us!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Everyone come meet his face with a thankful heart.Don\u2019t hold
        back your praises;make him great by your shouts of joy!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For the Lord is the greatest of all,King-God over all other gods!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: In one hand he holds the mysteries of the earth,and in the other he
        holds the highest mountain peaks.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He\u2019s the owner of every ocean,the engineer and sculptor of earth
        itself!"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Come and kneel before this Creator-God;come and bow before the mighty
        God, our majestic maker!
      comments: []
    - name: '7-9: '
      title: 
      number: 7-9
      content: "For we are those he cares for, and he is the God we worship.So drop
        everything else and listen to his voice!For this is what he\u2019s saying:\u201CToday,
        when I speak,don\u2019t even think about turning a deaf ear to melike they
        did when they tested me at Meribah and Massah, [[COMMENT(0)]]the place where
        they argued with me, their Creator.Your ancestors challenged me over and
        over with their complaining,even though I had convinced them of my power
        and love.They still doubted my care for them."
      comments:
      - number: "95:7\u20139"
        content: "    means \u201Cstrife\u201D or \u201Cargument.\u201D    means
          \u201Ctesting.\u201D  "
    - name: '7-9: '
      title: 
      number: 7-9
      content: "For we are those he cares for, and he is the God we worship.So drop
        everything else and listen to his voice!For this is what he\u2019s saying:\u201CToday,
        when I speak,don\u2019t even think about turning a deaf ear to melike they
        did when they tested me at Meribah and Massah, [[COMMENT(0)]]the place where
        they argued with me, their Creator.Your ancestors challenged me over and
        over with their complaining,even though I had convinced them of my power
        and love.They still doubted my care for them."
      comments:
      - number: "95:7\u20139"
        content: "    means \u201Cstrife\u201D or \u201Cargument.\u201D    means
          \u201Ctesting.\u201D  "
    - name: '7-9: '
      title: 
      number: 7-9
      content: "For we are those he cares for, and he is the God we worship.So drop
        everything else and listen to his voice!For this is what he\u2019s saying:\u201CToday,
        when I speak,don\u2019t even think about turning a deaf ear to melike they
        did when they tested me at Meribah and Massah, [[COMMENT(0)]]the place where
        they argued with me, their Creator.Your ancestors challenged me over and
        over with their complaining,even though I had convinced them of my power
        and love.They still doubted my care for them."
      comments:
      - number: "95:7\u20139"
        content: "    means \u201Cstrife\u201D or \u201Cargument.\u201D    means
          \u201Ctesting.\u201D  "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So for forty long years I was grieved and disgusted by them.I described
        them as wicked wandererswhose hearts would not follow my ways or keep my
        words.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So I made a vow in my anger and declared,\u2018They will not enter
        the resting place I\u2019ve planned for them!\u2019So don\u2019t you ever
        be hard-hearted or stubborn like they were!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: King of the World'
      title: King of the World
      number: 1
      content: "Go ahead\u2014sing your new song to the Lord!Let everyone in every
        language sing him a new song. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 96:1
        content: '  Every new thing God does requires a new song to make it known.    '
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Don\u2019t stop! Keep on singing! Make his name famous!Tell everyone
        every day how wonderful he is.Give them the good news of our great Savior.Take
        the message of his glory and miracles to every nation.Tell them about all
        the amazing things he has done."
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "Don\u2019t stop! Keep on singing! Make his name famous!Tell everyone
        every day how wonderful he is.Give them the good news of our great Savior.Take
        the message of his glory and miracles to every nation.Tell them about all
        the amazing things he has done."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For the Lord\u2019s greatness is beyond description,and he deserves
        all the praise that comes to him.He is our King-God, and it\u2019s right
        to be in holy awe of him."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Other gods [[COMMENT(0)]] are absolutely worthless.For the Lord God
        is Creator-God,who spread the splendor of the skies!
      comments:
      - number: 96:5
        content: "  The Septuagint reads \u201Cdemons.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Breathtaking brilliance and awe-inspiring majestyradiate from his
        shining presence.His stunning beauty overwhelms all who come before him.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 96:6
        content: "  Or \u201CStrength and beauty are in his sanctuary.\u201D  "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Surrender to the Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, all you nations
        and peoples.Surrender to him all your pride and strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Confess that <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> alone deserves all the
        glory and honor.Bring an offering and come celebrate in his courts.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Come worship the Lord God wearing the splendor of holiness.Let everyone
        wait in wonder as they tremble in awe before him.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Tell the nations plainly that <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> rules
        over all!He is doing a great job, and nothing will disrupt him,for he treats
        everyone fair and square.
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: Let the skies sing for joy! Let the earth join in the chorus.Let oceans
        thunder and fields echo this ecstatic praiseuntil every swaying tree of every
        forest joins in,lifting up their songs of joyous praise to him!
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: Let the skies sing for joy! Let the earth join in the chorus.Let oceans
        thunder and fields echo this ecstatic praiseuntil every swaying tree of every
        forest joins in,lifting up their songs of joyous praise to him!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For here he comes, the Lord God,and he\u2019s ready to judge the
        world.He will do what\u2019s right and can be trustedto always do what\u2019s
        fair."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Rules Over All'
      title: God Rules Over All
      number: 1
      content: A psalm of David when his kingdom was established [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        now reigns as King! Let everyone rejoice!His rule extends everywhere, even
        to distant lands,and the islands of the sea, let them all be glad.
      comments:
      - number: 97
        content: '  This inscription is from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Clouds both dark and mysterious now surround him. [[COMMENT(0)]]His
        throne of glory rests upona foundation of righteousness and justice.
      comments:
      - number: 97:2
        content: '  See  ;  .  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: All around him burns a blazing glory-fire consuming all his foes.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: When his lightning strikes, it lights up the world.People are wide-eyed
        as they tremble and shake.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Mountains melt away like wax in a firewhen the Lord of all the earth
        draws near.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Heaven\u2019s messengers preach righteousness, andpeople everywhere
        see God\u2019s glory in the sky!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Shame covers all who boast in other gods, for they worship idols.For
        all the supernatural powers once worshipedthe true and living God.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But God\u2019s Zion-people are content,for they know and hear the
        truth.The people of praise rejoice over all your judgments, O&nbsp;Lord!"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For you are King-God, the Most High God over all the earth.You are
        exalted above every supernatural power!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Listen, you lovers of God! Hate evil,for God can keep you from wrongand
        protect you from the power of wickedness.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For he sows seeds of light within his devoted lovers,and seeds of
        joy burst forth for the lovers of God!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So be glad and continue to give him thanks,for God\u2019s holiness
        is seen in everything he does."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sing a New Song'
      title: Sing a New Song
      number: 1
      content: "David\u2019s poetic praise [[COMMENT(0)]]Go ahead\u2014sing your
        brand-new song to the Lord!He is famous for his miracles and marvels,for
        he is victorious through his mighty power and holy strength."
      comments:
      - number: 98
        content: "  The Septuagint has David as the author. The Hebrew reads simply
          \u201CA psalm.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Everyone knows how God has saved us,for he has displayed his justice
        throughout history.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He never forgets to show us his love and faithfulness.How kind he
        has been to Israel!All the nations know how he stands behind his peopleand
        how he saves his own.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So go ahead, everyone, and shout out your praises with joy!Break out
        of the box and let loosewith the most joyous sound of praise!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Sing your melody of praise to the Lordand make music like never before!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 98:5
        content: "  Or \u201Caccompanied by a harp and the sound of music.\u201D  "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Blow those trumpets and shofars!Shout with joyous triumph before King
        <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Let the ocean\u2019s waves join in the chorus with their roaring
        praiseuntil everyone everywhere shouts out in unison,\u201CGlory to the Lord!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Let the rivers and streams clap with applauseas the mountains rise
        in a standing ovationto join the mighty choir of exaltation.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Look! Here he comes! The Lord and judge of all the earth!He\u2019s
        coming to make things right and to do it fair and square.And everyone will
        see that he does all things well!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God of Holiness'
      title: God of Holiness
      number: 1
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is King over all! Everyone trembles
        in awe before him.He rules enthroned between the wings of the cherubim.So
        let the earth shake and quake in wonder before him!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is great and glorious in the midst
        of his Zion-people.He is exalted above all!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Let everyone praise this breathtaking God, for he is holy.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: A lover of justice is our mighty King; he is right in all his ways.He
        insists on being fair to all,promoting true justice and righteousness in
        Jacob.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: So everyone, exalt the Lord our Godfacedown before his glory-throne,
        for he is great and holy.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: God has his praying priests,like Moses, Aaron, and Samuel, who all
        interceded,asking God for help.God heard their cries and came to their rescue.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He spoke to them from the pillar of clouds,and they followed his instructions,doing
        everything he told them.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: God, the great forgiver, answered their prayers,yet he would punish
        them when they went astray.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Keep exalting the Lord our Godfacedown before his glory-throne, for
        he is great and holy!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Praise God'
      title: Praise God
      number: 1
      content: "A poetic song for thanksgivingLift up a great shout of joy to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!Go
        ahead and do it\u2014everyone, everywhere!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Worship <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> with gladness.Sing your way
        into his presence with joy!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And realize what this really means\u2014we have the privilege of
        worshiping <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> our God.For he is our Creator and
        we belong to him.We are the people of his pleasure. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 100:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe sheep of his pasture.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: You can pass through his open gates [[COMMENT(0)]] with the password
        of praise.Come right into his presence with thanksgiving.Come bring your
        thank offering to himand affectionately bless his beautiful name!
      comments:
      - number: 100:4
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cgate [doorway]\u201D is    and has
          multiple meanings. It can also mean \u201Cstorm.\u201D When you pass through
          his gates you enter into the stormy, passionate love of God. See  .  "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> is always good and ready to receive
        you.He\u2019s so loving that it will amaze you\u2014so kind that it will
        astound you!And he is famous for his faithfulness toward all.Everyone knows
        our God can be trusted,for he keeps his promises to every generation!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Integrity'
      title: Integrity
      number: 1
      content: "David\u2019s poetic praiseLord, I will sing about your faithful love
        for me.My song of praise will have your justice as its theme."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I\u2019m trying my best to walk in the way of integrity,especially
        in my own home.But I need your help!I\u2019m wondering, Lord, when will you
        appear?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I refuse to gaze on that which is vulgar.I despise works of evil peopleand
        anything that moves my heart away from you.I will not let evil hold me in
        its grip.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Every perverse and crooked way I have put away from my heart,for I
        will have nothing to do with the deeds of darkness. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 101:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cevil people.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I will silence those who secretly want to slander my friends,and I
        will not tolerate the proud and arrogant.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: My innermost circle [[COMMENT(0)]] will only be thosewho I know are
        pure and godly.They will be the only ones I allow to minister to me.
      comments:
      - number: 101:6
        content: "  Or \u201CThe faithful of the land.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "There\u2019s no room in my home for hypocrites,for I can\u2019t stand
        chronic liars who flatter and deceive."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "At each and every sunrise I will awake to do what\u2019s rightand
        put to silence those who love wickedness,freeing God\u2019s people [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>.\u201D</smallcaps>
        from their evil grip.I will do all of this because of my great love for you!  "
      comments:
      - number: 101:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe city of        This phrase, implied in the Hebrew
          text, brings conclusion to the psalm.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: From Tears to Praise'
      title: From Tears to Praise
      number: 1
      content: A prayer for those who are overwhelmed and for all the discouraged
        who come to pour out their hearts before the Lord [[COMMENT(0)]]Lord, listen
        to my prayer! Listen to my cry for help!
      comments:
      - number: 102
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "You can\u2019t hide your face from me in the day of my distress.Stoop
        down to hear my prayer and answer me quickly, Lord!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "For my days of happiness have gone up in smoke.My body is raging
        with fever, my heart is sick,and I\u2019m consumed by this illness\u2014withered
        like a dead leaf. I can\u2019t even eat."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "For my days of happiness have gone up in smoke.My body is raging
        with fever, my heart is sick,and I\u2019m consumed by this illness\u2014withered
        like a dead leaf. I can\u2019t even eat."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I\u2019m nothing but skin and bones.Nothing\u2019s left of me but
        whispered groans."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I\u2019m like a pelican of the wilderness, [[COMMENT(0)]]like an
        owl among the ruins."
      comments:
      - number: 102:6
        content: "  Ancient expositors viewed the \u201Cpelican in the wilderness\u201D
          as a reference to Christ. The famous legend and much medieval artwork taught
          that the pelican would give the gift of blood to her starving young by
          piercing her own breast with her beak, allowing her young to drink her
          blood and live. What an amazing example of sacrificial love. Augustine
          writes concerning this: \u201CThe mother wounds herself deeply and pours
          forth her blood over her young, bathed in which they recover life.\u201D
          See Augustine, \u201CExposition on the Book of Psalms,\u201D in  , ed.
          A. Cleveland Coxe and Philip Schaff (Peabody, MA: Hendrickson, 1955), 8:497.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I\u2019m sleepless, shivering in the cold, forlorn, and friendless,like
        a lonely bird on the rooftop."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: My every enemy mocks and insults me incessantly.They even use my name
        as a curse to speak over others!
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: Because of your great and furious anger against me,all I do is suffer
        with sorrow,with nothing to eat but a meal of mourning. [[COMMENT(0)]]My
        crying fills my cup with salty tears!In your wrath you have rejected me,sweeping
        me away like dirt on the floor.
      comments:
      - number: "102:9\u201310"
        content: "  Or \u201CI eat ashes as if they were bread.\u201D Ashes speak
          of mourning, for mourners would often throw dust and ashes over their heads.    "
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: Because of your great and furious anger against me,all I do is suffer
        with sorrow,with nothing to eat but a meal of mourning. [[COMMENT(0)]]My
        crying fills my cup with salty tears!In your wrath you have rejected me,sweeping
        me away like dirt on the floor.
      comments:
      - number: "102:9\u201310"
        content: "  Or \u201CI eat ashes as if they were bread.\u201D Ashes speak
          of mourning, for mourners would often throw dust and ashes over their heads.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "My days are marked by the lengthening shadows of death.I\u2019m withering
        away and there\u2019s nothing left of me."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: But then I remember that you, O&nbsp;Lord,still sit enthroned as King
        over all!The fame of your name will be revealed to every generation.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I know you are about to arise and show your tender love to Zion.Now
        is the time, Lord,for your compassion and mercy to be poured out\u2014the
        appointed time has comefor your prophetic promises to be fulfilled!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For your servants weep in sympathy over Zion\u2019s ruinsand feel
        love for her every stone."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: When you arise to intervene,all the nations and kings will be stunnedand
        will fear your awesome name, trembling before your glory!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Yes, you will reveal yourself to Zionand appear in the brightness
        of your gloryto restore her and give her children.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He responds to the prayer of the poor and brokenand will not despise
        the cry of the homeless.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Write all this down for the coming generation,so re-created people
        [[COMMENT(0)]] will read it and praise the Lord!
      comments:
      - number: 102:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cthose born anew [re-created].\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Tell them how Yah [[COMMENT(0)]] looked down from his high and holy
        place,gazing from his glory to survey the earth.
      comments:
      - number: 102:19
        content: '  Taken from  weh. Yah is often used as the name of the God of
          Power.  '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He listened to all the groaning of his people longing to be free,and
        he set loose the sons of death to experience life.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Multitudes will stream to Jerusalem topraise the Lord and declare
        his name in Zion!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Peoples from every land, their kings and kingdoms,will gather together
        to worship the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But God has brought me to my knees, shortening my life.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So I cry out to you, my God, Father of eternity,please don\u2019t
        let me die!I know my life is not yet finished."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: With your hands you once formed the foundations of the earthand handcrafted
        the heavens above.
      comments: []
    - name: '26-27: '
      title: 
      number: 26-27
      content: "They will all fade away one day like worn-out clothing,ready to be
        discarded, but you\u2019ll still be here.You will replace it all!Your first
        creation will be changed,but you alone will endure, the God of all eternity!"
      comments: []
    - name: '26-27: '
      title: 
      number: 26-27
      content: "They will all fade away one day like worn-out clothing,ready to be
        discarded, but you\u2019ll still be here.You will replace it all!Your first
        creation will be changed,but you alone will endure, the God of all eternity!"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Generation after generation our descendants will live securely,for
        you are the one protecting us, keeping us for yourself.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Our Father\u2019s Love"
      title: "Our Father\u2019s Love"
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s song of praiseWith my whole heart, with my whole
        life,and with my innermost being,I bow in wonder and love before you, the
        holy God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Yahweh, you are my soul\u2019s celebration.How could I ever forget
        the miracles of kindnessyou\u2019ve done for me?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You kissed my heart with forgiveness, in spite of all I\u2019ve done.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]You\u2019ve healed me inside and out from every disease."
      comments:
      - number: 103:3
        content: '  From this verse through the rest of the psalm, the writer used
          the second person (you). This translation has left the psalm in the first
          person to enhance the poetic nuance for the English reader.    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You\u2019ve rescued me from hell [[COMMENT(0)]] and saved my life.You\u2019ve
        crowned me with love and mercy."
      comments:
      - number: 103:4
        content: "  Or \u201Credeemed me from the pit,\u201D a term often used for
          Sheol or hell.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You satisfy my every desire with good things. [[COMMENT(0)]]You\u2019ve
        supercharged my life so that I soar again like a flying eagle in the sky!"
      comments:
      - number: 103:5
        content: "  The Hebrew text is somewhat difficult to understand. It is literally
          \u201Cwho satisfies with good ornaments.\u201D      Or \u201Cyour youth
          [implying both strength and beauty] he restores.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You\u2019re a God who makes things right,giving justice to the defenseless."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You unveiled to Moses your plansand showed Israel\u2019s sons what
        you could do."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Lord, you\u2019re so kind and tenderhearted [[COMMENT(0)]]and so
        patient with people who fail you!Your love is like a flooding riveroverflowing
        its banks with kindness. "
      comments:
      - number: 103:8
        content: "  Or \u201CLord, you\u2019re so compassionate and merciful.\u201D
          The Hebrew word for \u201Ccompassion\u201D has a homonym that means \u201Cwomb.\u201D
          The Lord carries his people like a mother carries a child in her womb.     
          See  .    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You don\u2019t look at us only to find our faults, [[COMMENT(0)]]just
        so that you can hold a grudge against us."
      comments:
      - number: 103:9
        content: "  Or \u201CYou [he] will not always fight with us [like fighting
          with enemies].\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You may discipline us for our many sins,but never as much as we really
        deserve.Nor do you get even with us for what we\u2019ve done."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Higher than the highest heavens\u2014that\u2019s how high your tender
        mercy extends!Greater than the grandeur of heaven aboveis the greatness of
        your loyal love, towering over allwho fear you and bow down before you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Farther than from a sunrise to a sunset\u2014that\u2019s how far
        you\u2019ve removed our guilt from us."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The same way a loving father feels toward his children\u2014that\u2019s
        but a sample of your tender feelings toward us, [[COMMENT(0)]]your beloved
        children, who live in awe of you."
      comments:
      - number: 103:13
        content: "  Or \u201Clike a father has deep compassion for his children.\u201D
          The Hebrew word for \u201Ctender feelings\u201D is  , which has a homonym
          that can be translated \u201Cwomb.\u201D Our Father carries you in his
          womb. What a beautiful word play that our Father has a mother\u2019s nurturing
          love for his children.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "You know all about us, inside and out. [[COMMENT(0)]]You are mindful
        that we\u2019re made from dust."
      comments:
      - number: 103:14
        content: "  The Hebrew word    can be translated \u201Cform\u201D or \u201Cframe.\u201D
          God knows our frame. But    also has a homonym that means \u201Cto be in
          distress\u201D or \u201Cto be frustrated.\u201D So this sentence could
          be translated \u201CYou know all about our frustrations and distress.\u201D
          These thoughts combined would mean that God hasn\u2019t forgotten that
          he formed us from dust and we\u2019ll experience frustrations as human
          beings. God is sympathetic to our difficulties.    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Our days are so few, and our momentary beauty [[COMMENT(0)]]so swiftly
        fades away!
      comments:
      - number: 103:15
        content: "  The Hebrew word translated \u201Cbeauty\u201D actually means
          \u201Cshining.\u201D  "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then all of a sudden we\u2019re gone,like grass clippings blown away
        in a gust of wind,taken away to our appointment with death,leaving nothing
        to show that we were here."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Lord, your endless love stretchesfrom one eternity to the other,unbroken
        and unrelenting toward those who fear youand those who bow facedown in awe
        before you.Your faithfulness to keep every gracious promise you\u2019ve madepasses
        from parents, to children, to grandchildren, and beyond."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: You are faithful to all those who follow your waysand keep your word.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Yahweh has established his throne in heaven;his kingdom rules the
        entire universe.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So bless the Lord, all his messengers of power,for you are his mighty
        heroes who listen intentlyto the voice of his word to do it.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Bless and praise the Lord, you mighty warriors,ministers who serve
        him well and fulfill his desires.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I will bless and praise the Lord with my whole heart!Let all his
        works throughout the earth,wherever his dominion stretches\u2014let everything
        bless the Lord!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Our Creator\u2019s Compassion 104This psalm, attributed to David
        in the Septuagint, can be seen as an exposition of the days of creation:
        first day: vv.1\u20132; second day: vv.3\u20134; third day: vv.5\u201317;
        fourth day: vv.18\u201323; fifth day: vv.24\u201326; sixth day: vv.27\u201330."
      title: "Our Creator\u2019s Compassion 104This psalm, attributed to David in
        the Septuagint, can be seen as an exposition of the days of creation: first
        day: vv.1\u20132; second day: vv.3\u20134; third day: vv.5\u201317; fourth
        day: vv.18\u201323; fifth day: vv.24\u201326; sixth day: vv.27\u201330."
      number: 1
      content: '[[COMMENT(0)]]Everything I am will praise and bless the Lord!O&nbsp;Lord,
        my God, your greatness takes my breath away,overwhelming me by your majesty,
        beauty, and splendor! [[COMMENT(1)]]'
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">104</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">This psalm, attributed
          to David in the Septuagint, can be seen as an exposition of the days of
          creation: first day: vv.</span>  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">;
          second day: vv.</span>  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">; third
          day: vv.</span>  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">; fourth day:
          vv.</span>  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">; fifth day: vv.</span> 
          <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">; sixth day: vv.</span>  <span
          class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">.</span>    '
      - number: 104:1
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: You wrap yourself with a shimmering, glistening light.You wear sunshine
        like a garment of glory.You stretch out the starry skies like a tapestry.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You build your balconies with light beamsand ride as King in a chariot
        you made from clouds.You fly upon the wings of the wind.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: You make your messengers into winds of the Spirit,and all your ministers
        become flames of fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You, our Creator, formed the earth,and you hold it all together so
        it will never fall apart.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: You poured the ocean depths over the planet,submerging mountains beneath.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Yet at the sound of your thunder-shoutthe waters all fled away, filling
        the deep with seas.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The mountains rose and valleys sankto the levels you decreed for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then you set a boundary line for the seasand commanded them not to
        trespass.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: You sent springs cascading through the valleys,flowing freely between
        the mountains and hills.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: You provide drink for every living thing;men and beasts [[COMMENT(0)]]
        have their thirst quenched because of you.
      comments:
      - number: 104:11
        content: "  Or \u201Cwild donkeys.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The birds build nests near the tranquil streams,chirping their joyous
        songs from the branches above.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: From your kindness you send the rain to water the mountainsfrom the
        upper rooms of your palace.Your goodness [[COMMENT(0)]] brings forth fruit
        for all to enjoy.
      comments:
      - number: 104:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cyour works.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Your compassion brings the earth\u2019s harvest, feeding the hungry.You
        cause the grass to grow for livestock,along with the fruit, grains, and vegetables
        to feed mankind."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You provide sweet wine to gladden hearts.You give us daily bread to
        sustain life,giving us glowing health for our bodies. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 104:15
        content: "  Or \u201Coil for our faces to shine.\u201D  "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The trees of the Lord drink until they\u2019re satisfied.Lebanon\u2019s
        lofty trees stand tall right where you planted them."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Within their branches you provide for birdsa place to build their
        nests;even herons find a home in the cypress trees.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: You make the high mountains a home for wild goatsand the rocky crag
        where the rock badgers burrow.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: You made the moon to mark the monthsand the sun to measure the days.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You turn off the light and it becomes night,and all the beasts of
        the forest come out to prowl.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The mighty lions roar for their dinner,but it\u2019s you, God, who
        feeds them all."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: At sunrise they slink back to their densto crouch down in the shadows.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Then man goes out to his labor and toil,working from dawn to dusk.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: O&nbsp;Lord, what an amazing variety of all you have created!Wild
        and wonderful is this world you have made,while wisdom was there at your
        side.This world is full of so many creatures, yet each belongs to you!
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And then there is the sea! So vast! So wide and deep\u2014swarming
        with countless forms of sea life, both small and great."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Trading ships glide through the high seas.And look! There are the
        massive whalesbounding upon the waves.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: All the creatures wait expectantly for youto give them their food
        as you determine.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: You come near and they all gather around,feasting from your open hands,and
        each is satisfied from your abundant supply.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: But if you were to withhold from them and turn away,they all would
        panic.And when you choose to take away their breath,each one dies and returns
        to the dust.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: When you release your Spirit-Wind, life is created,ready to replenish
        life upon the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "May God\u2019s glorious splendor endure forever!May the Lord take
        joy and pleasure in all that he has made."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For the earth\u2019s overseer has the power to make it tremble;just
        a touch of his finger and volcanoes eruptas the earth shakes and melts."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: I will sing my song to the Lord as long as I live!Every day I will
        sing my praises to God.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: May you be pleased with every sweet thought I have about you,for you
        are the source of my joy and gladness.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Now, let all the sinners be swept from the earth.But I will keep
        on praising you, my Lord, with all that is within me.My joyous, blissful
        shouts of \u201CHallelujah\u201D are all because of you!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Wonderful Works 105The first fifteen verses of this psalm
        were sung as the ark of glory was brought up to Jerusalem. See2&nbsp;Sam.
        6;1&nbsp;Chron. 13\u201316."
      title: "God\u2019s Wonderful Works 105The first fifteen verses of this psalm
        were sung as the ark of glory was brought up to Jerusalem. See2&nbsp;Sam.
        6;1&nbsp;Chron. 13\u201316."
      number: 1
      content: '[[COMMENT(0)]]Go ahead and give God thanksfor all the glorious things
        he has done!Go ahead and worship him!Tell everyone about his wonders!'
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">105</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">The first fifteen
          verses of this psalm were sung as the ark of glory was brought up to Jerusalem.
          See</span>  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">;</span>  <span
          class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">.</span>    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Let\u2019s sing his praises! Sing, and put all of his miracles to
        music!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Shine and make your joyful boast in him, you lovers of God.Let\u2019s
        be happy and keep rejoicing no matter what."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Seek more of his strength! Seek more of him!Let\u2019s always be
        seeking the light of his face."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Don\u2019t you ever forget his miracles and marvels.Hold to your
        heart every judgment he has decreed."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For you are his servants, the true seed of Abraham,and you are the
        chosen ones, Jacob\u2019s sons."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For he is the Lord our God,and his wise authority [[COMMENT(0)]] can
        be seen in all he does.
      comments:
      - number: 105:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cjudgments.\u201D    "
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: For though a thousand generations may pass away,he is still true to
        his word.He has kept every promise [[COMMENT(0)]] he made to Abraham and
        to Isaac.
      comments:
      - number: "105:8\u20139"
        content: "  Or \u201Cpromise of the covenant [pact].\u201D    "
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: For though a thousand generations may pass away,he is still true to
        his word.He has kept every promise [[COMMENT(0)]] he made to Abraham and
        to Isaac.
      comments:
      - number: "105:8\u20139"
        content: "  Or \u201Cpromise of the covenant [pact].\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: His promises have become an everlasting covenant to Jacob,as a decree
        to Jacob.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said to them, \u201CI will give you all the land of Canaanas your
        inheritance.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: They were very few in numberwhen God gave them that promise,and they
        were all foreigners to that land.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: They were wandering from one land to anotherand from one kingdom to
        another. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 105:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cfrom a kingdom to another nation.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Yet God would not permit anyone to touch them,punishing even kings
        who came against them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said to them, \u201CDon\u2019t you dare lay a hand on my anointed
        ones,and don\u2019t do a thing to hurt my prophets!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So God decreed a famine upon Canaan-land,cutting off their food supply.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But he had already sent a man ahead of his people to Egypt;it was
        Joseph, who was sold as a slave.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: His feet were bruised by strong shacklesand his soul was held by iron.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "God\u2019s promise to Joseph purged his characteruntil it was time
        for his dreams to come true."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Eventually, the king of Egypt sent for him, setting him free at last.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Then Joseph was put in charge of everything under the king;he became
        the master of the palaceover all the royal possessions.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Pharoah gave him authority over all the princes of the land,and Joseph
        became the teacher of wisdom to the king\u2019s advisers."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Jacob, with all of Joseph\u2019s family,came from Canaan to
        Egypt and settled in Goshen. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 105:23
        content: "  Or \u201Clived as a foreigner in the land of Ham [Egypt].\u201D
          Ham was a son of Noah.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: God made them very fruitful, and they multiplied incrediblyuntil they
        were greater in number than those who ruled them.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: God turned their hearts to hate his peopleand to deal treacherously
        with his servants.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: But he sent them his faithful servant, Moses, the deliverer,and chose
        Aaron to accompany him.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Their command brought down signs and wonders,working miracles in Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "By God\u2019s direction, they spoke and released a plagueof thick
        darkness over the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: God turned their rivers to blood, causing every fish to die.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And the judgment-plague of frogs came in enormous numbers,swarming
        everywhere, even into Pharaoh\u2019s bedroom!"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "God spoke and another plague was released\u2014massive swarms of
        flies, vast clouds of insects, covered the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: God rained down hail and flaming fire upon Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Their gardens and vines were all destroyed,shattering trees into splinters
        throughout the territory.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: God spoke, and devouring hordes of locusts swept over the land,
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: picking the ground clean of vegetation and crops.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Then God struck down their firstborn sons,the pride and joy [[COMMENT(0)]]
        of every Egyptian family.
      comments:
      - number: 105:36
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe beginning of all their strength.\u201D    "
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: At last, God freed all the Hebrews from their slaveryand sent them
        away laden with the silver and gold of Egypt.And not even one was feeble
        [[COMMENT(0)]] on their way out!
      comments:
      - number: 105:37
        content: "  Or \u201CNot one of his tribes was a pauper\u201D or \u201CNot
          one stumbled.\u201D  "
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: Egypt was relieved at their exodus, ready to see them go,for the terror
        of the Lord of the Hebrews had fallen upon them!
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: God spread out a cloud as shade as they moved aheadand a cloud of
        fire to light up their night.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Moses prayed and God brought them quail to eat.He satisfied them
        with heaven\u2019s bread falling from the sky."
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: He broke open the boulderand the waters poured out like a river in
        the desert.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: For God could never forgethis holy promise to his servant Abraham.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: So God brought out his chosen ones with singing;with a joyful shout
        they were set free!
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: He gave them lands and nations, just like he promised.Fruitful lands
        of crops they had never planted were now theirs.
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: All this was done for them so that they would be faithfulto keep the
        ways of God, obeying his laws and following his truths.Hallelujah! Praise
        the Lord!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Is Good'
      title: God Is Good
      number: 1
      content: Hallelujah! Praise the Lord!Everyone thank God, for he is good and
        easy to please.Your tender love for us, Lord, continues on forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Who could ever fully describe your glorious miracles?<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        who could ever praise you enough?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The happiest one on earth is the one who keeps your wordand clings
        to righteousness every moment.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So remember me, Lord, as you take joy in your people.And when you
        come to bring the blessings of salvation,don\u2019t forget me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Let me share in the wealth and beauty of all your devoted lovers,rejoice
        with your nation in all their joys,and let me share in the glory you give
        to your chosen ones.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "We have all sinned so much, just like our fathers.\u201CGuilty\u201D
        is written over our lives."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Our fathers who were delivered from Egyptdidn\u2019t fully understand
        your wonders,and they took you for granted.Over and over you showed them
        such tender love and mercy!Yet they were barely beyond the Red Seawhen they
        rebelled against you."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Nonetheless, you saved them more than onceso they would know how powerful
        you are,showing them the honor of your name.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You roared over the waters of the Red Sea,making a dry path for your
        people to cross through.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: You freed them from the strong powerof those who oppressed themand
        rescued them from bondage.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the waters rushed over their enemies and drowned them all\u2014not
        one survived."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Seeing this, the people believed your words,and they all broke out
        with songs of praise!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet how quickly they forgot your miracles of power.They wouldn\u2019t
        wait for you to act when they were hungry,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: but demanded you satisfy their cravings and give them food!They tested
        you to the breaking point.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So you gave them what they wanted to eat,but their souls starved away
        to nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They became envious of Moses and Aaron, your holy ones.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: You split open the earth, and it swallowed upDathan and Abiram along
        with their followers.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Fire fell from heaven and burnt up all the band of rebels,turning
        them to ashes.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: They made an idol of a calf at Sinaiand bowed to worship their man-made
        statue.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: They preferred the image of a grass-eating oxto the presence of the
        glory-filled God.
      comments: []
    - name: '21-22: '
      title: 
      number: 21-22
      content: They totally forgot it was you who saved themby the wonders and awesome
        miracles you worked in Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '21-22: '
      title: 
      number: 21-22
      content: They totally forgot it was you who saved themby the wonders and awesome
        miracles you worked in Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So you decided to destroy them.But Moses, your chosen leader,stood
        in the gap between you and the peopleand made intercession on their behalfto
        turn away your wrath from killing them all.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Yet they still didn\u2019t believe your wordsand they despised the
        land of delight you gave to them."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: They grumbled and found fault with everythingand closed their hearts
        to your voice.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So you solemnly swore to themthat they would all die in the desert.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And you scattered their children to distant lands to die as exiles.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then our fathers joined the worshipersof the false god named \u201CLord
        of the Pit.\u201DThey even ate the sacrifices offered to the dead!"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: All they did made you burn with anger.It made you so angry that a
        plague broke out among them!
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: It continued until Phineas intervened and executedthe guilty for causing
        judgment to fall upon them. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 106:30
        content: '  This is implicit information found in the story of Phineas ().    '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Because of this deed of righteousnessPhineas will be remembered forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Your people also provoked you to wrathat the stream called Strife.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]This is where Moses got into serious trouble!
      comments:
      - number: 106:32
        content: "  The word used here is  , the Hebrew word for \u201Cstrife\u201D
          ().  "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Because the people were rebellious against you,Moses exploded in anger
        and spoke to them out of his bitterness.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Neither did our fathers destroy the enemies in the land,as you had
        commanded them.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: But they mingled themselves with their enemiesand learned to copy
        their works of darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: They began to serve their gods and bow before their idols.All of this
        led them away from youand brought about their downfall.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: They even sacrificed their little children to the demon spirits,
      comments: []
    - name: '38-39: '
      title: 
      number: 38-39
      content: shedding the innocent blood of their sons and daughters.These dark
        practices greatly defiled the land and their own souls,through the murder
        and bloodshed of their own babies!Their sins made them spiritual adulterers
        before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '38-39: '
      title: 
      number: 38-39
      content: shedding the innocent blood of their sons and daughters.These dark
        practices greatly defiled the land and their own souls,through the murder
        and bloodshed of their own babies!Their sins made them spiritual adulterers
        before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "This is why you were furious.As your anger burned hot against them,you
        couldn\u2019t even stand to lookat your very own people any longer!"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: So you turned them over to the crushing hands of other nations,and
        those who hated them became tyrants over them.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: Oppressive enemies subdued them,ruling over them with their tyranny.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Many times you would have come to rescue them,but they continued in
        their rebellious ways,choosing to ignore your warnings.Then they sank lower
        and lower, destroyed by their depravity.
      comments: []
    - name: '44-45: '
      title: 
      number: 44-45
      content: "Yet even so, you waited and waited,watching to see if they would
        turnand cry out to you for a father\u2019s help.And then, when you heard
        their cry,you relented and you remembered your covenant,and you turned your
        heart toward them again,according to your abundant, overflowing, and limitless
        love."
      comments: []
    - name: '44-45: '
      title: 
      number: 44-45
      content: "Yet even so, you waited and waited,watching to see if they would
        turnand cry out to you for a father\u2019s help.And then, when you heard
        their cry,you relented and you remembered your covenant,and you turned your
        heart toward them again,according to your abundant, overflowing, and limitless
        love."
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: Then you caused even their oppressorsto pity them and show them compassion.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Do it again, Lord! Save us, O&nbsp;Lord, our God!Gather us from our
        exile and unite us togetherso that we will give our great and joyous thanks
        to you againand bring you glory by our praises.
      comments: []
    - name: '48: Book 5The Deuteronomy PsalmsPsalms of praise and the Word'
      title: Book 5The Deuteronomy PsalmsPsalms of praise and the Word
      number: 48
      content: "Blessed be our Lord God forever and ever.And let everyone everywhere
        say, \u201CHallelujah!\u201DAmen! Faithful is our King!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Constant Love"
      title: "God\u2019s Constant Love"
      number: 1
      content: "Let everyone give all their praise and thanks to the Lord!Here\u2019s
        why\u2014he\u2019s better than anyone could ever imagine.Yes, he\u2019s always
        loving and kind, and his faithful love never ends."
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "So, go ahead\u2014let everyone know it!Tell the world how he broke
        throughand delivered you from the power of darkness andhas gathered us together
        from all over the world.He has set us free to be his very own!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: "So, go ahead\u2014let everyone know it!Tell the world how he broke
        throughand delivered you from the power of darkness andhas gathered us together
        from all over the world.He has set us free to be his very own!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Some of us once wandered in the wilderness like desert nomads,with
        no true direction or dwelling place.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Starving, thirsting, staggering,we became desperate and filled with
        despair.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then we cried out, \u201CLord, help us! Rescue us!\u201D And he did!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He led us out by the right wayuntil we reached a suitable city to
        dwell in.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So lift your hands and thank God for his marvelous kindnessand for
        all his miracles of mercy for those he loves.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: How he satisfies the souls of thirsty onesand fills the hungry with
        goodness!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Some of us once sat in darkness,living in the dark shadows of death.We
        were prisoners to our pain, chained to our regrets.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For we rebelled against God\u2019s Wordand rejected the wise counsel
        of God Most High."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: So he humbled us through our circumstances,watching us as we stumbled,
        with no one there to pick us back up.Our own pain became our punishment.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then we cried out, \u201CLord, help us! Rescue us!\u201D And he did!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "His light broke through the darkness andhe led us out in freedom
        from death\u2019s dark shadowand snapped every one of our chains."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So lift your hands and give thanks to God for his marvelous kindnessand
        for his miracles of mercy for those he loves!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For he smashed through heavy prison doors andshattered the steel bars
        that held us back, just to set us free!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Some of us were such fools, bringing on ourselvessorrow and suffering
        all because of our sins.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Sick and feeble, unable to stand the sight of food,we drew near to
        the gates of death.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then we cried out, \u201CLord, help us! Rescue us!\u201D And he did!"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "God spoke the words \u201CBe healed,\u201D and we were healed,delivered
        from death\u2019s door!"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: So lift your hands and give thanks to God for his marvelous kindnessand
        for his miracles of mercy for those he loves!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Bring your praise as an offering and your thanks as a sacrificeas
        you sing your story of miracles with a joyful song.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Some of us set sail upon the sea to faraway ports,transporting our
        goods from ship to shore.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "We were witnesses of God\u2019s power out in the ocean deep;we saw
        breathtaking wonders upon the high seas."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: When God spoke he stirred up a storm,lifting high the waves with hurricane
        winds.
      comments: []
    - name: '26-27: '
      title: 
      number: 26-27
      content: "Ships were tossed by the swelling sea, rising to the sky,then dropping
        down to the depths,reeling like drunkards, spinning like tops,everyone at
        their wits\u2019 end until even sailors despaired of life, cringing in terror."
      comments: []
    - name: '26-27: '
      title: 
      number: 26-27
      content: "Ships were tossed by the swelling sea, rising to the sky,then dropping
        down to the depths,reeling like drunkards, spinning like tops,everyone at
        their wits\u2019 end until even sailors despaired of life, cringing in terror."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then we cried out, \u201CLord, help us! Rescue us!\u201D And he did!"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: God stilled the storm, calmed the waves,and he hushed the hurricane
        winds to only a whisper.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: We were so relieved, so glad as he guided ussafely to harbor in a
        quiet haven.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: So lift your hands and give thanks to God for his marvelous kindnessand
        for his miracles of mercy for those he loves!
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Let\u2019s exalt him on high and lift up our praises in public;let
        all the people and the leaders of the nation knowhow great and wonderful
        is <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, our God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Whenever he chooses he can dry up a riverand turn the land into a
        desert.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Or he can take a fruitful land and make it into a saltwater swamp,all
        because of the wickedness of those who dwell there.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: But he also can turn a barren wilderness into an oasis with water!He
        can make springs flow into desert lands
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: and turn them into fertile valleys so that cities spring up,and he
        gives it all to those who are hungry.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: They can plant their fields and vineyards thereand reap a bumper crop
        and gather a fruitful harvest.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: God will bless them and cause them to multiply and prosper.
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: But others will become poor,humbled because of their oppression, tyranny,
        and sorrows.
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: For God pours contempt upon their arrogant abuse of power,heaping
        scorn upon their princes,and makes them wander among ruins.
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: But he raises up the poor and lowly with his favor,giving them a safe
        place to live where no one can touch them.God will grant them a large family
        and bless them!
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: The lovers of God will rejoice when they see this.Good men are glad
        when the evil ones are silenced.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "If you are truly wise, you\u2019ll learn from what I\u2019ve told
        you.It\u2019s time for you to consider these profound lessonsof God\u2019s
        great love and mercy!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: A Prayer for God\u2019s Help"
      title: "A Prayer for God\u2019s Help"
      number: 1
      content: A poetic psalm by King DavidMy heart, O&nbsp;God, is focused and determined.Now
        I can sing my song with passionate praises!Awake, O&nbsp;my soul, with the
        music of his splendor.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Arise, my soul, and sing his praises!I will awaken the dawn with my
        worship,greeting the daybreak with my songs of light.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Wherever I go, I will thank you.All the nations will hear my praise
        songs to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Your love is so extravagant, it reaches higher than the heavens!Your
        faithfulness is so astonishing, it stretches to the skies!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Lord God, be exalted as you soar throughout the heavens.May your shining
        glory be seen high above all the earth!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Come to your beloved ones and gently draw us out.Answer our prayer
        for your saving help.Come with your might and strength, for we need you,
        Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '7-9: '
      title: 
      number: 7-9
      content: "Then I heard the Lord speak in his holy splendor,and from his sanctuary
        I heard the Lord promise:\u201CIn my triumph I will be the one to measure
        outthe portion of my inheritance to my people,and I will secure the land
        as I promised you.Shechem, Succoth, Gilead, Manasseh [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014they
        are all still mine!\u201D he says.\u201CJudah will continue to produce kings
        and lawgivers,and Ephraim will produce great warriors.Moab will become my
        lowly servant.Edom will likewise serve my purposes.I will lift up a shout
        of victory over the land of Philistia!"
      comments:
      - number: "108:7\u20139"
        content: '  The Hebrew includes two geographical places in the text: Shechem
          and Succoth. Shechem is where Jacob (Israel) first bought title to the
          land, paying one hundred pieces of silver for the place where he camped.
          Succoth is another place where Jacob temporarily camped in the Land of
          Promise. These two places speak of God being the one who brought them in
          and portioned out the land for his people.    '
