    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But who will bring my triumph into Edom\u2019s fortresses?\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 108:10
        content: '    is a variant form of the word  .  '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Lord, have you really rejected us, refusing to fight our battles?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Give us a father\u2019s help when we face our enemies.For to trust
        in any man is an empty hope."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "With God\u2019s help we will prevail with might and power.And with
        God\u2019s help we\u2019ll trample down our every foe!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God, It\u2019s Time for Vengeance"
      title: "God, It\u2019s Time for Vengeance"
      number: 1
      content: "To the Pure and Shining OneA poetic song by King DavidGod of all
        my praise, don\u2019t stand silently by, aloof to my pain,"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: while the wicked slander me with their lies.Even right in front of
        my face they lie through their teeth.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I\u2019ve done nothing to them, but they still surround mewith their
        venomous words of hatred and vitriol."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Though I love them, they stand accusing me like Satanfor what I\u2019ve
        never done.I will pray until I become prayer itself. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 109:4
        content: "  In the face of accusation and slander, David wrote in Hebrew
          literally \u201CI am prayer!\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: They continually repay me with evil when I show them good.They give
        me hatred when I show them love.
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: Show him how it feels! Let accusing liars be raised up against him,like
        Satan himself standing right next to him.And let him be declared guilty by
        a wicked judge.May even his prayers be seen as sinful!
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: Show him how it feels! Let accusing liars be raised up against him,like
        Satan himself standing right next to him.And let him be declared guilty by
        a wicked judge.May even his prayers be seen as sinful!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Shorten his life and let another replace him!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Make his wife a widow and his children orphans!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Let them wander as beggars in the street,like homeless vagabonds,
        evicted from their ruins!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Let the creditors seize his entire estate,and strangers, like vultures,
        take all that\u2019s left!"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Let no one be kind to him by showing pity to his fatherless children!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: May all his posterity die with him! Cut down his family tree!
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: And may all the sins of his ancestors be recorded,remembered before
        you, forever!Cut off even the memory of his family from the face of the earth,
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: And may all the sins of his ancestors be recorded,remembered before
        you, forever!Cut off even the memory of his family from the face of the earth,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: because he never once showed love or kindness to others,but persecuted
        the poor, the brokenhearted, and afflicted ones,even putting them to death!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Since he enjoyed cursing them,may all his curses now come raining
        back on himuntil it all overwhelms him with misfortune!Since he refused to
        bless others,God, withhold every single blessing from him!
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Bitterness, such vile vindictiveness, was upon everything he did.Cursing
        was his lifestyle.
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "So smother him now with his own curses as his just reward.This will
        be the Lord\u2019s punishment upon him andall my lying accusers who speak
        evil against me."
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "So smother him now with his own curses as his just reward.This will
        be the Lord\u2019s punishment upon him andall my lying accusers who speak
        evil against me."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But now, O&nbsp; <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>-God, make yourself
        real to melike you promised me you would. [[COMMENT(0)]]Because of your constant
        love and your heart-melting kindness, come be my hero and deliver me!
      comments:
      - number: 109:21
        content: "  The Hebrew text reads \u201Cfor your name\u2019s sake.\u201D  "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I\u2019m so broken, needy and hurting.My heart is pierced through
        and I\u2019m so wounded."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I\u2019m slipping down a dark slope, shaken to the core, and helpless."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "All my fasting has left me so weak I can hardly stand.Now I\u2019m
        shriveled up, nothing but skin and bones."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I\u2019m the example of failure and shame to all who see me.They
        just walk by me, shaking their heads."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: You have to help me, O&nbsp;Lord God!My true hero, come to my rescue
        and save me,for you are loving and kind.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then everyone will know that you have won my victory,and they will
        all say to the Lord, \u201CYou have finished it!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So let them curse me if they want,but I know you will bless me!All
        their efforts to destroy me will fail,but I will succeed and be glad.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So let my Satan-like accusers fail!Make them look ridiculous if they
        try to come against me.Clothe them with a robe of guilty shame from this
        day on!
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But I will give my thanks to you over and over,and everyone will hear
        my lavish praises.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: For you stand right next to the broken onesas their saving hero to
        rescue them from all their accusers!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Messiah, King, and Priest 110This psalm is applied to Christ in the
        New Testament, where it is quoted more often than any other Old Testament
        passage.'
      title: Messiah, King, and Priest 110This psalm is applied to Christ in the
        New Testament, where it is quoted more often than any other Old Testament
        passage.
      number: 1
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]King David\u2019s psalm<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        said to my Lord, the Messiah:\u201CSit with me as enthroned ruler [[COMMENT(1)]]while
        I subdue your every enemy.They will bow low before youas I make them a footstool
        for your feet.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">110</span>
        content: '  <span class="ChapterContent_heading__xBDcs">This psalm is applied
          to Christ in the New Testament, where it is quoted more often than any
          other Old Testament passage.</span>    '
      - number: 110:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cat my right hand.\u201D The right hand is the position
          of authority and honor.      A footstool symbolizes what is subdued. It
          is taken from the Hebrew root word \u201Cto subdue.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Messiah, I know God himself will establish your kingdomas you reign
        in Zion-glory.For he says to you, \u201CRule in the midst of your enemies!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Your people will be your love offerings.In the day of your mighty
        power you will be exalted,and in the brightness of your holy ones you will
        shineas an army arising from the womb of the dawn,anointed with the dew of
        your youth! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 110:3
        content: "  Or \u201Clike dew, your youth will come to you.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> has taken a solemn oathand will never
        back away from it, saying,\u201CYou are a priest for eternity, after the
        manner of Melchizedek!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 110:4
        content: "  Melchizedek was the name of a Canaanite king and priest over
          the Jebusite kingdom that later became Jerusalem. The name Melchizedek
          means \u201Cmy king of righteousness.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Lord stands in full authority [[COMMENT(0)]] to shatter to piecesthe
        kings who stand against youon the day he displays his terrible wrath.
      comments:
      - number: 110:5
        content: "  The Hebrew word used here for \u201CLord\u201D is    or  . It
          is the plural form of  . Jesus is called Lord of lords, and we are the
          lords that he is Lord over. We are seated at his right hand (Benjamin)
          to rule with him.  "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He will judge every rebellious nation,filling their battlefields with
        corpses,and will shatter the strongholds of ruling powers.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Yet he himself will drink from his inheritanceas from a flowing brook;refreshed
        by love he will stand victorious!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Celebrate God\u2019s Greatness"
      title: "Celebrate God\u2019s Greatness"
      number: 1
      content: Shout hallelujah to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!May every one of
        his devoted lovers hear my passionate praise to him,even among the council
        of the holy ones.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For God\u2019s mighty miracles astound me!His wonders are so delightfully
        mysteriousthat they leave all who seek them astonished."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Everything he does is full of splendor and beauty!Each miracle demonstrates
        his eternal perfection.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: His unforgettable works of surpassing wonderreveal his grace and tender
        mercy.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He satisfies all who love and trust him,and he keeps every promise
        he makes.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He reveals mighty power and marvels to his peopleby handing them nations
        as a gift.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: All God accomplishes is flawless, faithful, and fair,and his every
        word proves trustworthy and true.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They are steadfast forever and ever,formed from truth and righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "His forever-love paid a full ransom for his peopleso that now we\u2019re
        free to come before <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>to worship his holy and
        awesome name!"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Where can wisdom be found? It is born in the fear of God.Everyone
        who follows his wayswill never lack his living-understanding.And the adoration
        of God will abide throughout eternity!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Triumph of Faith'
      title: The Triumph of Faith
      number: 1
      content: Shout in celebration of praise to the Lord!Everyone who loves the
        Lord and delights in himwill cherish his words and be blessed beyond expectation.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Their descendants will be prosperous and influential.Every generation
        of the righteous will experience his favor.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Great blessing and wealth fills the house of the wise,for their integrity
        endures forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Even if darkness overtakes them,sunrise-brilliance will come bursting
        throughbecause they are gracious to others, so tender and true.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Life is good for the one who is generous and charitable,conducting
        affairs with honesty and truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Their circumstances will never shake themand others will never forget
        their example.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They will not live in fear or dread of what may come,for their hearts
        are firm, ever secure in their faith.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Steady and strong, they will not be afraid,but will calmly face their
        every foeuntil they all go down in defeat.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Never stingy and always generous to those in need,they lived lives
        of influence and honor that will never be forgotten,for they were full of
        good deeds.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But the wicked take one look at a life lived like thisand they grit
        their teeth in anger, not understanding their bliss.The wicked slink away
        speechless in the darkness that falls,where hope dies and all their dreams
        fade away to nothing,nothing at all!
      comments: []
