  - verses:
    - name: "1: I\u2019m Saved"
      title: "I\u2019m Saved"
      number: 1
      content: I am passionately in love with God because he listens to me.He hears
        my prayers and answers them.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As long as I live I\u2019ll keep praying to him,for he stoops down
        to listen to my heart\u2019s cry."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Death once stared me in the face,and I was close to slipping into
        its dark shadows.I was terrified and overcome with sorrow.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I cried out to the Lord, \u201CGod, come and save me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He was so kind, so gracious to me.Because of his passion toward me,he
        made everything right and he restored me.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So I\u2019ve learned from my experiencethat God protects the vulnerable.For
        I was broken and brought low,but he answered me and came to my rescue!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now I can say to myself and to all,\u201CRelax and rest, be confident
        and serene,for the Lord rewards fully those who simply trust in him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "God has rescued my soul from death\u2019s fearand dried my eyes of
        many tears.He\u2019s kept my feet firmly on his path"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: and strengthened me so that I may please him [[COMMENT(0)]]and walk
        before <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> in his fields of life.
      comments:
      - number: 116:9
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.  '
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: "Even when it seems I\u2019m surroundedby many liars and my own fears,and
        though I\u2019m hurting in my suffering and trauma,I still stay faithful
        to God and speak words of faith."
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: "Even when it seems I\u2019m surroundedby many liars and my own fears,and
        though I\u2019m hurting in my suffering and trauma,I still stay faithful
        to God and speak words of faith."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So now, what can I ever give back to Godto repay him for the blessings
        he\u2019s poured out on me?"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I will lift up his cup of salvation and praise him extravagantlyfor
        all that he\u2019s done for me."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I will fulfill the promise I made to Godin the presence of his gathered
        people.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When one of God\u2019s holy lovers dies,it is costly to the Lord,
        touching his heart."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Lord, because I am your loving servant,you have broken open my life
        and freed me from my chains.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now I\u2019ll worship you passionately and bring to youmy sacrifice
        of praise, drenched with thanksgiving!"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I\u2019ll keep my promise to you, God,in the presence of your gathered
        people, just like I said I would."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: I will worship you here in your living presence,in the temple in Jerusalem.I
        will worship and sing hallelujah, for I praise you, Lord!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Glorious Praise'
      title: Glorious Praise
      number: 1
      content: A praise psalmLet everyone everywhere shine with praise to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!
        [[COMMENT(0)]]Let it all out! Go ahead and praise him!
      comments:
      - number: 117:1
        content: "  The word for \u201Cpraise\u201D is taken from the Hebrew words
          for \u201Cto shine.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For he has conquered us with his great love,and his kindness has melted
        our hearts.His faithfulness lasts forever, and he will never fail you.So
        go ahead, let it all out!Praise Yah!O&nbsp;Yah! [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>;
        it is the name of God as he displays his power.</smallcaps><smallcaps>  </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: 117:2
        content: '  The name Yah is not an abbreviated form of    is found 6,830
          times in the Hebrew text, and Yah is found 49 times.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Glorious Thanksgiving'
      title: Glorious Thanksgiving
      number: 1
      content: A praise psalm [[COMMENT(0)]]Keep on giving your thanks to God, for
        he is so good!His constant, tender love lasts forever!
      comments:
      - number: 118
        content: '  This is the psalm or hymn that Jesus likely sang after the Passover
          supper with his disciples, before making his way to Gethsemane and Calvary.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Let all his princely people sing,\u201CHis constant, tender love
        lasts forever!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Let all his holy priests sing,\u201CHis constant, tender love lasts
        forever!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Let all his lovers who bow low before him sing,\u201CHis constant,
        tender love lasts forever!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Out of my deep anguish and pain I prayed,and God, you helped me as
        a father.You came to my rescue and broke open the wayinto a beautiful and
        broad place.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Now I know, Lord, that you are for me,and I will never fear what man
        can do to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For you stand beside me as my hero who rescues me.I\u2019ve seen
        with my own eyes the defeat of my enemies.I\u2019ve triumphed over them all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Lord, it is so much better to trust in you to save methan to put my
        confidence in someone else.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Yes, it is so much better to trust in the Lord to save methan to put
        my confidence in celebrities.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Once I was hemmed in and surrounded by thosewho don\u2019t love you.But
        by <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s supernatural power I overcame them
        all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "Yes, they surrounded me,like a swarm of killer bees swirling around
        me.I was trapped like one trapped by a raging fire;I was surrounded with
        no way out and at the point of collapse.But by <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s
        supernatural power, I overcame them all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "Yes, they surrounded me,like a swarm of killer bees swirling around
        me.I was trapped like one trapped by a raging fire;I was surrounded with
        no way out and at the point of collapse.But by <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s
        supernatural power, I overcame them all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: They pushed me right up to the edge, and I was ready to fall,but you
        helped me to triumph, and together we overcame them all.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Lord, you are my true strength and my glory-song,my champion, my Savior!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The joyful songs I now sing will be sung againin the hearts and homes
        of all your devoted lovers.My loud shouts of victory will echo throughout
        the land. [[COMMENT(0)]]For <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>\u2019s right hand
        conquers valiantly!"
      comments:
      - number: 118:15
        content: "  Or \u201Cin the tents of the righteous.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The right hand of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> exalts!The right hand
        of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> will never fail.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: You will not let them kill me,but I will live to tell the world what
        the Lord has done for me.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Yes, the Lord punished me as I deserved,but he\u2019ll never give
        me over to death."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Swing wide, you gates of righteousness, and let me pass through,and
        I will enter into God\u2019s presence to worship only him."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: I have found the gateway to God,the pathway to his presence for all
        his devoted lovers.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I will offer all my loving praise to you,and I thank you so much for
        answering my prayerand bringing me salvation!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The very stone the masons rejected as flawedhas turned out to be the
        most important capstone of the arch, [[COMMENT(0)]]holding up the very house
        of God.
      comments:
      - number: 118:22
        content: "  The words \u201Ccapstone of the arch\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Chead of the corner.\u201D  "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Lord himself is the one who has done this,and it\u2019s so amazing,
        so marvelous to see!"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: This is the very day of the Lord that bringsgladness and joy, filling
        our hearts with glee.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: O&nbsp;God, please come and save us again;bring us your breakthrough-victory!
      comments: []
