        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint and implied in the Hebrew.  '
    - name: '141: '
      title: 
      number: 141
      content: "Even though I\u2019m considered insignificant and despisedby the
        world, I\u2019ll never abandon your ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '142: '
      title: 
      number: 142
      content: Your righteousness has no end; it is everlasting,and your rules are
        perfectly fair.
      comments: []
    - name: '143: '
      title: 
      number: 143
      content: Even though my troubles overwhelm me with anguish,I still delight
        and cherish every message you speak to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '144: Save Me, God'
      title: Save Me, God
      number: 144
      content: Give me more revelation so that I can live for you,for nothing is
        more pure and eternal than your truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '145: '
      title: 
      number: 145
      content: "Answer my passionate prayer, O&nbsp;Lord,and I\u2019ll obey everything
        you say."
      comments: []
    - name: '146: '
      title: 
      number: 146
      content: "Save me, God, and I\u2019ll follow your every instruction."
      comments: []
    - name: '147: '
      title: 
      number: 147
      content: "Before the day dawns, I\u2019ll be crying out for helpand wrapping
        your words into my life."
      comments: []
    - name: '148: '
      title: 
      number: 148
      content: I lie awake every night pondering your promises to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '149: '
      title: 
      number: 149
      content: "Lord, listen to my heart\u2019s cry, for I know your love is real
        for me;breathe life into me again by the revelation of your justice."
      comments: []
    - name: '150: '
      title: 
      number: 150
      content: "Here they come\u2014these lawless rebels are coming near,but they
        are all so far away from your laws."
      comments: []
    - name: '151: '
      title: 
      number: 151
      content: God, you are near me always, so close to me;every one of your commands
        reveals truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '152: Breathe Life into Me Again'
      title: Breathe Life into Me Again
      number: 152
      content: "I\u2019ve known all along how true and unchangingis every word you
        speak, established forever!"
      comments: []
    - name: '153: '
      title: 
      number: 153
      content: "Look upon all my misery and come be my hero to rescue me,for I will
        never forget what you\u2019ve revealed to me."
      comments: []
    - name: '154: '
      title: 
      number: 154
      content: Take my side and defend me in these sufferings;redeem me and revive
        me, just like you promised you would.
      comments: []
    - name: '155: '
      title: 
      number: 155
      content: The wicked are so far from salvation,for they could not care less
        about your message of truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '156: '
      title: 
      number: 156
      content: Your tender mercies are what I need, O&nbsp;God;give me back my life
        againthrough the revelation of your judgments.
      comments: []
    - name: '157: '
      title: 
      number: 157
      content: "I have so many enemies who persecute me,yet I won\u2019t swerve from
        following your ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '158: '
      title: 
      number: 158
      content: I grieve when I see how the faithless ones live,for they just walk
        away from your promises.
      comments: []
    - name: '159: '
      title: 
      number: 159
      content: Lord, see how much I truly love your instructions.So in your tender
        kindness, breathe life into me again.
      comments: []
    - name: "160: Devoted to God\u2019s Word"
      title: "Devoted to God\u2019s Word"
      number: 160
      content: The sum total of all your words adds up to absolute truth,and every
        one of your righteous decrees is everlasting.
      comments: []
    - name: '161: '
      title: 
      number: 161
      content: The powerful elite have persecuted me without a cause,but my heart
        trembles in awe because of your miracle-words.
      comments: []
    - name: '162: '
      title: 
      number: 162
      content: Your promises are the source of my bubbling joy;the revelation of
        your Word thrills melike one who has discovered hidden treasure.
      comments: []
    - name: '163: '
      title: 
      number: 163
      content: I despise every lie and hate every falsehood,for I am passionate about
        keeping your precepts.
      comments: []
    - name: '164: '
      title: 
      number: 164
      content: I stop to praise you seven times a day,all because your ways are perfect!
      comments: []
    - name: '165: '
      title: 
      number: 165
      content: There is such a great peace and well-being that comesto the lovers
        of your Word, and they will never be offended.
      comments: []
    - name: '166: '
      title: 
      number: 166
      content: "Lord, I\u2019m longing for more of your salvation,for I want to do
        what pleases you."
      comments: []
    - name: '167: '
      title: 
      number: 167
      content: My love for your ways is indescribable;in my innermost being I want
        to follow them perfectly!
      comments: []
    - name: '168: I Want to Follow You'
      title: I Want to Follow You
      number: 168
      content: I will keep your instructions and follow your counsel;all my ways
        are an open book before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '169: '
      title: 
      number: 169
      content: "Lord, listen to my prayer. It\u2019s like a sacrifice I bring to
        you;I must have more revelation of your Word!"
      comments: []
    - name: '170: '
      title: 
      number: 170
      content: Take my words to heart when I ask you, Lord;rescue me, just like you
        promised!
      comments: []
    - name: '171: '
      title: 
      number: 171
      content: "I offer you my joyous praise for all that you\u2019ve taught me."
      comments: []
    - name: '172: '
      title: 
      number: 172
      content: "Your wonderful words will become my song of worship,for everything
        you\u2019ve commanded is perfect and true."
      comments: []
    - name: '173: '
      title: 
      number: 173
      content: "Place your hands of strength and favor upon me,for I\u2019ve made
        my choice to follow your ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '174: '
      title: 
      number: 174
      content: I wait for your deliverance, O&nbsp;Lord,for your words thrill me
        like nothing else!
      comments: []
    - name: '175: '
      title: 
      number: 175
      content: Invigorate my life so that I can praise you even more,and may your
        truth be my strength!
      comments: []
    - name: '176: '
      title: 
      number: 176
      content: "I\u2019ll never forget what you\u2019ve taught me, Lord,but when
        I wander off and lose my way,come after me, for I am your beloved!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Helped Me'
      title: God Helped Me
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairway [[COMMENT(0)]]I was desperate for you to help
        me in my struggles, and you did!
      comments:
      - number: 120
        content: "    all begin with the words \u201CA song to take you higher\u201D
          or \u201CA song of ascent\u201D or \u201CA song of the stairway.\u201D
          It is likely these fifteen songs were sung on the fifteen steps that would
          take the worshiper into the temple. On each step they would stop to worship
          and sing the corresponding psalm as they went up ever higher into the temple
          to worship God. Others believe they were the songs sung as David brought
          up the ark of glory to Jerusalem. They are also known as \u201CSongs of
          Degrees\u201D or \u201CSongs of Ascent.\u201D One Hebrew manuscript titles
          them \u201CSongs of the Homeward Marches.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So come and deliver me nowfrom this treachery and false accusation.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "O&nbsp;lying deceivers, don\u2019t you know what is your fate?"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: You will be pierced through with condemnationand consumed with burning
        coals of fire!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why am I doomed to live as an alien,scattered among these cruel savages?
        [[COMMENT(0)]]Am I destined to dwell in the darkened tents of desert nomads? '
      comments:
      - number: 120:5
        content: "  The Hebrew text includes the word  , which is a foreign land.
          The meaning of the word    is \u201Cto scatter\u201D and may refer to ancient
          Persia.      The Hebrew text includes the word  , who was one of Ishmael\u2019s
          sons, whose descendants became a wandering group of nomads.    means \u201Ca
          dark place.\u201D See  .  "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For too long I\u2019ve had to live among those who hate peace."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: I speak words of peace while they speak words of war,but they refuse
        to listen.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: God Protects Us'
      title: God Protects Us
      number: 1-2
      content: "A song of the stairwayI look up to the mountains and hills, longing
        for God\u2019s help.But then I realize that our true help and protectionis
        only from the Lord,our Creator who made the heavens and the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '1-2: God Protects Us'
      title: God Protects Us
      number: 1-2
      content: "A song of the stairwayI look up to the mountains and hills, longing
        for God\u2019s help.But then I realize that our true help and protectionis
        only from the Lord,our Creator who made the heavens and the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He will guard and guide me, never letting me stumble or fall.God is
        my keeper; he will never forget nor ignore me.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: He will never slumber nor sleep;he is the Guardian-God for his people,
        Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> himself will watch over you;he\u2019s
        always at your side to shelter you safely in his presence."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He\u2019s protecting you from all danger both day and night."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He will keep you from every form of evil or calamityas he continuously
        watches over you.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You will be guarded by God himself.You will be safe when you leave
        your home,and safely you will return.He will protect you now,and he\u2019ll
        protect you forevermore!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem'
      title: Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "A song of the stairway by King David [[COMMENT(0)]]I was overjoyed
        when they said,\u201CLet\u2019s go up to the house of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 122
        content: '  David wrote this song for the people to sing for the feasts.
          It was sung when the worshipers entered the gates of Jerusalem.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And now at last we stand here, inside the very gates of Jerusalem!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: O&nbsp;Jerusalem, you were built as a city of praise,where God and
        man mingle together. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 122:3
        content: "  The Hebrew phrase \u201Ca city bound together\u201D is taken
          from a root word that means \u201Cjoined, united, coupled.\u201D By inference
          in the context, it is the city where God dwells and man worships.  "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: This is where all the tribes of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> are
        requiredto come and worship him.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: This is where the thrones of kings have been establishedto rule in
        righteousness;even King David ruled from here.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Pray and seek for Jerusalem\u2019s peace,for all who love her will
        prosper!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: O&nbsp;Jerusalem, may there be peace for thosewho dwell inside your
        wallsand prosperity in your every palace.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: I intercede for the sake of my family and friendswho dwell there,
        that they may all live in peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For the sake of your house, <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> our God,I
        will seek the welfare and prosperity of Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Prayer for Mercy'
      title: A Prayer for Mercy
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayO&nbsp;God-Enthroned in heaven, I lift my eyes
        toward you in worship.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The way I love youis like the way a servant wants to please his master,the
        way a maid waits for the orders of her mistress.We look to you, our God,
        with passionate longingto please you and discover more of your mercy and
        grace.
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "For we\u2019ve had more than our fill of this scoffing and scorn\u2014this
        mistreatment by the wealthy elite.Lord, show us your mercy!Lord, show us
        your grace!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "For we\u2019ve had more than our fill of this scoffing and scorn\u2014this
        mistreatment by the wealthy elite.Lord, show us your mercy!Lord, show us
        your grace!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Victory'
      title: Victory
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairway by King DavidWhat if God had not been on our
        side? Let all Israel admit this!
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: What if God had not been there for us?Our enemies, in their violent
        anger,would have swallowed us up alive!
      comments: []
    - name: '2-3: '
      title: 
      number: 2-3
      content: What if God had not been there for us?Our enemies, in their violent
        anger,would have swallowed us up alive!
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: The nations, with their flood of rage, would have swept us away,and
        we would have drownedand perished beneath their torrent of terror!
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: The nations, with their flood of rage, would have swept us away,and
        we would have drownedand perished beneath their torrent of terror!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "We can praise God over and over that he never left us!God wouldn\u2019t
        allow the terror of our enemies to defeat us."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "We are free from the hunter\u2019s trap;their snare is broken and
        we have escaped!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For the same God who made everything,our Creator and our mighty maker,he
        himself is our helper and defender!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Surrounding Presence"
      title: "God\u2019s Surrounding Presence"
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayThose who trust in the Lord are as unshakable,as
        unmovable as mighty Mount Zion!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Just as the mountains surround Jerusalem,so the Lord\u2019s wraparound
        presencesurrounds his people, protecting them now and forever."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The wicked will not always rule over the godly,provoking them to do
        what is evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: God, let your goodness be given away to your good people,to all your
        righteous ones!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But those who turn away from truth\u2014them you will turn away from
        you, to follow their crooked ways.You will give them just what they deserve.May
        Israel experience peace and prosperity!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Restored'
      title: Restored
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayIt was like a dream come truewhen you freed
        us from our bondage and brought us back to Zion!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "We laughed and laughed and overflowed with gladness.We were left
        shouting for joy and singing your praise.All the nations saw it and joined
        in, saying,\u201CThe Lord has done great miracles for them!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Yes, he did mighty miracles and we are overjoyed!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Now, Lord, do it again! Restore us to our former glory!May streams
        of your refreshing flow over usuntil our dry hearts are drenched again.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Those who sow their tears as seeds [[COMMENT(0)]]will reap a harvest
        with joyful shouts of glee.
      comments:
      - number: 126:5
        content: "  Or \u201Csow their seeds with tears.\u201D A sower weeps when
          he sows his precious seed while his children are hungry. This is a picture
          of sacrificing what little we have for the harvest to come.  "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They may weep as they go out carrying their seed to sow,but they will
        return with joyful laughter and shouting with gladnessas they bring back
        armloads of blessing and a harvest overflowing!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God and His Gifts'
      title: God and His Gifts
      number: 1
      content: "A song of the stairway by King SolomonIf God\u2019s grace doesn\u2019t
        help the builders,they will labor in vain to build a house.If God\u2019s
        mercy doesn\u2019t protect the city,all the sentries will circle it in vain."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: It really is senseless to work so hardfrom early morning till late
        at night,toiling to make a living for fear of not having enough.God can provide
        for his devoted lovers even while they sleep!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Children are God\u2019s love-gift; they are heaven\u2019s generous
        reward."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Children born to a young couple will one day rise to protectand provide
        for their parents. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 127:4
        content: "  The Hebrew text refers to children as \u201Carrows in the hands
          of a warrior.\u201D Our children will be our future protection and provision.
          So the more the merrier!    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Happy will be the couple who has many of them!A household full of
        children will not bring shame on your namebut victory when you face your
        enemies,for your offspring will have influence and honor [[COMMENT(0)]]to
        prevail on your behalf!
      comments:
      - number: 127:5
        content: "  The Hebrew includes a reference to \u201Cspeaking with your enemies
          at the gate.\u201D This is in the context of children being God\u2019s
          way of blessing parents in their old age.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Blessings of the Lord'
      title: The Blessings of the Lord
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayHow joyous are those who love the Lord and bow
        low before God,ready to obey him!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Your reward will be prosperity, happiness, and well-being.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Your wife will bless your heart and home.Your children will bring
        you joy as they gather around your table.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yes, this is God\u2019s generous reward for those who love him."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: May the Lord bless you out of his Zion-glory!May you see the prosperity
        of Jerusalemthroughout your lifetime.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And may you be surrounded by your grandchildren.Happiness to you!
        And happiness to Israel!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Persecuted But Not Defeated'
      title: Persecuted But Not Defeated
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayLet all Israel admit it.From our very beginning
        we have been persecuted by the nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And from our very beginningwe have faced never-ending discrimination.Nevertheless,
        our enemies have not defeated us. We\u2019re still here!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: They have hurt us more than can be expressed,ripping us to shreds,
        cutting deeply into our souls.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But no matter what, the Lord is good to us.He is a righteous God who
        stood to defend us,breaking the chains of the evil ones that bound us.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: May all who hate the Jewsfall back in disgrace to a shameful defeat!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Let them be like grass planted in shallow soilthat soon withers with
        no sustenance.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Let them be like weeds ignored by the reaperand worthless to the harvester.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Let no one who sees them say,\u201CMay the blessings of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        be upon your life.May the Lord bless you.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 129:8
        content: "  In the Jewish culture, if you passed by one who was harvesting
          his crops, you would shout out, \u201CThe Lord bless you!\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Out of the Depths'
      title: Out of the Depths
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayLord, I cry out to you out of the depths of
        my despair!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Hear my voice, O&nbsp;God!Answer this prayer and hear my plea for
        mercy.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Lord, if you measured us and marked us with our sins,who would ever
        have their prayers answered?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But your forgiving love is what makes you so wonderful.No wonder you
        are loved and worshiped!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: This is why I wait upon you, expecting your breakthrough,for your
        Word brings me hope.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I long for you more than any watchmanwould long for the morning light.I
        will watch and wait for you, O&nbsp;God,throughout the night.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: O&nbsp;Israel, keep hoping, keep trusting,and keep waiting on the
        Lord,for he is tenderhearted, kind, and forgiving.He has a thousand ways
        to set you free!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He himself will redeem you;he will ransom you from the cruel slavery
        of your sins!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: My Heart Is Meek'
      title: My Heart Is Meek
      number: 1
      content: "A song of the stairway by King DavidLord, my heart is meek before
        you.I don\u2019t consider myself better than others.I\u2019m content to not
        pursue matters that are over my head\u2014such as your complex mysteries
        and wonders\u2014that I\u2019m not yet ready to understand."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I am humbled and quieted in your presence.Like a contented child
        who rests on its mother\u2019s lap, [[COMMENT(0)]]I\u2019m your resting child
        and my soul is content in you."
      comments:
      - number: 131:2
        content: "  \u201CLike a contented child\u201D is literally \u201CLike a
          weaned child.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: O&nbsp;people of God, [[COMMENT(0)]] your time has come to quietly
        trust,waiting upon the Lord now and forever.
      comments:
      - number: 131:3
        content: "  Or \u201CO&nbsp;Israel.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Dynasty"
      title: "David\u2019s Dynasty"
      number: 1
      content: "A song of the stairwayLord, please don\u2019t forget all the hardshipsDavid
        had to pass through."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And how he promised you, Jacob\u2019s mighty God, saying,"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI will not cross the threshold of my own hometo sleep in my
        own bed."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I will not sleep or slumber,nor even take time to close my eyes in
        rest,
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "until I find a place for you to dwell, O&nbsp;mighty God of Jacob.I
        devote myself to finding a resting place for you!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 132:5
        content: '  Historically, this refers to David wanting to bring the ark of
          glory back to Jerusalem.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: First we heard that the ark was at Bethlehem.Then we found it in the
        forest of Kiriath-Jearim. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 132:6
        content: "  Although the Hebrew text does not have the word    but simply 
          , this translation supplies the word    from its reference in verse  .
          For the sake of understanding the text, this translation substitutes \u201CBethlehem\u201D
          for \u201CEphrathah\u201D (Ephrathah was the ancient name for Bethlehem)
          and \u201CKiriath-Jearim\u201D for \u201CJaar\u201D (\u201Cthe fields of
          Jaar\u201D was a variant form of Kiriath-Jearim, which means \u201Cthe
          city of forests\u201D).    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Let\u2019s go into God\u2019s dwelling placeand bow down and worship
        before him."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Arise, O&nbsp;Lord, and enter your resting place,both you and the
        ark of your glorious strength!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: May your priests wear the robes of righteousness,and let all your
        godly lovers sing for joy!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Don\u2019t forsake your anointed king now,but honor your servant
        David."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For you gave your word and promised Davidin an unbreakable oath that
        one of his sonswould be sitting on the throne to succeed him as king.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You also promised that if David\u2019s sonswould be faithful to keep
        their promise to follow you,obeying the words you spoke to them,then David\u2019s
        dynasty would never end."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Lord, you have chosen Zion as your dwelling place,for your pleasure
        is fulfilled in making it your home.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I hear you say, \u201CI will make this place my eternal dwelling,for
        I have loved and desired it as my very own!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I will make Zion prosper andsatisfy her poor with my provision.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will cover my priests with salvation\u2019s power,and all my righteous
        ones will shout for joy!"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I will increase the anointing that was upon David,and my glistening
        glory will rest upon my anointed one.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I will clothe his enemies with shame,but holiness will bloom on my
        anointed one.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 132:18
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew reads \u201Chis
          crown will sparkle and gleam.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Unity'
      title: Unity
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairway by King DavidHow truly wonderful and delightful
        it isto see brothers and sisters living together in sweet unity! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 133:1
        content: '  This specifically speaks to the tribes of Israel that live in
          harmony, but it also applies to believers today. Nothing can be sweeter
          than the love of Christ we share with one another.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It\u2019s as precious as the sacred scented oilflowing from the head
        of the high priest Aaron,dripping down upon his beard and running all the
        way downto the hem of his priestly robes. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 133:2
        content: "  Or \u201Crunning down the collar of his robe.\u201D  "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: This harmony can be compared to the dewdripping from Mount Hermon,which
        flows down upon the hills of Zion.Indeed, that is where <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        has decreed his blessingswill be found, the promise of life forevermore!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Night Watch'
      title: The Night Watch
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayAll his loving priests who serve and sing,come
        and sing your song of blessing to God.Come and stand before him in the house
        of Godthroughout the night watch,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: lifting up your hands in holy worship; come and bless the Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "May the Lord, whom you worship,the mighty maker of heaven and earth,bless
        you from Zion\u2019s glory!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: His Wonderful Works'
      title: His Wonderful Works
      number: 1
      content: A song of the stairwayShout hallelujah and praise the greatness of
        God!All his righteous ones, praise him!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: All you worshiping priests on duty in the temple,
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: praise him, for he is beautiful!Sing loving praises to his lovely
        name.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> has chosen Jacob for his own purpose,and
        Israel is his special treasure.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Next to every other god, the greatness of our God is unequaled.For
        our God is incomparable!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He does what he pleases with unlimited power and authority,extending
        his greatness throughout the entire universe!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He forms the misty clouds and creates thunder and lightning,bringing
        the wind and rain out of his heavenly storehouse.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He struck down the eldest child in each Egyptian home;both man and
        beast perished that night.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He did great miracles\u2014mighty signs and wonders throughout the
        landbefore Pharaoh and all his subjects."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He conquered many nations and killed their mighty kings,
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: like Sihon, king of the Amorites, and Og, king of Bashan,and kings
        from every kingdom in Canaan.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He gave their land to Israel as an inheritance for his people.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: O&nbsp; <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, your name endures forever!Your
        fame is known in every generation.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For you will vindicate your persecuted people,showing your tender
        love to all your servants.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The unbelieving nations worship what they make.They worship their
        wealth and their work.They idolize what they own and what they do.
      comments: []
    - name: '16-18: '
      title: 
      number: 16-18
      content: "Their possessions will never satisfy.Their lifeless and futile works
        cannot bring life to them!Their things can\u2019t talk to them or answer
        their prayers.Blind men can only create blind things.Those deaf to God can
        only make a deaf image. [[COMMENT(0)]]Dead men can only create dead idols.And
        everyone who trusts in these powerless, dead thingswill be just like what
        they worship\u2014powerless and dead!"
      comments:
      - number: "135:16\u201318"
        content: "  Referring to the idols, the Hebrew could be translated \u201Cwith
          mouths, but they cannot speak; with eyes, but they cannot see; with ears,
          but they cannot hear.\u201D    "
    - name: '16-18: '
      title: 
      number: 16-18
      content: "Their possessions will never satisfy.Their lifeless and futile works
        cannot bring life to them!Their things can\u2019t talk to them or answer
        their prayers.Blind men can only create blind things.Those deaf to God can
        only make a deaf image. [[COMMENT(0)]]Dead men can only create dead idols.And
        everyone who trusts in these powerless, dead thingswill be just like what
        they worship\u2014powerless and dead!"
      comments:
      - number: "135:16\u201318"
        content: "  Referring to the idols, the Hebrew could be translated \u201Cwith
          mouths, but they cannot speak; with eyes, but they cannot see; with ears,
          but they cannot hear.\u201D    "
    - name: '16-18: '
      title: 
      number: 16-18
      content: "Their possessions will never satisfy.Their lifeless and futile works
        cannot bring life to them!Their things can\u2019t talk to them or answer
        their prayers.Blind men can only create blind things.Those deaf to God can
        only make a deaf image. [[COMMENT(0)]]Dead men can only create dead idols.And
        everyone who trusts in these powerless, dead thingswill be just like what
        they worship\u2014powerless and dead!"
      comments:
      - number: "135:16\u201318"
        content: "  Referring to the idols, the Hebrew could be translated \u201Cwith
          mouths, but they cannot speak; with eyes, but they cannot see; with ears,
          but they cannot hear.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Praise Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, all the families of Israel!Praise
        Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>, you family of Aaron! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 135:19
        content: "  The name Aaron means \u201Clight-bringer\u201D or \u201Clight-bearer.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Let all the priests [[COMMENT(0)]] bless Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!Let
        all his lovers who bow low before him praise the Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>!
      comments:
      - number: 135:20
        content: "  Or \u201Call the family of Levi.\u201D Levi represents the holy
          priesthood.      Or \u201Cthose who fear him.\u201D  "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So bless the Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> who lives in Jerusalemand
        dwells in Zion\u2019s glory!Hallelujah and praise the Lord!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: His Tender Love'
      title: His Tender Love
      number: 1
      content: Let everyone thank God, for he is good, and he is easy to please!His
        tender love for us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Give thanks to God, our King over all gods!His tender love for us
        continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Give thanks to the Lord over all lords!His tender love for us continues
        on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Give thanks to the only miracle-working God!His tender love for us
        continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Give thanks to the Creator who made the heavens with wisdom! [[COMMENT(0)]]His
        tender love for us continues on forever!
      comments:
      - number: 136:5
        content: '  See  ;  .    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: To him who formed dry ground, raising it up from the sea!His tender
        love for us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Praise the one who created every heavenly light!His tender love for
        us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He set the sun in the sky to rule over day!His tender love for us
        continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Praise him who set in place the moon and stars to rule over the night!His
        tender love for us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Give thanks to God, who struck down the firstborn in Egypt!His tender
        love for us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He brought his people out of Egypt with miracles!His tender love for
        us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: With his mighty power he brought them out!His tender love for us continues
        on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He split open the Red Sea for them!His tender love for us continues
        on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And led his people right through the middle!His tender love for us
        continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He vanquished Pharaoh\u2019s armies, drowning them all!His tender
        love for us continues on forever!"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He led his people through the wilderness!His tender love for us continues
        on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He\u2019s the one who smashed mighty kingdoms!His tender love for
        us continues on forever!"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He triumphed over powerful kings who stood in his way!His tender love
        for us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He conquered Sihon, king of the Amorites!His tender love for us continues
        on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He conquered the giant named Og, king of Bashan! [[COMMENT(0)]]His
        tender love for us continues on forever!
      comments:
      - number: 136:20
        content: "  The name Og means \u201Cgiant.\u201D  "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Then he gave away their lands as an inheritance!His tender love for
        us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For he handed it all over to Israel, his beloved!His tender love for
        us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He\u2019s the God who chose us when we were nothing!His tender love
        for us continues on forever!"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He has rescued us from the power of our enemies!His tender love for
        us continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: He provides food for hungry men and animals!His tender love for us
        continues on forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Give thanks to the great God of the heavens!His tender love for us
        continues on forever!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Our Captivity'
      title: The Song of Our Captivity
      number: 1
      content: "Along the banks of Babylon\u2019s riverswe sat as exiles, mourning
        our captivity,and wept with great love for Zion."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Our music and mirth were no longer heard, only sadness.We hung up
        our harps on the willow trees.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Our captors tormented us, saying, \u201CMake music for us andsing
        one of your happy Zion-songs!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But how could we sing the song of the Lordin this foreign wilderness?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: May my hands never make music againif I ever forget you, O&nbsp;Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: May I never be able to sing again if I fail to honor Jerusalem supremely!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Lord, may you never forgetwhat the sons of Edom did to us, saying,\u201CLet\u2019s
        raze the city of Jerusalem and burn it to the ground!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 137:7
        content: "  The Hebrew text reads \u201CStrip her [Jerusalem] naked!\u201D  "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Listen, O&nbsp;Babylon, you evil destroyer!The one who destroys you
        will be rewarded above all others.You will be repaid for what you\u2019ve
        done to us."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Great honor will come to those who destroy you and your future,by
        smashing your infants against the rubble of your own destruction.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Divine Presence'
      title: The Divine Presence
      number: 1
      content: "By King DavidI thank you, Lord, and with all the passion of my heartI
        worship you in the presence of angels! [[COMMENT(0)]]Heaven\u2019s mighty
        ones will hear my voiceas I sing my loving praise to you."
      comments:
      - number: 138:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cgods.\u201D The Hebrew    is literally \u201Cmighty
          ones\u201D and can refer to either angels or the gods of the heathen.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I bow down before your divine presenceand bring you my deepest worshipas
        I experience your tender love and your living truth.For your Word and the
        fame of your namehave been magnified above all else! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 138:2
        content: "  Or \u201CYou have exalted your Word above all your name.\u201D  "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: At the very moment I called out to you, you answered me!You strengthened
        me deep within my souland breathed fresh courage into me.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: One day all the kings of the earthwill rise to give you thanks when
        they hear the living wordsthat I have heard you speak.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: They too will sing of your wonderful ways,for your ineffable glory
        is great!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For though you are lofty and exalted,you stoop to embrace the lowly.Yet
        you keep your distance from those filled with pride.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: By your mighty power I can walk through any devastation,and you will
        keep me alive, reviving me.Your power set me free from the hatred of my enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You keep every promise you\u2019ve ever made to me!Since your love
        for me is constant and endless,I ask you, Lord, to finish every good thing
        that you\u2019ve begun in me!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: You Know All About Me'
      title: You Know All About Me
      number: 1
      content: "For the Pure and Shining OneKing David\u2019s poetic songLord, you
        know everything there is to know about me."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: You perceive every movement of my heart and soul,and you understand
        my every thought before it even enters my mind.
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "You are so intimately aware of me, Lord.You read my heart like an
        open bookand you know all the words I\u2019m about to speakbefore I even
        start a sentence!You know every step I will take before my journey even begins."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "You are so intimately aware of me, Lord.You read my heart like an
        open bookand you know all the words I\u2019m about to speakbefore I even
        start a sentence!You know every step I will take before my journey even begins."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You\u2019ve gone into my future to prepare the way,and in kindness
        you follow behind meto spare me from the harm of my past. [[COMMENT(0)]]You
        have laid your hand on me!"
      comments:
      - number: 139:5
        content: "  Or \u201CYou hem me in [lit. \u201Cbesiege me\u201D] before and
          behind.\u201D The implication is that God protects the psalmist from what
          may come in the future and what has happened in the past.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: This is just too wonderful, deep, and incomprehensible!Your understanding
        of me brings me wonder and strength. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 139:6
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. The Hebrew reads \u201Ctoo
          high to understand.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Where could I go from your Spirit?Where could I run and hide from
        your face?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If I go up to heaven, you\u2019re there!If I go down to the realm
        of the dead, you\u2019re there too!"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If I fly with wings into the shining dawn, you\u2019re there!If I
        fly into the radiant sunset, [[COMMENT(0)]] you\u2019re there waiting!"
      comments:
      - number: 139:9
        content: "  Implied in the Hebrew, which reads \u201Cthe remote parts of
          the sea\u201D or \u201Cbeyond the horizon to the west.\u201D The sea is
          west of Israel.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Wherever I go, your hand will guide me;your strength will empower
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "It\u2019s impossible to disappear from youor to ask the darkness
        to hide me,for your presence is everywhere, bringing light into my night."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "There is no such thing as darkness with you.The night, to you, is
        as bright as the day;there\u2019s no difference between the two."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You formed my innermost being, shaping my delicate insideand my intricate
        outside,and wove them all together in my mother\u2019s womb. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 139:13
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cknit\u201D or \u201Cwove\u201D can
          also be translated \u201Ccovered\u201D or \u201Cdefended.\u201D God places
          an eternal spirit inside the conceived child within the womb of a mother
          and covers that life, sends the child a guardian angel, and watches over
          him or her.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I thank you, God, for making me so mysteriously complex!Everything
        you do is marvelously breathtaking.It simply amazes me to think about it!How
        thoroughly you know me, Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You even formed every bone in my bodywhen you created me in the secret
        place; [[COMMENT(0)]]carefully, skillfully you shaped me  from nothing to
        something.
      comments:
      - number: 139:15
        content: "  The Hebrew text is literally \u201Cthe depths of the earth.\u201D     
          Or \u201Cembroidered me.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "You saw who you created me to be before I became me! [[COMMENT(0)]]Before
        I\u2019d ever seen the light of day,the number of days you planned for mewere
