      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Protect me! Keep me from the traps of wickedness they set for me.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Let them all stumble into their own trapswhile I escape without a
        scratch!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: My Only Hope'
      title: My Only Hope
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic song of instructionA prayer when he was
        confined in a caveGod, I\u2019m crying out to you!I lift up my voice boldly
        to beg for your mercy."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I spill out my heart to you and tell you all my troubles.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For when I was desperate, overwhelmed, and about to give up,you were
        the only one there to help.You gave me a way of escapefrom the hidden traps
        of my enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I look to my left and right to see if there is anyone who will help,but
        there\u2019s no one who takes notice of me.I have no hope of escape, and
        no one cares whether I live or die."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So I cried out to you, Lord, my only hiding place.You\u2019re all
        I have, my only hope in this life,my last chance for help."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Please listen to my heart\u2019s cry,for I am low and in desperate
        need of you!Rescue me from all those who persecute me,for I am no match for
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Bring me out of this dungeon so I can declare your praise!And all
        the righteous will celebrateall the wonderful things you\u2019ve done for
        me!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: My Humble Prayer'
      title: My Humble Prayer
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic song when he was chased by Absalom [[COMMENT(0)]]Lord,
        you must hear my prayer,for you are faithful to your promises.Answer my cry,
        O&nbsp;righteous God!"
      comments:
      - number: 143
        content: '  As translated from the Septuagint.  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Don\u2019t bring me into your courtroom for judgment,for there is
        no one who is righteous before you."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "My enemies have chased and caught meand crushed my life into dust.Now
        I\u2019m living in the darkness of death\u2019s shadow."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: My inner being is in depressionand my heart is heavy, dazed with despair.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I remember the glorious miracles of days gone by,and I often think
        of all the wonders of old.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now I\u2019m reaching out to you, thirsting for youlike the dry,
        cracked ground thirsts for rain.Pause in his presence"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Lord, come quickly and answer me,for my depression deepens and I\u2019m
        about to give up.Don\u2019t leave me now or I\u2019ll die!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Let the dawning day bring me revelationof your tender, unfailing love.Give
        me light for my path and teach me, for I trust in you.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Save me from all my enemies, for I hide myself in you.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I just want to obey all you ask of me.So teach me, Lord, for you are
        my God.Your gracious Spirit is all I need, so lead me on good pathsthat are
        pleasing to you, my one and only God!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Lord, if you rescue me, it will bring you more glory,for you are true
        to your promises.Bring me out of these troubles!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Since I am your loving servant, destroy all thosewho are trying to
        harm me.And because you are so loving and kind to me,silence all of my enemies!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rescue Me'
      title: Rescue Me
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic song as he stood before Goliath [[COMMENT(0)]]There
        is only one strong, safe, and secure place for me;it\u2019s in God alone
        who gives me strength for the battle."
      comments:
      - number: 144
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint. Put yourself in David\u2019s
          place as he faced a giant named Goliath. Imagine how he felt as you read
          through this psalm.  "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He\u2019s my shelter of love and my fortress of faith,who wraps himself
        around me as a secure shield.I hide myself in this one who subdues enemies
        before me."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Lord, what is it about us that you would even notice us?Why do you
        even bother with us?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For man is nothing but a faint whisper, a mere breath.We spend our
        days like nothing more than a passing shadow.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Step down from heaven, Lord, and come down!Make the mountains melt
        at your touch.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Loose your fiery lightning flashes and scatter your enemies.Overthrow
        them with your terrifying judgments.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Reach down from your heavensand rescue me from this helland deliver
        me from these dark powers.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They speak nothing but lies; their words are pure deceit.Nothing they
        say can ever be trusted.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: My God, I will sing you a brand-new song!The harp inside my heart
        will make music to you!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I will sing of you, the one who gives victory to kings\u2014the one
        who rescues David, your loving servant,from the fatal sword."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Deliver me and save me from these dark powerswho speak nothing but
        lies.Their words are pure deceit,and you can\u2019t trust anything they say."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Deliver us! Then our homes will be happy.Our sons will grow up as
        strong, sturdy menand our daughters with graceful beauty,royally fashioned
        as for a palace.
      comments: []
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "Our barns will be filled to the brim,overflowing with the fruits
        of our harvest.Our fields will be full of sheep and cattle,too many to count,and
        our livestock will not miscarry their young.Our enemies will not invade our
        land,and there\u2019ll be no breach in our walls."
      comments: []
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "Our barns will be filled to the brim,overflowing with the fruits
        of our harvest.Our fields will be full of sheep and cattle,too many to count,and
        our livestock will not miscarry their young.Our enemies will not invade our
        land,and there\u2019ll be no breach in our walls."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: What bliss we experience when these blessings fall!The people who
        love and serve our God will be happy indeed!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Greatness"
      title: "God\u2019s Greatness"
      number: 1
      content: "King David\u2019s poetic song of praiseMy heart explodes with praise
        to you!Now and forever my heart bows in worship to you,my King and my God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Every day I will lift up my praise to your namewith praises that will
        last throughout eternity.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Lord, you are great and worthy of the highest praise!For there is
        no end to the discoveryof the greatness that surrounds you.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Generation after generation will declare more of your greatnessand
        declare more of your glory.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Your magnificent splendor and the miracles of your majestyare my constant
        meditation.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Your awe-inspiring acts of power have everyone talking!I\u2019m telling
        people everywhere about your excellent greatness!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Our hearts bubble over as we celebrate the fameof your marvelous beauty,
        bringing bliss to our hearts.We shout with ecstatic joy over your breakthrough
        for us.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You\u2019re kind and tenderhearted to those who don\u2019t deserve
        itand very patient with people who fail you.Your love is like a flooding
        river overflowing its banks with kindness."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: God, everyone sees your goodness,for your tender love is blended into
        everything you do.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Everything you have made will praise you, fulfilling its purpose.And
        all your godly ones will be found bowing before you.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: They will tell the world of the lavish splendor of your kingdomand
        preach about your limitless power.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: They will demonstrate for all to see your miracles of mightand reveal
        the glorious majesty of your kingdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You are the Lord who reigns over your never-ending kingdom through
        all the ages of time and eternity!You are faithful to fulfill every promise
        you\u2019ve made.You manifest yourself as kindness in all you do. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 145:13
        content: "  The last two lines of this verse are only found in one reliable
          Hebrew manuscript and in the Septuagint. It could also be translated \u201CAll
          your works are very holy.\u201D  "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Weak and feeble ones you will sustain.Those bent over with burdens
        of shame you will lift up.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You have captured our attentionand the eyes of all look to you.You
        give what they hunger for at just the right time.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When you open your generous hand, it\u2019s full of blessings,satisfying
        the longings of every living thing."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: You are fair and righteous in everything you do,and your love is wrapped
        into all your works.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: You draw near to those who call out to you,listening closely, especially
        when their hearts are true.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Every godly one receiveseven more than what they ask for.For you hear
        what their hearts really long for,and you bring them your saving strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: God, you watch carefully over all your devoted lovers like a bodyguard,but
        you will destroy the ungodly.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I will praise you, Lord!Let everyone everywhere join me in praisingthe
        beautiful Lord of holiness from now through eternity!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Our True Help'
      title: Our True Help
      number: 1
      content: A poetic psalm by Haggai and Zechariah [[COMMENT(0)]]Hallelujah! Praise
        the Lord!My innermost being will praise you, Lord!
      comments:
      - number: 146
        content: "  As translated from the Septuagint.    are called \u201CHallelujah
          Psalms\u201D because they all begin in Hebrew with the words \u201CHallelujah,
          praise the Lord.\u201D  "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I will spend my life praising you andsinging high praises to you,
        my God, every day of my life!
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "We can never look to men for help;no matter who they are, they can\u2019t
        save us,for even our great leaders fail and fall.They too are just mortals
        who will one day die.At death the spirits of all depart and their bodies
        return to dust.In the day of their death all their projects and plans are
        over."
      comments: []
    - name: '3-4: '
      title: 
      number: 3-4
      content: "We can never look to men for help;no matter who they are, they can\u2019t
        save us,for even our great leaders fail and fall.They too are just mortals
        who will one day die.At death the spirits of all depart and their bodies
        return to dust.In the day of their death all their projects and plans are
        over."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But those who hope in the Lord will be happy and pleased!Our help
        comes from the God of Jacob!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You keep all your promises.You are the Creator of heaven\u2019s glory,earth\u2019s
        grandeur, and the ocean\u2019s greatness."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The oppressed get justice with you.The hungry are satisfied with you.Prisoners
        find their freedom with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You open the eyes of the blind,and you fully restore those bent over
        with shame.You love those who love and honor you.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You watch over strangers and immigrantsand support the fatherless
        and widows.But you subvert the plans of the ungodly.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Lord, you will reign forever!Zion\u2019s God will rule throughout
        time and eternity!Hallelujah! Praise the Lord!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Our Amazing God'
      title: Our Amazing God
      number: 1
      content: Hallelujah! Praise the Lord!How beautiful it is when we sing our praises
        to the beautiful God,for praise makes you lovely before himand brings him
        great delight!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> builds up Jerusalem;he gathers up the
        outcasts and brings them home.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He heals the wounds of every shattered heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: He sets his stars in place, calling them all by their names. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 147:4
        content: '  See  ;  ;  ;  .    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "How great is our God!There\u2019s absolutely nothing his power cannot
        accomplish,and he has infinite understanding of everything."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> supports and strengthens the humble,but
        the ungodly will be brought down to the dust.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Sing out with songs of thanksgiving to the Lord!Let\u2019s sing our
        praises with melodies overflowing!"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
